{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1781420769610,"sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","part":{"id":"prt_ec4f3c149001IQlFmWWMG6btkl","messageID":"msg_ec4f3baae001KbqlDyNudWl7Zx","sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","snapshot":"80e441d337a6e884e7b125bb97768c96ea4c2181","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1781420777152,"sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","part":{"id":"prt_ec4f3cad9001Fj2n2MhXhTEc4S","messageID":"msg_ec4f3baae001KbqlDyNudWl7Zx","sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","type":"text","text":"The workflow references confirm that this is a pre-bound autonomous lineage. I’m loading the YAML asset to follow the exact `phase_init`, `phase_main_loop`, and `phase_synthesis` steps, while skipping only the forbidden `resolveArtifactRoot` node as instructed.","time":{"start":1781420772057,"end":1781420777151},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_03b34aadf3fdd607016a2e52e4063081918bc2ff77a87cabd9","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781420777208,"sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_qDsCCjpKXelVy3CwLmaUhrEM","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-research-loop_auto.yaml","offset":1,"limit":500},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-research-loop_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n2: # DEEP RESEARCH: AUTONOMOUS DEEP RESEARCH LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n3: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n4: # YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT (S7 / M11):\n5: # - This asset does not currently use typed BooleanExpr predicates under\n6: #   `when:`; flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\n7: #   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\n8: # - `after:` carries prose timing / narrative notes if needed; `when:` in\n9: #   this file is reserved for future typed predicates and must NOT carry\n10: #   free-form narrative prose.\n11: # - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\n12: #   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\n13: #\n14: # GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION (T-YML-DPR-01 / paired with T-DOC-03 R50-001):\n15: # - `resume` is a tested WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files\n16: #   and JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as\n17: #   write-path below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger\n18: #   extraction can surface resume correctly rather than false-negative.\n19: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n20: role: Deep Research Loop Manager\n21: purpose: Iterative deep research with convergence detection\n22: action: Run deep-research loop from initialization through synthesis\n23: operating_mode:\n24:   workflow: iterative_loop\n25:   workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n26:   workflow_execution: autonomous\n27:   approvals: none\n28:   tracking: progressive_research_state\n29:   validation: convergence_detection\n30: \n31: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n32: # OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n33: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n34: operating_principles:\n35:   core: \"Fresh context per iteration + externalized state = no context degradation\"\n36:   approach: \"Dispatch focused agent, evaluate convergence, repeat or stop\"\n37:   mandate: \"Never hold findings in memory; write everything to files\"\n38: \n39: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n40: # USER INPUTS (from setup phase)\n41: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n42: user_inputs:\n43:   research_topic: \"[RESEARCH_TOPIC] - Topic to investigate deeply. REQUIRED.\"\n44:   spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Spec folder path. REQUIRED.\"\n45:   max_iterations: \"[MAX_ITERATIONS] - Maximum loop iterations. Default: 10.\"\n46:   convergence_threshold: \"[CONVERGENCE_THRESHOLD] - Stop threshold. Default: 0.05.\"\n47: \n48: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n49: # CONTEXT LOADING\n50: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n51: context_loading:\n52:   trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n53:   purpose: \"Load prior research context for the topic and buffer it until strategy.md exists\"\n54:   mcp_integration:\n55:     tool: memory_context\n56:     note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n57:     parameters: { input: \"{research_topic}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n58:   when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n59:   behavior:\n60:     if_context_found: \"Store full results as prior_context plus a concise prior_context_summary; inject after strategy.md is created.\"\n61:     if_no_context: \"Set prior_context and prior_context_summary to 'None' and continue.\"\n62: \n63: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n64: # SKILL REFERENCE\n65: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n66: skill_reference:\n67:   skill: deep-research\n68:   skill_md: .opencode/skills/deep-research/SKILL.md\n69:   references:\n70:     loop_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\n71:     spec_check_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\n72:     state_format: .opencode/skills/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md\n73:     convergence: .opencode/skills/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md\n74:   templates:\n75:     config: .opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json\n76:     strategy: .opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\n77: \n78: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n79: # AGENT CONFIGURATION\n80: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n81: agent_config:\n82:   agent: deep-research\n83:   agent_file: \".opencode/agents/deep-research.md\"\n84:   # Canonical path. Runtime-specific directories (e.g. .claude/agents/) reference this source.\n85:   model: opus\n86:   leaf_only: true\n87:   tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, WebFetch]\n88:   mcp_servers: [mk-spec-memory]\n89:   tool_call_budget: { target: 8, max: 12 }\n90: \n91: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n92: # STATE FILE PATHS\n93: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n94: state_paths:\n95:   # Template paths document the canonical packet layout. Runtime resolution happens via\n96:   # step_resolve_artifact_root plus the shared resolver, so root specs keep root-local\n97:   # research/ and child phases keep local research/ packet directories.\n98:   packet_dir: \"{artifact_dir}\"\n99:   config: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json\"\n100:   state_log: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-state.jsonl\"\n101:   strategy: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-strategy.md\"\n102:   registry: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-findings-registry.json\"\n103:   dashboard: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-dashboard.md\"\n104:   pause_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-pause\"\n105:   lock_file: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research.lock\"\n106:   prompt_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/prompts\"\n107:   iteration_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations\"\n108:   iteration_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\"\n109:   # Per-iteration structured delta stream (one file per iteration) — complement to the\n110:   # canonical state_log append. The delta file MUST contain at least one record whose\n111:   # `type === \"iteration\"` so the reducer can rehydrate iteration state after a partial\n112:   # run. Variants like `\"iteration_delta\"` are silently dropped by the reducer; the\n113:   # post_dispatch_validate step enforces the canonical type below.\n114:   delta_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas\"\n115:   delta_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl\"\n116:   research_output: \"{artifact_dir}/research.md\"\n117:   resource_map_output: \"{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md\"\n118:   archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n119:   synthesis_snapshot_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/synthesis-v{generation}.md\"\n120: \n121: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n122: # WORKFLOW\n123: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n124: workflow:\n125: \n126:   step_resolve_artifact_root:\n127:     description: \"Resolve artifact directory — use fan-out lineage override when provided, else resolve from spec_folder\"\n128:     note: \"Root specs keep research artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/research/. Child phases and sub-phases keep local packet directories in {spec_folder}/research/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/research_archive/{packet}/.\"\n129:     branch_on: \"config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\"\n130:     if_present:\n131:       bind:\n132:         artifact_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n133:         artifact_root_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n134:         artifact_subfolder: null\n135:         artifact_archive_root: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}/_archive\"\n136:     if_absent:\n137:       command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'research')));\\\"\"\n138:       outputs:\n139:         - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local research owner directory\"\n140:         - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n141:         - artifact_dir: \"Resolved research packet directory for this target\"\n142:         - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local research archive directory for this target\"\n143: \n144:   step_fanout_spawn:\n145:     description: \"Spawn fan-out lineages; skip and proceed to phase_init normally when single-executor\"\n146:     skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n147:     instructions: |\n148:       Fan-out mode is active. Spawn all lineages. Each lineage runs the full loop in its own\n149:       isolated sub-packet under {artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/.\n150:       After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis — skip phase_init and\n151:       phase_main_loop entirely (those are the single-executor path). The merge step in\n152:       phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n153:     sub_steps:\n154:       step_fanout_spawn_cli:\n155:         description: \"Spawn all CLI lineages in capped worker pool\"\n156:         skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind != 'native'\"\n157:         command: |\n158:           node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs \\\n159:             --spec-folder {spec_folder} \\\n160:             --loop-type research \\\n161:             --fanout-config-json '{config.fanout_json}' \\\n162:             --base-artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n163:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n164:         wait_for_completion: true\n165:       step_fanout_spawn_native:\n166:         description: \"Dispatch each native lineage as a sequential deep-research sub-agent\"\n167:         skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind == 'native'\"\n168:         for_each: \"lineage in expanded native entries of config.fanout\"\n169:         dispatch:\n170:           agent: deep-research\n171:           model: opus\n172:           context: |\n173:             Execute the deep-research loop with these parameters:\n174:               spec_folder: {spec_folder}\n175:               config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: {artifact_dir}/lineages/{lineage.label}\n176:               session_id: fanout-{lineage.label}-{fanout_run_id}\n177:               executor: native\n178:             Run to convergence. Write all outputs to the override directory.\n179:         wait_for_completion: true\n180: \n181:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n182:   # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n183:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n184:   phase_init:\n185:     purpose: Create all state files for the research session\n186:     steps:\n187: \n188:       step_preflight_contract:\n189:         action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n190:         verify:\n191:           - required_values_present: [research_topic, spec_folder, max_iterations, convergence_threshold]\n192:           - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation)\"\n193:           - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n194:           - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n195:         on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n196: \n197:       step_create_directories:\n198:         action: \"Create spec folder and research packet directories if they don't exist\"\n199:         command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir}\"\n200: \n201:       step_detect_resource_map:\n202:         action: \"Detect resource-map.md before config creation so init can persist the flag and seed Known Context\"\n203:         inspect:\n204:           - \"{spec_folder}/resource-map.md\"\n205:         classify:\n206:           present: \"resource-map.md exists at init\"\n207:           absent: \"resource-map.md does not exist at init\"\n208:         outputs:\n209:           - resource_map_present: \"Boolean true when {spec_folder}/resource-map.md exists, else false\"\n210:           - resource_map_known_context: \"When present: summarize the map by section with entry counts across READMEs, Documents, Commands, Agents, Skills, Specs, Scripts, Tests, Config, and Meta, plus a one-line theme summary for each section. When absent: 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n211: \n212:       step_resolve_canonical_names:\n213:         action: \"Resolve canonical research packet artifact names before classification\"\n214:         inspect_legacy:\n215:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/config.json\"\n216:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/state.jsonl\"\n217:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/strategy.md\"\n218:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/dashboard.md\"\n219:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/.pause\"\n220:         migration_policy: \"dual-read / single-write for 4 weeks\"\n221:         on_legacy_read:\n222:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"migration\",\"legacyPath\":\"{legacy_path}\",\"canonicalPath\":\"{canonical_path}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n223: \n224:       step_acquire_lock:\n225:         action: \"Acquire the advisory lock defined by the spec_check_protocol before session classification\"\n226:         command: \"Open {state_paths.lock_file} with exclusive non-blocking advisory locking semantics; fail closed on contention.\"\n227:         note: \"macOS/BSD locking here is advisory. Stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n228:         # <!-- F-010-B5-01 -->\n229:         # Lock-cleanup contract: the lock file MUST be released on every terminal exit path that follows acquisition.\n230:         # Runtimes honoring step_acquire_lock are required to perform this cleanup before halting or pausing.\n231:         on_halt:\n232:           action: \"Release {state_paths.lock_file} before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n233:           applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\", \"step_preinit_spec_branch.conflict-detected\"]\n234:           command: \"Remove or close-with-release {state_paths.lock_file}; failures here are logged but do not block the halt\"\n235:         on_cancel:\n236:           action: \"Release {state_paths.lock_file} on user cancel or pause-sentinel detection before sentinel processing\"\n237:           command: \"Remove or close-with-release {state_paths.lock_file}; cancel completes regardless of cleanup result\"\n238:         on_workflow_exit:\n239:           action: \"Release {state_paths.lock_file} as the final step of any workflow exit path (success or failure)\"\n240:           command: \"Remove or close-with-release {state_paths.lock_file}; idempotent — safe to invoke when already released\"\n241: \n242:       step_classify_session:\n243:         action: \"Classify the session before writing files\"\n244:         inspect:\n245:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n246:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n247:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n248:         classify:\n249:           fresh: \"None of the three state artifacts exist\"\n250:           resume: \"Config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and agree on topic/spec folder\"\n251:           completed-session: \"Resume artifacts exist and config.status == 'complete'\"\n252:           invalid-state: \"Any partial, missing, or contradictory combination\"\n253:         outputs:\n254:           - session_state: \"fresh | resume | completed-session | invalid-state\"\n255:         on_resume:\n256:           # T-YML-DPR-01 / R50-001: Resume is a WRITE-PATH. Produces `iteration-NNN.md` + JSONL appends.\n257:           # Paired with T-DOC-03 Gate 3 trigger addition (resume, save context, save memory, /memory:save).\n258:           gate3_classification: write-path\n259:           gate3_rationale: \"resume produces iteration-NNN.md writes and JSONL state-log appends\"\n260:           log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n261:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n262:           skip_to: phase_loop\n263:         on_restart:\n264:           action: \"Archive the current research packet under the root-level research_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n265:           command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n266:           set:\n267:             lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n268:             parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n269:             generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n270:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n271:           skip_to: step_create_config\n272:         note_deferred_branches: \"fork and completed-continue are deferred and no longer runtime-supported in this release. The reducer still reads `lineageMode` from config for dashboards and analysis, but only `new`, `resume`, and `restart` are live. See deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branch Contract for the one-session contract.\"\n273:         on_completed_session:\n274:           log: \"Prior session already completed. Do not route directly to synthesis; archive the completed research/ tree or start a fresh packet instead.\"\n275:           halt: true\n276:           message: \"Completed deep-research packet detected. Archive or replace the existing research/ tree before starting a new session.\"\n277:         on_invalid_state:\n278:           halt: true\n279:           message: \"Existing deep-research state is incomplete or contradictory. Repair or archive the invalid research packet before continuing.\"\n280:         on_fresh:\n281:           action: \"Proceed with a new session\"\n282: \n283:       step_create_config:\n284:         action: \"Create deep-research-config.json from template\"\n285:         template: .opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json\n286:         populate:\n287:           topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n288:           maxIterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n289:           # Semantic: newInfoRatio with negative-knowledge emphasis. See SKILL.md §\"Convergence Threshold Semantics\".\n290:           convergenceThreshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n291:           stuckThreshold: 3\n292:           maxDurationMinutes: 120\n293:           specFolder: \"{spec_folder}\"\n294:           resource_map_present: \"{resource_map_present}\"\n295:           # <!-- F-010-B5-04 -->\n296:           # Honor the parsed --no-resource-map flag from deep-research.md:73 (default true; false when flag is set).\n297:           # The markdown command parses $ARGUMENTS and binds {resource_map_emit} before this step runs.\n298:           resource_map.emit: \"{resource_map_emit}\"\n299:           createdAt: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n300:           status: \"initialized\"\n301:           executionMode: \"auto\"\n302:           lineage.sessionId: \"{AUTO_SESSION_ID}\"\n303:           lineage.parentSessionId: null\n304:           lineage.lineageMode: \"new\"\n305:           lineage.generation: 1\n306:           lineage.continuedFromRun: null\n307:         output: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n308: \n309:       step_create_state_log:\n310:         action: \"Initialize JSONL state log with config record\"\n311:         # <!-- F-010-B5-04 -->\n312:         # Same parsed --no-resource-map flag honored here so config and state_log agree from line 1.\n313:         content: '{\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"{research_topic}\",\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"convergenceThreshold\":{convergence_threshold},\"resource_map_present\":{resource_map_present},\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":{resource_map_emit}},\"createdAt\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\"}'\n314:         output: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n315: \n316:       step_create_strategy:\n317:         action: \"Create strategy file from template with initial questions\"\n318:         template: .opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\n319:         populate:\n320:           topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n321:           key_questions: \"Derive 3-5 key questions from the research topic\"\n322:           known_context: \"None\"\n323:           known_context_summary: \"None\"\n324:           max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n325:           convergence_threshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n326:         output: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n327: \n328:       step_create_registry:\n329:         action: \"Initialize reducer-owned findings registry\"\n330:         content: '{\"openQuestions\":[],\"resolvedQuestions\":[],\"keyFindings\":[],\"ruledOutDirections\":[],\"metrics\":{\"iterationsCompleted\":0,\"openQuestions\":0,\"resolvedQuestions\":0,\"keyFindings\":0,\"convergenceScore\":0,\"coverageBySources\":{}}}'\n331:         output: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n332: \n333:       step_enrich_strategy_context:\n334:         action: \"Ensure Known Context is written only after strategy.md exists\"\n335:         condition: \"prior_context_found\"\n336:         edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n337:         note: \"Append or replace the Known Context section with prior_context_summary and retained detail from prior_context\"\n338: \n339:       step_enrich_strategy_resource_map:\n340:         action: \"Inject resource-map status into Known Context after strategy.md exists\"\n341:         edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n342:         note: \"When resource_map_present is true, append the resource_map_known_context snapshot. When false, append 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n343: \n344:       step_detect_spec_present:\n345:         action: \"Classify late-INIT spec.md state after the durable research packet exists\"\n346:         inspect:\n347:           - \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n348:           - \"{state_paths.lock_file}\"\n349:         classify:\n350:           no-spec: \"spec.md is absent before any pre-init mutation\"\n351:           spec-present: \"spec.md exists and approved host anchors are available for bounded mutation\"\n352:           spec-just-created-by-this-run: \"spec.md already carries this run's DR seed markers and should not be reseeded\"\n353:           conflict-detected: \"missing host anchor, duplicate markers, or generated-block ambiguity makes mutation unsafe\"\n354:         outputs:\n355:           - folder_state: \"no-spec | spec-present | spec-just-created-by-this-run | conflict-detected\"\n356:           - normalized_topic: \"Trim, lowercase, and collapse whitespace in research_topic before dedupe checks\"\n357:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"spec_check_result\",\"folder_state\":\"{folder_state}\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"lockPath\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n358: \n359:       step_preinit_spec_branch:\n360:         action: \"Run the bounded pre-init spec branch required by spec_check_protocol\"\n361:         protocol_reference: \".opencode/skills/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\"\n362:         branches:\n363:           no-spec:\n364:             create: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n365:             seed_markers:\n366:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n367:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n368:             requirements_host: \"Seed Requirements from the research ask without broadening scope\"\n369:             scope_host: \"Seed Scope from the research ask without inventing implementation details\"\n370:             set:\n371:               folder_state: \"spec-just-created-by-this-run\"\n372:               validate_spec_doc: true\n373:             append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_seed_created\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-just-created-by-this-run\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Requirements\",\"Scope\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Seeded Level 1 spec.md from research topic with DR seed markers.\",\"seed_markers\":[\"DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS\",\"DR-SEED:SCOPE\"],\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n374:           spec-present:\n375:             edit: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n376:             set:\n377:               validate_spec_doc: true\n378:             idempotency_check:\n379:               host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n380:               normalized_match: \"Normalize the existing anchor text by lowercasing, stripping punctuation, collapsing whitespace, and trimming before comparing with {normalized_topic}.\"\n381:               if_match:\n382:                 skip_append: true\n383:                 append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_deduped\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Skipped duplicate pre-init topic append because normalized topic already exists in Open Questions.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n384:               if_no_match:\n385:                 append_only:\n386:                   - host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n387:                     content: \"Add the normalized research topic only if it is not already present.\"\n388:                   - host_anchor: \"Research Context\"\n389:                     content: \"Add a bounded note that deep-research is active for this topic and that research/research.md remains canonical.\"\n390:                 append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_added\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\",\"Research Context\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Appended bounded pre-init research context for the normalized topic.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n391:           spec-just-created-by-this-run:\n392:             verify_markers:\n393:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n394:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n395:             set:\n396:               validate_spec_doc: false\n397:             note: \"Treat already-seeded spec.md as a no-op guard and continue.\"\n398:           conflict-detected:\n399:             append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_mutation_conflict\",\"folder_state\":\"conflict-detected\",\"reason\":\"Pre-init spec.md mutation is ambiguous or unsafe.\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n400:             halt: true\n401: \n402:       step_validate_preinit_spec_doc:\n403:         action: \"Run targeted strict validation after any deep-research pre-init spec.md mutation\"\n404:         condition: \"validate_spec_doc\"\n405:         command: \"SPECKIT_RULES=FRONTMATTER_VALID,LEVEL_DECLARED,TEMPLATE_SOURCE,TEMPLATE_HEADERS,PLACEHOLDER_FILLED,SECTIONS_PRESENT,ANCHORS_VALID,SPEC_DOC_INTEGRITY,TOC_POLICY bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh {spec_folder} --strict\"\n406:         note: \"This enforces the authored-spec markdown structural contract without applying full-packet required-file or completeness checks to workflow-owned research artifacts. It uses the Node validation orchestrator, whose strict path was measured at about 108ms for a fresh Level 3 packet on the local harness.\"\n407: \n408:       step_init_complete:\n409:         log: \"Initialization complete. Config, state, and strategy files created.\"\n410:         set: { current_iteration: 1, current_segment: 1, stuck_count: 0 }\n411: \n412:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n413:   # PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n414:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n415:   phase_loop:\n416:     purpose: Dispatch agent iterations until convergence\n417:     repeat: true\n418:     max_repeats: \"{max_iterations}\"\n419:     steps:\n420: \n421:       step_read_state:\n422:         action: \"Read current state from JSONL and strategy\"\n423:         read:\n424:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n425:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n426:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n427:         extract:\n428:           - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n429:           - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n430:           - current_segment: \"Latest segment_start event segment, else 1\"\n431:           - last_newInfoRatio: \"Extract newInfoRatio from last iteration record\"\n432:           - last_focus: \"Extract focus from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n433:           - ratio_prev: \"Extract newInfoRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n434:           - ratio_latest: \"Extract newInfoRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n435:           - next_focus: \"Extract 'Next Focus' section from strategy.md\"\n436:           - remaining_questions: \"Count unchecked items in 'Key Questions'\"\n437:           - remaining_questions_list: \"List unchecked key questions from strategy.md\"\n438:           - answered_count: \"Count answered questions from strategy.md\"\n439:           - total_questions: \"Count total questions tracked in strategy.md\"\n440:           - resource_map_present: \"Extract boolean from deep-research-config.json, default false\"\n441:           - resource_map_prompt_line: \"If resource_map_present is true, return 'Resource map: prior-inventoried files are listed in {spec_folder}/resource-map.md; treat them as the exclusion set when hunting for net-new files; flag only missed-from-map candidates as gaps.' Else return 'Resource map: resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.'\"\n442:           - least_explored: \"First unanswered question not covered by the most recent iteration focus, else first unanswered question\"\n443:           - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'run N: focus (ratio)'\"\n444:           - latest_status: \"Extract status from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n445: \n446:       step_check_pause_sentinel:\n447:         action: \"Check for pause sentinel file\"\n448:         check: \"Does {state_paths.pause_sentinel} exist?\"\n449:         if_exists:\n450:           log_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n451:           message: \"Research paused. Delete research/.deep-research-pause to resume.\"\n452:           halt: true\n453:         if_not_exists:\n454:           proceed: true\n455: \n456:       step_graph_convergence:\n457:         action: \"Evaluate coverage-graph convergence before the inline 3-signal vote and persist the graph decision snapshot\"\n458:         bash: 'node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs --spec-folder \"{spec_folder}\" --loop-type \"research\" --session-id \"{config.lineage.sessionId}\"'\n459:         note: \"Run before the inline vote. STOP from the inline 3-signal vote is allowed only when the graph decision is STOP_ALLOWED or absent.\"\n460:         outputs:\n461:           - graph_decision: \"Tool decision value (CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED), else null when unavailable\"\n462:           - graph_decision_json: \"JSON-encoded graph decision string, else null\"\n463:           - graph_signals_json: \"Tool signals object, else {}\"\n464:           - graph_blockers_json: \"Tool blockers array, else []\"\n465:           - graph_trace_json: \"Tool trace payload, else []\"\n466:           - graph_convergence_score: \"signals.blendedScore when present, else the best available graph score, else 0\"\n467:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"graph_convergence\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"decision\":{graph_decision_json},\"signals\":{graph_signals_json},\"blockers\":{graph_blockers_json},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n468: \n469:       step_check_convergence:\n470:         action: \"Evaluate stop conditions and combine the inline 3-signal vote with graph convergence\"\n471:         algorithm: |\n472:           1. if iteration_count >= max_iterations: STOP (maxIterationsReached). This terminal cap bypasses quality-guard overrides; record failed guards/blockers as synthesis evidence instead of continuing.\n473:           2. if remaining_questions == 0: STOP (all_questions_answered)\n474:           3. if stuck_count >= config.stuckThreshold: STUCK_RECOVERY\n475:           4. GRAPH-ASSISTED COMPOSITE CONVERGENCE:\n476:                step_graph_convergence already recorded graph_decision, graph_signals_json, graph_blockers_json, and graph_convergence_score for this run.\n477:                The existing inline 3-signal vote still computes the inline STOP candidate and is not replaced.\n478:                signals = []\n479:                Filter: exclude iterations where status == thought from signal inputs (use only evidence iterations)\n480:                a) Rolling average (w=0.30, needs 3+ iterations):\n481:                   avg = mean(last 3 newInfoRatios)\n482:                   stop if avg < convergence_threshold\n483:                b) MAD noise floor (w=0.35, needs 4+ iterations):\n484:                   noiseFloor = MAD(all ratios) * 1.4826\n485:                   stop if latest ratio <= noiseFloor\n486:                c) Question entropy (w=0.35):\n487:                   coverage = answered / total questions\n488:                   stop if coverage >= 0.85\n489:                Redistribute weights for unavailable signals.\n490:                if weighted_stop_score > 0.60: inline_stop_candidate = true\n491:                Combined stop rule: STOP only if the inline 3-signal vote says STOP AND graph_decision is STOP_ALLOWED or absent.\n492:                if inline_stop_candidate and graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\":\n493:                  decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n494:                  reason = \"blockedStop\"\n495:                  stop_blocked = true\n496:                  blocked_by_json = JSON array derived from graph_blockers_json\n497:                  blocked_by_csv = comma-separated blocker names derived from graph_blockers_json\n498:                  gate_convergence_pass = false\n499:                  gate_convergence_score = graph_convergence_score\n500:                  gate_key_question_coverage_pass = no blocker named questionCoverage\n\n(Showing lines 1-500 of 1079. Use offset=501 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP RESEARCH: AUTONOMOUS DEEP RESEARCH LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT (S7 / M11):\n# - This asset does not currently use typed BooleanExpr predicates under\n#   `when:`; flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\n#   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\n# - `after:` carries prose timing / narrative notes if needed; `when:` in\n#   this file is reserved for future typed predicates and must NOT carry\n#   free-form narrative prose.\n# - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\n#   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\n#\n# GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION (T-YML-DPR-01 / paired with T-DOC-03 R50-001):\n# - `resume` is a tested WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files\n#   and JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as\n#   write-path below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger\n#   extraction can surface resume correctly rather than false-negative.\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrole: Deep Research Loop Manager","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-research-loop_auto.yaml","text":"# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP RESEARCH: AUTONOMOUS DEEP RESEARCH LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT (S7 / M11):\n# - This asset does not currently use typed BooleanExpr predicates under\n#   `when:`; flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\n#   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\n# - `after:` carries prose timing / narrative notes if needed; `when:` in\n#   this file is reserved for future typed predicates and must NOT carry\n#   free-form narrative prose.\n# - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\n#   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\n#\n# GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION (T-YML-DPR-01 / paired with T-DOC-03 R50-001):\n# - `resume` is a tested WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files\n#   and JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as\n#   write-path below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger\n#   extraction can surface resume correctly rather than false-negative.\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrole: Deep Research Loop Manager\npurpose: Iterative deep research with convergence detection\naction: Run deep-research loop from initialization through synthesis\noperating_mode:\n  workflow: iterative_loop\n  workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n  workflow_execution: autonomous\n  approvals: none\n  tracking: progressive_research_state\n  validation: convergence_detection\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\noperating_principles:\n  core: \"Fresh context per iteration + externalized state = no context degradation\"\n  approach: \"Dispatch focused agent, evaluate convergence, repeat or stop\"\n  mandate: \"Never hold findings in memory; write everything to files\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# USER INPUTS (from setup phase)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nuser_inputs:\n  research_topic: \"[RESEARCH_TOPIC] - Topic to investigate deeply. REQUIRED.\"\n  spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Spec folder path. REQUIRED.\"\n  max_iterations: \"[MAX_ITERATIONS] - Maximum loop iterations. Default: 10.\"\n  convergence_threshold: \"[CONVERGENCE_THRESHOLD] - Stop threshold. Default: 0.05.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# CONTEXT LOADING\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\ncontext_loading:\n  trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n  purpose: \"Load prior research context for the topic and buffer it until strategy.md exists\"\n  mcp_integration:\n    tool: memory_context\n    note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n    parameters: { input: \"{research_topic}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n  when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n  behavior:\n    if_context_found: \"Store full results as prior_context plus a concise prior_context_summary; inject after strategy.md is created.\"\n    if_no_context: \"Set prior_context and prior_context_summary to 'None' and continue.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# SKILL REFERENCE\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nskill_reference:\n  skill: deep-research\n  skill_md: .opencode/skills/deep-research/SKILL.md\n  references:\n    loop_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\n    spec_check_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\n    state_format: .opencode/skills/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md\n    convergence: .opencode/skills/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md\n  templates:\n    config: .opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json\n    strategy: .opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# AGENT CONFIGURATION\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nagent_config:\n  agent: deep-research\n  agent_file: \".opencode/agents/deep-research.md\"\n  # Canonical path. Runtime-specific directories (e.g. .claude/agents/) reference this source.\n  model: opus\n  leaf_only: true\n  tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, WebFetch]\n  mcp_servers: [mk-spec-memory]\n  tool_call_budget: { target: 8, max: 12 }\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# STATE FILE PATHS\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nstate_paths:\n  # Template paths document the canonical packet layout. Runtime resolution happens via\n  # step_resolve_artifact_root plus the shared resolver, so root specs keep root-local\n  # research/ and child phases keep local research/ packet directories.\n  packet_dir: \"{artifact_dir}\"\n  config: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json\"\n  state_log: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-state.jsonl\"\n  strategy: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-strategy.md\"\n  registry: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-findings-registry.json\"\n  dashboard: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-dashboard.md\"\n  pause_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-pause\"\n  lock_file: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research.lock\"\n  prompt_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/prompts\"\n  iteration_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations\"\n  iteration_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\"\n  # Per-iteration structured delta stream (one file per iteration) — complement to the\n  # canonical state_log append. The delta file MUST contain at least one record whose\n  # `type === \"iteration\"` so the reducer can rehydrate iteration state after a partial\n  # run. Variants like `\"iteration_delta\"` are silently dropped by the reducer; the\n  # post_dispatch_validate step enforces the canonical type below.\n  delta_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas\"\n  delta_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl\"\n  research_output: \"{artifact_dir}/research.md\"\n  resource_map_output: \"{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md\"\n  archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n  synthesis_snapshot_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/synthesis-v{generation}.md\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# WORKFLOW\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nworkflow:\n\n  step_resolve_artifact_root:\n    description: \"Resolve artifact directory — use fan-out lineage override when provided, else resolve from spec_folder\"\n    note: \"Root specs keep research artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/research/. Child phases and sub-phases keep local packet directories in {spec_folder}/research/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/research_archive/{packet}/.\"\n    branch_on: \"config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\"\n    if_present:\n      bind:\n        artifact_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n        artifact_root_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n        artifact_subfolder: null\n        artifact_archive_root: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}/_archive\"\n    if_absent:\n      command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'research')));\\\"\"\n      outputs:\n        - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local research owner directory\"\n        - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n        - artifact_dir: \"Resolved research packet directory for this target\"\n        - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local research archive directory for this target\"\n\n  step_fanout_spawn:\n    description: \"Spawn fan-out lineages; skip and proceed to phase_init normally when single-executor\"\n    skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n    instructions: |\n      Fan-out mode is active. Spawn all lineages. Each lineage runs the full loop in its own\n      isolated sub-packet under {artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/.\n      After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis — skip phase_init and\n      phase_main_loop entirely (those are the single-executor path). The merge step in\n      phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n    sub_steps:\n      step_fanout_spawn_cli:\n        description: \"Spawn all CLI lineages in capped worker pool\"\n        skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind != 'native'\"\n        command: |\n          node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs \\\n            --spec-folder {spec_folder} \\\n            --loop-type research \\\n            --fanout-config-json '{config.fanout_json}' \\\n            --base-artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        wait_for_completion: true\n      step_fanout_spawn_native:\n        description: \"Dispatch each native lineage as a sequential deep-research sub-agent\"\n        skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind == 'native'\"\n        for_each: \"lineage in expanded native entries of config.fanout\"\n        dispatch:\n          agent: deep-research\n          model: opus\n          context: |\n            Execute the deep-research loop with these parameters:\n              spec_folder: {spec_folder}\n              config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: {artifact_dir}/lineages/{lineage.label}\n              session_id: fanout-{lineage.label}-{fanout_run_id}\n              executor: native\n            Run to convergence. Write all outputs to the override directory.\n        wait_for_completion: true\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_init:\n    purpose: Create all state files for the research session\n    steps:\n\n      step_preflight_contract:\n        action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n        verify:\n          - required_values_present: [research_topic, spec_folder, max_iterations, convergence_threshold]\n          - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation)\"\n          - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n          - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n        on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n\n      step_create_directories:\n        action: \"Create spec folder and research packet directories if they don't exist\"\n        command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir}\"\n\n      step_detect_resource_map:\n        action: \"Detect resource-map.md before config creation so init can persist the flag and seed Known Context\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{spec_folder}/resource-map.md\"\n        classify:\n          present: \"resource-map.md exists at init\"\n          absent: \"resource-map.md does not exist at init\"\n        outputs:\n          - resource_map_present: \"Boolean true when {spec_folder}/resource-map.md exists, else false\"\n          - resource_map_known_context: \"When present: summarize the map by section with entry counts across READMEs, Documents, Commands, Agents, Skills, Specs, Scripts, Tests, Config, and Meta, plus a one-line theme summary for each section. When absent: 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n\n      step_resolve_canonical_names:\n        action: \"Resolve canonical research packet artifact names before classification\"\n        inspect_legacy:\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/config.json\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/state.jsonl\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/strategy.md\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/dashboard.md\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/.pause\"\n        migration_policy: \"dual-read / single-write for 4 weeks\"\n        on_legacy_read:\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"migration\",\"legacyPath\":\"{legacy_path}\",\"canonicalPath\":\"{canonical_path}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n      step_acquire_lock:\n        action: \"Acquire the advisory lock defined by the spec_check_protocol before session classification\"\n        command: \"Open {state_paths.lock_file} with exclusive non-blocking advisory locking semantics; fail closed on contention.\"\n        note: \"macOS/BSD locking here is advisory. Stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n        # <!-- F-010-B5-01 -->\n        # Lock-cleanup contract: the lock file MUST be released on every terminal exit path that follows acquisition.\n        # Runtimes honoring step_acquire_lock are required to perform this cleanup before halting or pausing.\n        on_halt:\n          action: \"Release {state_paths.lock_file} before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n          applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\", \"step_preinit_spec_branch.conflict-detected\"]\n          command: \"Remove or close-with-release {state_paths.lock_file}; failures here are logged but do not block the halt\"\n        on_cancel:\n          action: \"Release {state_paths.lock_file} on user cancel or pause-sentinel detection before sentinel processing\"\n          command: \"Remove or close-with-release {state_paths.lock_file}; cancel completes regardless of cleanup result\"\n        on_workflow_exit:\n          action: \"Release {state_paths.lock_file} as the final step of any workflow exit path (success or failure)\"\n          command: \"Remove or close-with-release {state_paths.lock_file}; idempotent — safe to invoke when already released\"\n\n      step_classify_session:\n        action: \"Classify the session before writing files\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        classify:\n          fresh: \"None of the three state artifacts exist\"\n          resume: \"Config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and agree on topic/spec folder\"\n          completed-session: \"Resume artifacts exist and config.status == 'complete'\"\n          invalid-state: \"Any partial, missing, or contradictory combination\"\n        outputs:\n          - session_state: \"fresh | resume | completed-session | invalid-state\"\n        on_resume:\n          # T-YML-DPR-01 / R50-001: Resume is a WRITE-PATH. Produces `iteration-NNN.md` + JSONL appends.\n          # Paired with T-DOC-03 Gate 3 trigger addition (resume, save context, save memory, /memory:save).\n          gate3_classification: write-path\n          gate3_rationale: \"resume produces iteration-NNN.md writes and JSONL state-log appends\"\n          log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: phase_loop\n        on_restart:\n          action: \"Archive the current research packet under the root-level research_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n          command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n          set:\n            lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n            parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n            generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: step_create_config\n        note_deferred_branches: \"fork and completed-continue are deferred and no longer runtime-supported in this release. The reducer still reads `lineageMode` from config for dashboards and analysis, but only `new`, `resume`, and `restart` are live. See deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branch Contract for the one-session contract.\"\n        on_completed_session:\n          log: \"Prior session already completed. Do not route directly to synthesis; archive the completed research/ tree or start a fresh packet instead.\"\n          halt: true\n          message: \"Completed deep-research packet detected. Archive or replace the existing research/ tree before starting a new session.\"\n        on_invalid_state:\n          halt: true\n          message: \"Existing deep-research state is incomplete or contradictory. Repair or archive the invalid research packet before continuing.\"\n        on_fresh:\n          action: \"Proceed with a new session\"\n\n      step_create_config:\n        action: \"Create deep-research-config.json from template\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json\n        populate:\n          topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n          maxIterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n          # Semantic: newInfoRatio with negative-knowledge emphasis. See SKILL.md §\"Convergence Threshold Semantics\".\n          convergenceThreshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n          stuckThreshold: 3\n          maxDurationMinutes: 120\n          specFolder: \"{spec_folder}\"\n          resource_map_present: \"{resource_map_present}\"\n          # <!-- F-010-B5-04 -->\n          # Honor the parsed --no-resource-map flag from deep-research.md:73 (default true; false when flag is set).\n          # The markdown command parses $ARGUMENTS and binds {resource_map_emit} before this step runs.\n          resource_map.emit: \"{resource_map_emit}\"\n          createdAt: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n          status: \"initialized\"\n          executionMode: \"auto\"\n          lineage.sessionId: \"{AUTO_SESSION_ID}\"\n          lineage.parentSessionId: null\n          lineage.lineageMode: \"new\"\n          lineage.generation: 1\n          lineage.continuedFromRun: null\n        output: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n\n      step_create_state_log:\n        action: \"Initialize JSONL state log with config record\"\n        # <!-- F-010-B5-04 -->\n        # Same parsed --no-resource-map flag honored here so config and state_log agree from line 1.\n        content: '{\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"{research_topic}\",\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"convergenceThreshold\":{convergence_threshold},\"resource_map_present\":{resource_map_present},\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":{resource_map_emit}},\"createdAt\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\"}'\n        output: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n\n      step_create_strategy:\n        action: \"Create strategy file from template with initial questions\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\n        populate:\n          topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n          key_questions: \"Derive 3-5 key questions from the research topic\"\n          known_context: \"None\"\n          known_context_summary: \"None\"\n          max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n          convergence_threshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n        output: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n\n      step_create_registry:\n        action: \"Initialize reducer-owned findings registry\"\n        content: '{\"openQuestions\":[],\"resolvedQuestions\":[],\"keyFindings\":[],\"ruledOutDirections\":[],\"metrics\":{\"iterationsCompleted\":0,\"openQuestions\":0,\"resolvedQuestions\":0,\"keyFindings\":0,\"convergenceScore\":0,\"coverageBySources\":{}}}'\n        output: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n\n      step_enrich_strategy_context:\n        action: \"Ensure Known Context is written only after strategy.md exists\"\n        condition: \"prior_context_found\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        note: \"Append or replace the Known Context section with prior_context_summary and retained detail from prior_context\"\n\n      step_enrich_strategy_resource_map:\n        action: \"Inject resource-map status into Known Context after strategy.md exists\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        note: \"When resource_map_present is true, append the resource_map_known_context snapshot. When false, append 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n\n      step_detect_spec_present:\n        action: \"Classify late-INIT spec.md state after the durable research packet exists\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n          - \"{state_paths.lock_file}\"\n        classify:\n          no-spec: \"spec.md is absent before any pre-init mutation\"\n          spec-present: \"spec.md exists and approved host anchors are available for bounded mutation\"\n          spec-just-created-by-this-run: \"spec.md already carries this run's DR seed markers and should not be reseeded\"\n          conflict-detected: \"missing host anchor, duplicate markers, or generated-block ambiguity makes mutation unsafe\"\n        outputs:\n          - folder_state: \"no-spec | spec-present | spec-just-created-by-this-run | conflict-detected\"\n          - normalized_topic: \"Trim, lowercase, and collapse whitespace in research_topic before dedupe checks\"\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"spec_check_result\",\"folder_state\":\"{folder_state}\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"lockPath\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n      step_preinit_spec_branch:\n        action: \"Run the bounded pre-init spec branch required by spec_check_protocol\"\n        protocol_reference: \".opencode/skills/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\"\n        branches:\n          no-spec:\n            create: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n            seed_markers:\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n            requirements_host: \"Seed Requirements from the research ask without broadening scope\"\n            scope_host: \"Seed Scope from the research ask without inventing implementation details\"\n            set:\n              folder_state: \"spec-just-created-by-this-run\"\n              validate_spec_doc: true\n            append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_seed_created\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-just-created-by-this-run\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Requirements\",\"Scope\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Seeded Level 1 spec.md from research topic with DR seed markers.\",\"seed_markers\":[\"DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS\",\"DR-SEED:SCOPE\"],\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          spec-present:\n            edit: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n            set:\n              validate_spec_doc: true\n            idempotency_check:\n              host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n              normalized_match: \"Normalize the existing anchor text by lowercasing, stripping punctuation, collapsing whitespace, and trimming before comparing with {normalized_topic}.\"\n              if_match:\n                skip_append: true\n                append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_deduped\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Skipped duplicate pre-init topic append because normalized topic already exists in Open Questions.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n              if_no_match:\n                append_only:\n                  - host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n                    content: \"Add the normalized research topic only if it is not already present.\"\n                  - host_anchor: \"Research Context\"\n                    content: \"Add a bounded note that deep-research is active for this topic and that research/research.md remains canonical.\"\n                append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_added\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\",\"Research Context\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Appended bounded pre-init research context for the normalized topic.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          spec-just-created-by-this-run:\n            verify_markers:\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n            set:\n              validate_spec_doc: false\n            note: \"Treat already-seeded spec.md as a no-op guard and continue.\"\n          conflict-detected:\n            append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_mutation_conflict\",\"folder_state\":\"conflict-detected\",\"reason\":\"Pre-init spec.md mutation is ambiguous or unsafe.\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n            halt: true\n\n      step_validate_preinit_spec_doc:\n        action: \"Run targeted strict validation after any deep-research pre-init spec.md mutation\"\n        condition: \"validate_spec_doc\"\n        command: \"SPECKIT_RULES=FRONTMATTER_VALID,LEVEL_DECLARED,TEMPLATE_SOURCE,TEMPLATE_HEADERS,PLACEHOLDER_FILLED,SECTIONS_PRESENT,ANCHORS_VALID,SPEC_DOC_INTEGRITY,TOC_POLICY bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh {spec_folder} --strict\"\n        note: \"This enforces the authored-spec markdown structural contract without applying full-packet required-file or completeness checks to workflow-owned research artifacts. It uses the Node validation orchestrator, whose strict path was measured at about 108ms for a fresh Level 3 packet on the local harness.\"\n\n      step_init_complete:\n        log: \"Initialization complete. Config, state, and strategy files created.\"\n        set: { current_iteration: 1, current_segment: 1, stuck_count: 0 }\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_loop:\n    purpose: Dispatch agent iterations until convergence\n    repeat: true\n    max_repeats: \"{max_iterations}\"\n    steps:\n\n      step_read_state:\n        action: \"Read current state from JSONL and strategy\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n        extract:\n          - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n          - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n          - current_segment: \"Latest segment_start event segment, else 1\"\n          - last_newInfoRatio: \"Extract newInfoRatio from last iteration record\"\n          - last_focus: \"Extract focus from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n          - ratio_prev: \"Extract newInfoRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - ratio_latest: \"Extract newInfoRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - next_focus: \"Extract 'Next Focus' section from strategy.md\"\n          - remaining_questions: \"Count unchecked items in 'Key Questions'\"\n          - remaining_questions_list: \"List unchecked key questions from strategy.md\"\n          - answered_count: \"Count answered questions from strategy.md\"\n          - total_questions: \"Count total questions tracked in strategy.md\"\n          - resource_map_present: \"Extract boolean from deep-research-config.json, default false\"\n          - resource_map_prompt_line: \"If resource_map_present is true, return 'Resource map: prior-inventoried files are listed in {spec_folder}/resource-map.md; treat them as the exclusion set when hunting for net-new files; flag only missed-from-map candidates as gaps.' Else return 'Resource map: resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.'\"\n          - least_explored: \"First unanswered question not covered by the most recent iteration focus, else first unanswered question\"\n          - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'run N: focus (ratio)'\"\n          - latest_status: \"Extract status from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n\n      step_check_pause_sentinel:\n        action: \"Check for pause sentinel file\"\n        check: \"Does {state_paths.pause_sentinel} exist?\"\n        if_exists:\n          log_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          message: \"Research paused. Delete research/.deep-research-pause to resume.\"\n          halt: true\n        if_not_exists:\n          proceed: true\n\n      step_graph_convergence:\n        action: \"Evaluate coverage-graph convergence before the inline 3-signal vote and persist the graph decision snapshot\"\n        bash: 'node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs --spec-folder \"{spec_folder}\" --loop-type \"research\" --session-id \"{config.lineage.sessionId}\"'\n        note: \"Run before the inline vote. STOP from the inline 3-signal vote is allowed only when the graph decision is STOP_ALLOWED or absent.\"\n        outputs:\n          - graph_decision: \"Tool decision value (CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED), else null when unavailable\"\n          - graph_decision_json: \"JSON-encoded graph decision string, else null\"\n          - graph_signals_json: \"Tool signals object, else {}\"\n          - graph_blockers_json: \"Tool blockers array, else []\"\n          - graph_trace_json: \"Tool trace payload, else []\"\n          - graph_convergence_score: \"signals.blendedScore when present, else the best available graph score, else 0\"\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"graph_convergence\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"decision\":{graph_decision_json},\"signals\":{graph_signals_json},\"blockers\":{graph_blockers_json},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n\n      step_check_convergence:\n        action: \"Evaluate stop conditions and combine the inline 3-signal vote with graph convergence\"\n        algorithm: |\n          1. if iteration_count >= max_iterations: STOP (maxIterationsReached). This terminal cap bypasses quality-guard overrides; record failed guards/blockers as synthesis evidence instead of continuing.\n          2. if remaining_questions == 0: STOP (all_questions_answered)\n          3. if stuck_count >= config.stuckThreshold: STUCK_RECOVERY\n          4. GRAPH-ASSISTED COMPOSITE CONVERGENCE:\n               step_graph_convergence already recorded graph_decision, graph_signals_json, graph_blockers_json, and graph_convergence_score for this run.\n               The existing inline 3-signal vote still computes the inline STOP candidate and is not replaced.\n               signals = []\n               Filter: exclude iterations where status == thought from signal inputs (use only evidence iterations)\n               a) Rolling average (w=0.30, needs 3+ iterations):\n                  avg = mean(last 3 newInfoRatios)\n                  stop if avg < convergence_threshold\n               b) MAD noise floor (w=0.35, needs 4+ iterations):\n                  noiseFloor = MAD(all ratios) * 1.4826\n                  stop if latest ratio <= noiseFloor\n               c) Question entropy (w=0.35):\n                  coverage = answered / total questions\n                  stop if coverage >= 0.85\n               Redistribute weights for unavailable signals.\n               if weighted_stop_score > 0.60: inline_stop_candidate = true\n               Combined stop rule: STOP only if the inline 3-signal vote says STOP AND graph_decision is STOP_ALLOWED or absent.\n               if inline_stop_candidate and graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\":\n                 decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n                 reason = \"blockedStop\"\n                 stop_blocked = true\n                 blocked_by_json = JSON array derived from graph_blockers_json\n                 blocked_by_csv = comma-separated blocker names derived from graph_blockers_json\n                 gate_convergence_pass = false\n                 gate_convergence_score = graph_convergence_score\n                 gate_key_question_coverage_pass = no blocker named questionCoverage","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":500,"totalLines":1079,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-research-loop_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1781420777201,"end":1781420777206}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_03b34aadf3fdd607016a2e52e9179081918d0b9ff08fccb521"}},"id":"prt_ec4f3decd0010o2Mhm3OIk8bwh","sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","messageID":"msg_ec4f3baae001KbqlDyNudWl7Zx"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781420777240,"sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_6DLdMKUPTJIVvQMu9L0E57LE","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-research-loop_presentation.txt","offset":1,"limit":300},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-research-loop_presentation.txt</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Start Research Loop Presentation Contract\n2: \n3: Presentation source of truth for `/deep:start-research-loop`. The command router owns only mode selection, setup binding, and asset loading. Workflow YAML owns execution. This file owns visible prompts, dashboard/checkpoint layout, final result displays, examples, and next-step wording.\n4: \n5: ## 1. Startup Presentation\n6: \n7: This workflow gathers all setup inputs in one prompt. Confirm mode still includes multiple approval gates after setup; only the setup round-trip is consolidated here.\n8: \n9: For `:confirm` or no suffix, the consolidated setup prompt MUST be the first visible response. No implementation or file-modifying tool calls before asking. Lightweight read-only discovery to suggest a spec folder or load prior context is allowed, then ask ALL questions immediately and wait.\n10: \n11: For `:auto`, do not emit the consolidated prompt by default. Resolve setup with the three-tier branch below, then load the auto YAML only after all required values are bound.\n12: \n13: ### `:auto` Setup Resolution\n14: \n15: Setup contract: see `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/auto_mode_contract.md`.\n16: \n17: Under `execution_mode = AUTONOMOUS` (from the `:auto` suffix), follow the three-tier flow:\n18: \n19: 1. **Tier 1 — Resolve confidently** (contract §1): parse `$ARGUMENTS` flags + `PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:` block (§2) + the Default Resolution Table below (§3). When every required field is resolved, persist to `{artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json` (shape: `researchTopic`, `specFolder`, `maxIterations`, `convergenceThreshold`, `executionMode: \"auto\"`, `resource_map.emit`, `config.executor.*`), bind runtime YAML placeholders, set `STATUS: PASSED`, load `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-research-loop_auto.yaml`. End §0.\n20: \n21: 2. **Tier 2 — Targeted ask** (contract §1): when 1-2 required fields are genuinely ambiguous AND no default exists, emit ONE narrow question per ambiguous field. Command-specific Tier-2-eligible fields (per the Default Resolution Table below): `spec_folder`. **Ordering rule**: none needed. Missing `research_topic` is absence, not ambiguity — go to Tier 3.\n22: \n23: 3. **Tier 3 — Fail fast** (contract §4): emit the named-missing-inputs error format with `/deep:start-research-loop:auto` as the command name. Exit non-zero. Do not load YAML.\n24: \n25: `:confirm` path stays unchanged — see the consolidated setup prompt section below.\n26: \n27: ### PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS Schema (for `:auto` non-interactive dispatch)\n28: \n29: The dispatched prompt body may contain one structured marker block. Parse it before applying defaults. Grammar: see `auto_mode_contract.md` §2.\n30: \n31: ```yaml\n32: PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:\n33:   research_topic: WebSocket reconnection strategies  # string\n34:   spec_folder: <spec-folder>  # existing | new | update-related | phase-folder | explicit path\n35:   execution_mode: AUTONOMOUS  # from :auto suffix\n36:   maxIterations: 10  # positive integer\n37:   convergenceThreshold: 0.05  # decimal 0..1\n38:   executor: native  # native | cli-codex | cli-claude-code | cli-opencode\n39:   executor_model: \"\"  # optional executor-specific model id (cli-opencode e.g. xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro, minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M2.7-highspeed)\n40:   executor_config_dir: \"\"  # optional, cli-claude-code only; maps to CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR\n41:   executor_reasoning: \"\"  # optional reasoning effort\n42:   executor_service_tier: \"\"  # optional service tier\n43:   executor_timeout: 900  # optional positive integer seconds\n44:   resource_map_emit: true  # boolean\n45: ```\n46: \n47: Rules: see `auto_mode_contract.md` §2 (unspecified fields fall back to default; marker fields take precedence over `$ARGUMENTS` flags; unknown fields warn; malformed lines parse-error).\n48: \n49: ### Default Resolution Table\n50: \n51: | Field                   | Required | Resolves Via                                                                                                                                                                                           | Default                            | Tier-2 Candidate                                        |\n52: | -------------------------| ----------| --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------| ------------------------------------| ---------------------------------------------------------|\n53: | `research_topic`        | Y        | `$ARGUMENTS` positional topic, or marker `research_topic`                                                                                                                                              | none                               | N                                                       |\n54: | `spec_folder`           | Y        | flag `--spec-folder`, marker `spec_folder`, `scope-extract` → a spec-folder path named in the topic/`$ARGUMENTS` that resolves to an existing folder (auto-bound + stripped, per `auto_mode_contract` §1 source 3), or targeted choice among suggested existing/new/update-related/phase folder | none | Y, ONLY when topic is present, names no resolvable spec folder, and the folder choice is ambiguous |\n55: | `execution_mode`        | Y        | attached suffix `:auto` or marker `execution_mode`                                                                                                                                                     | `AUTONOMOUS` under `:auto`         | N                                                       |\n56: | `maxIterations`         | Y        | flag `--max-iterations`, marker `maxIterations`, or default                                                                                                                                            | `10`                               | N                                                       |\n57: | `convergenceThreshold`  | Y        | flag `--convergence`, marker `convergenceThreshold`, or default                                                                                                                                        | `0.05`                             | N                                                       |\n58: | `executor`              | N        | flag `--executor`, marker `executor`, config file, or default                                                                                                                                          | `native`                           | N                                                       |\n59: | `executor_model`        | N        | flag `--model`, marker `executor_model`, or executor-specific validation                                                                                                                               | none                               | N                                                       |\n60: | `executor_config_dir`   | N        | flag `--config-dir`, marker `executor_config_dir`, or executor-specific default                                                                                                                        | none                               | N                                                       |\n61: | `executor_reasoning`    | N        | flag `--reasoning-effort`, marker `executor_reasoning`, or executor default                                                                                                                            | none                               | N                                                       |\n62: | `executor_service_tier` | N        | flag `--service-tier`, marker `executor_service_tier`, or executor default                                                                                                                             | none                               | N                                                       |\n63: | `executor_timeout`      | N        | flag `--executor-timeout`, marker `executor_timeout`, or default                                                                                                                                       | `900`                              | N                                                       |\n64: | `resource_map_emit`     | N        | flag `--no-resource-map`, marker `resource_map_emit`, or default                                                                                                                                       | `true`                             | N                                                       |\n65: | `fanout_executors`      | N        | repeatable `--executor=<type>` flags or `--executors=<json>`; each `--executor` group accepts `--model`, `--config-dir`, `--reasoning-effort`, `--service-tier`, `--executor-timeout`, `--iters`, `--label`, `--count` | none (single-executor when absent) | N                                                       |\n66: | `fanout_concurrency`    | N        | flag `--concurrency=N`                                                                                                                                                                                 | `2`                                | N                                                       |\n67: \n68: **Fan-out default policy:** 0–1 `--executor` flags and no `--executors` → `config.executor` (single-executor, default, unchanged). 2+ `--executor` flags, `--executors`, or any `--count > 1` → `config.fanout`. Native fan-out (count N for `native` executor) runs N sequential `@deep-research` agent dispatches with isolated dirs. CLI fan-out runs N headless subprocesses concurrently in the capped pool.\n69: \n70: ### Consolidated Prompt Template\n71: \n72: **STATUS: ☐ BLOCKED**\n73: \n74: ```\n75: EXECUTE THIS SINGLE CONSOLIDATED PROMPT:\n76: \n77: 1. CHECK for mode suffix:\n78:    |-- \":auto\"         -> execution_mode = \"AUTONOMOUS\"\n79:    |-- \":confirm\"      -> execution_mode = \"INTERACTIVE\"\n80:    +-- No suffix       -> execution_mode = \"ASK\"\n81: \n82: 2. CHECK $ARGUMENTS for topic:\n83:    |-- Has content (ignoring suffixes and flags):\n84:    |     -> research_topic = $ARGUMENTS, omit Q0\n85:    +-- Empty -> include Q0\n86: \n87: 3. PARSE optional flags from $ARGUMENTS:\n88:    |-- --max-iterations=N -> maxIterations = N\n89:    |-- --convergence=N -> convergenceThreshold = N\n90:    |-- --spec-folder=PATH -> spec_path = PATH, omit Q1\n91:    |-- --executor=<type> -> config.executor.type (`native` | `cli-codex` | `cli-claude-code` | `cli-opencode`)\n92:    |-- --model=<id> -> config.executor.model (for example `gpt-5.4`)\n93:    |-- --config-dir=<path> -> config.executor.configDir (cli-claude-code only; fan-out sets CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR)\n94:    |-- --reasoning-effort=<level> -> config.executor.reasoningEffort (`none` | `minimal` | `low` | `medium` | `high` | `xhigh`)\n95:    |-- --service-tier=<tier> -> config.executor.serviceTier (`priority` | `standard` | `fast`)\n96:    |-- --executor-timeout=<seconds> -> config.executor.timeoutSeconds (positive integer, default `900`)\n97:    |-- --no-resource-map -> config.resource_map.emit = false\n98:    |-- --executor=<type> [--model=X] [--config-dir=PATH] [--reasoning-effort=Y] [--service-tier=Z] [--executor-timeout=N] [--iters=N] [--label=X] [--count=N]\n99:    |     (repeatable; each occurrence adds one entry to config.fanout.executors)\n100:    |-- --executors=<json> -> config.fanout.executors = parse(json) escape hatch for complex configs\n101:    |-- --concurrency=N -> config.fanout.concurrency (default 2)\n102:    |\n103:    |   Fan-out default policy:\n104:    |   - 0 or 1 --executor (no --executors, no count>1): write config.executor (single, unchanged)\n105:    |   - 2+ --executor flags, --executors, or any count>1: write config.fanout\n106:    |\n107:    +-- Defaults: maxIterations=10, convergenceThreshold=0.05, config.executor.type=`native`, config.executor.timeoutSeconds=900, config.resource_map.emit=`true`\n108: \n109:    Executor precedence for setup resolution:\n110:    - CLI flag > config file > schema defaults\n111:    - The generated `deep-research-config.json` stores executor settings under `config.executor.*`\n112: \n113:    Parsing to config mapping:\n114:    - `--executor` -> `config.executor.type`\n115:    - `--model` -> `config.executor.model`\n116:    - `--config-dir` -> `config.executor.configDir`\n117:    - `--reasoning-effort` -> `config.executor.reasoningEffort`\n118:    - `--service-tier` -> `config.executor.serviceTier`\n119:    - `--executor-timeout` -> `config.executor.timeoutSeconds`\n120: \n121:    Validation hook:\n122:    - `parseExecutorConfig` from `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts` runs at config-write time\n123:    - Invalid combinations fail fast with clear errors, including `cli-codex` without `--model` and reserved-but-unwired executor kinds\n124: \n125: 4. Search for related spec folders across alias roots:\n126:    $ find specs .opencode/specs -mindepth 2 -maxdepth 2 -type d 2>/dev/null | sort | tail -10\n127: \n128: 5. Search for prior work (background):\n129:    - memory_context({ input: research_topic OR \"deep-research\", mode: \"focused\", includeContent: true })\n130:    - Store: prior_work_found = [yes/no]\n131: \n132: 6. ASK with SINGLE prompt (include only applicable questions):\n133:    - Include Q-Exec only when `--executor` is NOT present and the topic text does NOT already mention executor hints such as `cli-codex`, `codex`, or `gpt-5.4`\n134:    - If Q-Exec is omitted and no executor is otherwise resolved, default to `native`\n135: \n136:    Q0. Research Topic (if not in command): What topic to research deeply?\n137: \n138:    Q1. Spec Folder (required):\n139:      A) Use existing [suggest if found]\n140:      B) Create new under `specs/[track]/[###]-[slug]/` (accept `.opencode/specs/` alias roots when already in use)\n141:      C) Update related [if match found]\n142:      D) Phase folder (e.g., `specs/NN-track/NNN-name/001-phase/` or matching `.opencode/specs/` alias)\n143: \n144:    Q2. Execution Mode (if no suffix):\n145:      A) Autonomous -- all iterations without approval\n146:      B) Interactive -- pause at each iteration for review\n147: \n148:    Q3. Max Iterations (if not set via flag):\n149:      Default is 10. Change? [Enter number or press enter for default]\n150: \n151:    Q-Exec. Executor (optional, press enter for default):\n152:      A) Native (default) — dispatch via @deep-research agent with Opus.\n153:      B) cli-codex — `codex exec` with --model X -c model_reasoning_effort -c service_tier.\n154:       C) cli-claude-code — `claude -p \"PROMPT\" --model X --permission-mode acceptEdits` with optional --effort and optional `--config-dir=PATH` for CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR. No service-tier.\n155:      D) cli-opencode — `opencode run --model X --format json --dangerously-skip-permissions --pure --dir {repo_root} [--variant Y] \"PROMPT\" </dev/null` (no `--agent`: current opencode rejects top-level `--agent general` — default agent runs; required for MiniMax/Xiaomi token-plan models). `reasoningEffort` maps to `--variant`. No service-tier.\n156: \n157:    Reply format examples:\n158:    - `\"A, A\"`\n159:    - `\"WebSocket research, A, B, 15\"`\n160:    - `\"WebSocket reconnection strategies, B, A, 10, 0.05, B, gpt-5.4, high, fast\"`\n161:    - `\"agent execution guardrails research, B, A, 15, 0.05, C, gpt-5.4, _, _\"`\n162: \n163: 7. WAIT for user response (DO NOT PROCEED)\n164: \n165: 8. Parse response and store ALL results:\n166:    - research_topic = [from Q0 or $ARGUMENTS]\n167:    - spec_choice = [A/B/C/D from Q1]\n168:    - spec_path = [derived path]\n169:    - execution_mode = [AUTONOMOUS/INTERACTIVE]\n170:    - maxIterations = [from Q3 or flag or default 10]\n171:    - convergenceThreshold = [from flag or default 0.05]\n172:     - executor config = [CLI flags, compact reply, config file, or default `native`; map compact reply fields to `config.executor.type/model/configDir/reasoningEffort/serviceTier`, and accept an optional volunteered convergence value before executor fields]\n173: \n174: 9. SET STATUS: PASSED\n175: \n176: STOP HERE - Wait for user answers before continuing.\n177: \n178: DO NOT proceed until user explicitly answers\n179: NEVER auto-create spec folders without confirmation\n180: NEVER split questions into multiple prompts\n181: ```\n182: \n183: **Phase Output:**\n184: - `research_topic` | `spec_choice` | `spec_path`\n185: - `execution_mode` | `maxIterations` | `convergenceThreshold`\n186: \n187: ## 2. Dashboard / Checkpoint Layout\n188: \n189: ### Deep Research\n190: \n191: Conduct autonomous iterative deep research with convergence detection. Each iteration dispatches a fresh LEAF agent (`@deep-research`) that reads externalized state, performs focused investigation, and writes findings to files.\n192: \n193: For code review and quality auditing, see `/deep:start-review-loop`.\n194: \n195: ### Convergence Threshold Semantics\n196: \n197: **Default:** 0.05 on newInfoRatio (fully-new=1.0, partially-new=0.5, +0.10 simplicity bonus, capped 1.0)\n198: \n199: **Semantic:** `convergenceThreshold` compares newly discovered information against accumulated research knowledge with negative-knowledge emphasis. Lower = more iterations / higher signal threshold.\n200: \n201: **NOT INTERCHANGEABLE with siblings:**\n202: - `deep-review` uses 0.10 default on weighted P0/P1/P2 severity ratio\n203: - `deep-ai-council` (proposed) uses 0.20 default on adjudicator-verdict stability\n204: \n205: Carrying threshold expectations across siblings will cause unexpected iteration counts. See 116 research at `.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/z_archive/116-deep-skill-evolution/006-deep-stack-cross-cutting/001-unique-value-differentiation/research/research.md` §2 F56/F78, §5 Recommendation, and §6 Parity Invariants.\n206: \n207: ```yaml\n208: role: Deep Research Loop Manager\n209: purpose: Run iterative research cycles until convergence or max iterations\n210: action: Execute YAML workflow managing init, loop, synthesis, and save phases\n211: operating_mode:\n212:   workflow: iterative_loop\n213:   compliance: MANDATORY\n214:   execution: autonomous_or_interactive\n215:   validation: convergence_detection\n216: ```\n217: \n218: ### Purpose\n219: \n220: Run an iterative loop for deep research: Initialize state under `{artifact_dir}` (resolved via `resolveArtifactRoot()` — root specs use `{spec_folder}/research/`; child phases and sub-phases use `{spec_folder}/research/{packet}-pt-{NN}/`), dispatch `@deep-research` agent per iteration, evaluate convergence, synthesize findings into `{artifact_dir}/research.md`, and emit `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` at convergence unless `--no-resource-map` disables it. Use when deep investigation requiring multiple rounds of discovery.\n221: \n222: ### Contract\n223: \n224: **Inputs:** `$ARGUMENTS` -- Research topic with optional flags and mode suffix\n225: **Outputs:** Spec folder with `{artifact_dir}/` packet (`{spec_folder}/research/` for root specs or `{spec_folder}/research/{packet}-pt-{NN}/` for nested phases), `research.md`, optional `resource-map.md`, state files, and `STATUS=<OK|FAIL|CANCELLED>`\n226: \n227: ### Workflow Overview\n228: \n229: | Phase | Name | Purpose | Outputs |\n230: |-------|------|---------|---------|\n231: | Init | Initialize | Create config, strategy (with research charter), state files | State files in `research/` |\n232: | Loop | Iterate | Dispatch @deep-research agent, evaluate convergence + quality guards, generate dashboard | iteration-NNN.md files, deep-research-dashboard.md |\n233: | Synth | Synthesize | Emit `research/resource-map.md` and compile final research/research.md | research/resource-map.md, research/research.md (17 sections) |\n234: | Save | Preserve | Refresh continuity update in canonical spec docs | canonical spec doc updated via `generate-context.js` |\n235: \n236: ### Execution Modes\n237: \n238: | Mode | Invocation | Behavior |\n239: |------|-----------|----------|\n240: | `:auto` | `/deep:start-research-loop:auto \"topic\"` | All iterations without approval |\n241: | `:confirm` | `/deep:start-research-loop:confirm \"topic\"` | Multi-gate review at setup, iteration, and synthesis |\n242: | (default) | `/deep:start-research-loop \"topic\"` | Ask user to choose mode during setup |\n243: \n244: ### Memory Integration Before Starting\n245: \n246: - `memory_context({ input: topic, intent: \"understand\" })` -- Load prior research\n247: - Inject results into strategy.md \"Known Context\" section\n248: \n249: ### Code Context Bootstrap\n250: \n251: - Use Code Graph (`code_graph_query`) to find relevant code examples before starting research\n252: - Query: 2-5 word concept descriptions related to the research topic\n253: - Inject discovered code patterns into strategy.md \"Known Context\" section alongside memory findings\n254: \n255: ## 3. Results Display\n256: \n257: ### Output Formats\n258: \n259: **Success:**\n260: ```\n261: Deep research complete.\n262: Iterations: [N] | Stop reason: [converged|max_iterations|all_answered]\n263: Artifacts: research/research.md, research/resource-map.md (unless `--no-resource-map`), [N] iteration files, continuity update in canonical spec docs refreshed\n264: Ready for: /speckit:plan [feature-description]\n265: STATUS=OK PATH=[spec-folder-path]\n266: ```\n267: \n268: **Failure:**\n269: ```\n270: Error: [error description]  Phase: [phase name]\n271: STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"[message]\"\n272: ```\n273: \n274: ### Memory Integration After Completing\n275: \n276: - `node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js /tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json [spec-folder]`\n277: - Verify that the canonical save routed continuity into the expected packet doc (decision-record.md / implementation-summary.md / handover.md)\n278: \n279: ### Anchor Tags (Automatic)\n280: \n281: `ANCHOR:deep-research-[topic]`, `ANCHOR:findings`, `ANCHOR:convergence-report`\n282: \n283: ### Error Handling\n284: \n285: | Error | Action |\n286: |-------|--------|\n287: | Agent dispatch timeout | Retry once with reduced scope, then mark timeout |\n288: | State file missing | Reconstruct from iteration files |\n289: | 3+ consecutive failures | Halt loop, enter synthesis with partial findings |\n290: | Memory save failure | Save to `scratch/` as backup |\n291: \n292: ## 4. Next-Step Suggestions\n293: \n294: ### Skill Reference\n295: \n296: Full protocol documentation: `.opencode/skills/deep-research/SKILL.md`\n297: \n298: Key references:\n299: - Loop protocol: `deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md`\n300: - Spec check protocol: `deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md`\n\n(Showing lines 1-300 of 374. Use offset=301 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deep Start Research Loop Presentation Contract\n\nPresentation source of truth for `/deep:start-research-loop`. The command router owns only mode selection, setup binding, and asset loading. Workflow YAML owns execution. This file owns visible prompts, dashboard/checkpoint layout, final result displays, examples, and next-step wording.\n\n## 1. Startup Presentation\n\nThis workflow gathers all setup inputs in one prompt. Confirm mode still includes multiple approval gates after setup; only the setup round-trip is consolidated here.\n\nFor `:confirm` or no suffix, the consolidated setup prompt MUST be the first visible response. No implementation or file-modifying tool calls before asking. Lightweight read-only discovery to suggest a spec folder or load prior context is allowed, then ask ALL questions immediately and wait.\n\nFor `:auto`, do not emit the consolidated prompt by default. Resolve setup with the three-tier branch below, then load the auto YAML only after all required values are bound.\n\n### `:auto` Setup Resolution\n\nSetup contract: see `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/auto_mode_contract.md`.\n\nUnder `execution_mode = AUTONOMOUS` (from the `:auto` suffix), follow the three-tier flow:\n\n1. **Tier 1 — Resolve confidently** (contract §1): parse `$ARGUMENTS` flags + `PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:` block (§2) + the Default Resolution Table below (§3). When every required field is resolved, persist to `{artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json` (shape: `researchTopic`, `specFolder`, `maxIterations`, `convergenceThreshold`, `executionMode: \"auto\"`, `resource_map.emit`, `config.executor.*`), bind runtime YAML placeholders, set `STATUS: PASSED`, load `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-research-loop_auto.yaml`. End §0.\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-research-loop_presentation.txt","text":"# Deep Start Research Loop Presentation Contract\n\nPresentation source of truth for `/deep:start-research-loop`. The command router owns only mode selection, setup binding, and asset loading. Workflow YAML owns execution. This file owns visible prompts, dashboard/checkpoint layout, final result displays, examples, and next-step wording.\n\n## 1. Startup Presentation\n\nThis workflow gathers all setup inputs in one prompt. Confirm mode still includes multiple approval gates after setup; only the setup round-trip is consolidated here.\n\nFor `:confirm` or no suffix, the consolidated setup prompt MUST be the first visible response. No implementation or file-modifying tool calls before asking. Lightweight read-only discovery to suggest a spec folder or load prior context is allowed, then ask ALL questions immediately and wait.\n\nFor `:auto`, do not emit the consolidated prompt by default. Resolve setup with the three-tier branch below, then load the auto YAML only after all required values are bound.\n\n### `:auto` Setup Resolution\n\nSetup contract: see `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/auto_mode_contract.md`.\n\nUnder `execution_mode = AUTONOMOUS` (from the `:auto` suffix), follow the three-tier flow:\n\n1. **Tier 1 — Resolve confidently** (contract §1): parse `$ARGUMENTS` flags + `PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:` block (§2) + the Default Resolution Table below (§3). When every required field is resolved, persist to `{artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json` (shape: `researchTopic`, `specFolder`, `maxIterations`, `convergenceThreshold`, `executionMode: \"auto\"`, `resource_map.emit`, `config.executor.*`), bind runtime YAML placeholders, set `STATUS: PASSED`, load `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-research-loop_auto.yaml`. End §0.\n\n2. **Tier 2 — Targeted ask** (contract §1): when 1-2 required fields are genuinely ambiguous AND no default exists, emit ONE narrow question per ambiguous field. Command-specific Tier-2-eligible fields (per the Default Resolution Table below): `spec_folder`. **Ordering rule**: none needed. Missing `research_topic` is absence, not ambiguity — go to Tier 3.\n\n3. **Tier 3 — Fail fast** (contract §4): emit the named-missing-inputs error format with `/deep:start-research-loop:auto` as the command name. Exit non-zero. Do not load YAML.\n\n`:confirm` path stays unchanged — see the consolidated setup prompt section below.\n\n### PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS Schema (for `:auto` non-interactive dispatch)\n\nThe dispatched prompt body may contain one structured marker block. Parse it before applying defaults. Grammar: see `auto_mode_contract.md` §2.\n\n```yaml\nPRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:\n  research_topic: WebSocket reconnection strategies  # string\n  spec_folder: <spec-folder>  # existing | new | update-related | phase-folder | explicit path\n  execution_mode: AUTONOMOUS  # from :auto suffix\n  maxIterations: 10  # positive integer\n  convergenceThreshold: 0.05  # decimal 0..1\n  executor: native  # native | cli-codex | cli-claude-code | cli-opencode\n  executor_model: \"\"  # optional executor-specific model id (cli-opencode e.g. xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro, minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M2.7-highspeed)\n  executor_config_dir: \"\"  # optional, cli-claude-code only; maps to CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR\n  executor_reasoning: \"\"  # optional reasoning effort\n  executor_service_tier: \"\"  # optional service tier\n  executor_timeout: 900  # optional positive integer seconds\n  resource_map_emit: true  # boolean\n```\n\nRules: see `auto_mode_contract.md` §2 (unspecified fields fall back to default; marker fields take precedence over `$ARGUMENTS` flags; unknown fields warn; malformed lines parse-error).\n\n### Default Resolution Table\n\n| Field                   | Required | Resolves Via                                                                                                                                                                                           | Default                            | Tier-2 Candidate                                        |\n| -------------------------| ----------| --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------| ------------------------------------| ---------------------------------------------------------|\n| `research_topic`        | Y        | `$ARGUMENTS` positional topic, or marker `research_topic`                                                                                                                                              | none                               | N                                                       |\n| `spec_folder`           | Y        | flag `--spec-folder`, marker `spec_folder`, `scope-extract` → a spec-folder path named in the topic/`$ARGUMENTS` that resolves to an existing folder (auto-bound + stripped, per `auto_mode_contract` §1 source 3), or targeted choice among suggested existing/new/update-related/phase folder | none | Y, ONLY when topic is present, names no resolvable spec folder, and the folder choice is ambiguous |\n| `execution_mode`        | Y        | attached suffix `:auto` or marker `execution_mode`                                                                                                                                                     | `AUTONOMOUS` under `:auto`         | N                                                       |\n| `maxIterations`         | Y        | flag `--max-iterations`, marker `maxIterations`, or default                                                                                                                                            | `10`                               | N                                                       |\n| `convergenceThreshold`  | Y        | flag `--convergence`, marker `convergenceThreshold`, or default                                                                                                                                        | `0.05`                             | N                                                       |\n| `executor`              | N        | flag `--executor`, marker `executor`, config file, or default                                                                                                                                          | `native`                           | N                                                       |\n| `executor_model`        | N        | flag `--model`, marker `executor_model`, or executor-specific validation                                                                                                                               | none                               | N                                                       |\n| `executor_config_dir`   | N        | flag `--config-dir`, marker `executor_config_dir`, or executor-specific default                                                                                                                        | none                               | N                                                       |\n| `executor_reasoning`    | N        | flag `--reasoning-effort`, marker `executor_reasoning`, or executor default                                                                                                                            | none                               | N                                                       |\n| `executor_service_tier` | N        | flag `--service-tier`, marker `executor_service_tier`, or executor default                                                                                                                             | none                               | N                                                       |\n| `executor_timeout`      | N        | flag `--executor-timeout`, marker `executor_timeout`, or default                                                                                                                                       | `900`                              | N                                                       |\n| `resource_map_emit`     | N        | flag `--no-resource-map`, marker `resource_map_emit`, or default                                                                                                                                       | `true`                             | N                                                       |\n| `fanout_executors`      | N        | repeatable `--executor=<type>` flags or `--executors=<json>`; each `--executor` group accepts `--model`, `--config-dir`, `--reasoning-effort`, `--service-tier`, `--executor-timeout`, `--iters`, `--label`, `--count` | none (single-executor when absent) | N                                                       |\n| `fanout_concurrency`    | N        | flag `--concurrency=N`                                                                                                                                                                                 | `2`                                | N                                                       |\n\n**Fan-out default policy:** 0–1 `--executor` flags and no `--executors` → `config.executor` (single-executor, default, unchanged). 2+ `--executor` flags, `--executors`, or any `--count > 1` → `config.fanout`. Native fan-out (count N for `native` executor) runs N sequential `@deep-research` agent dispatches with isolated dirs. CLI fan-out runs N headless subprocesses concurrently in the capped pool.\n\n### Consolidated Prompt Template\n\n**STATUS: ☐ BLOCKED**\n\n```\nEXECUTE THIS SINGLE CONSOLIDATED PROMPT:\n\n1. CHECK for mode suffix:\n   |-- \":auto\"         -> execution_mode = \"AUTONOMOUS\"\n   |-- \":confirm\"      -> execution_mode = \"INTERACTIVE\"\n   +-- No suffix       -> execution_mode = \"ASK\"\n\n2. CHECK $ARGUMENTS for topic:\n   |-- Has content (ignoring suffixes and flags):\n   |     -> research_topic = $ARGUMENTS, omit Q0\n   +-- Empty -> include Q0\n\n3. PARSE optional flags from $ARGUMENTS:\n   |-- --max-iterations=N -> maxIterations = N\n   |-- --convergence=N -> convergenceThreshold = N\n   |-- --spec-folder=PATH -> spec_path = PATH, omit Q1\n   |-- --executor=<type> -> config.executor.type (`native` | `cli-codex` | `cli-claude-code` | `cli-opencode`)\n   |-- --model=<id> -> config.executor.model (for example `gpt-5.4`)\n   |-- --config-dir=<path> -> config.executor.configDir (cli-claude-code only; fan-out sets CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR)\n   |-- --reasoning-effort=<level> -> config.executor.reasoningEffort (`none` | `minimal` | `low` | `medium` | `high` | `xhigh`)\n   |-- --service-tier=<tier> -> config.executor.serviceTier (`priority` | `standard` | `fast`)\n   |-- --executor-timeout=<seconds> -> config.executor.timeoutSeconds (positive integer, default `900`)\n   |-- --no-resource-map -> config.resource_map.emit = false\n   |-- --executor=<type> [--model=X] [--config-dir=PATH] [--reasoning-effort=Y] [--service-tier=Z] [--executor-timeout=N] [--iters=N] [--label=X] [--count=N]\n   |     (repeatable; each occurrence adds one entry to config.fanout.executors)\n   |-- --executors=<json> -> config.fanout.executors = parse(json) escape hatch for complex configs\n   |-- --concurrency=N -> config.fanout.concurrency (default 2)\n   |\n   |   Fan-out default policy:\n   |   - 0 or 1 --executor (no --executors, no count>1): write config.executor (single, unchanged)\n   |   - 2+ --executor flags, --executors, or any count>1: write config.fanout\n   |\n   +-- Defaults: maxIterations=10, convergenceThreshold=0.05, config.executor.type=`native`, config.executor.timeoutSeconds=900, config.resource_map.emit=`true`\n\n   Executor precedence for setup resolution:\n   - CLI flag > config file > schema defaults\n   - The generated `deep-research-config.json` stores executor settings under `config.executor.*`\n\n   Parsing to config mapping:\n   - `--executor` -> `config.executor.type`\n   - `--model` -> `config.executor.model`\n   - `--config-dir` -> `config.executor.configDir`\n   - `--reasoning-effort` -> `config.executor.reasoningEffort`\n   - `--service-tier` -> `config.executor.serviceTier`\n   - `--executor-timeout` -> `config.executor.timeoutSeconds`\n\n   Validation hook:\n   - `parseExecutorConfig` from `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts` runs at config-write time\n   - Invalid combinations fail fast with clear errors, including `cli-codex` without `--model` and reserved-but-unwired executor kinds\n\n4. Search for related spec folders across alias roots:\n   $ find specs .opencode/specs -mindepth 2 -maxdepth 2 -type d 2>/dev/null | sort | tail -10\n\n5. Search for prior work (background):\n   - memory_context({ input: research_topic OR \"deep-research\", mode: \"focused\", includeContent: true })\n   - Store: prior_work_found = [yes/no]\n\n6. ASK with SINGLE prompt (include only applicable questions):\n   - Include Q-Exec only when `--executor` is NOT present and the topic text does NOT already mention executor hints such as `cli-codex`, `codex`, or `gpt-5.4`\n   - If Q-Exec is omitted and no executor is otherwise resolved, default to `native`\n\n   Q0. Research Topic (if not in command): What topic to research deeply?\n\n   Q1. Spec Folder (required):\n     A) Use existing [suggest if found]\n     B) Create new under `specs/[track]/[###]-[slug]/` (accept `.opencode/specs/` alias roots when already in use)\n     C) Update related [if match found]\n     D) Phase folder (e.g., `specs/NN-track/NNN-name/001-phase/` or matching `.opencode/specs/` alias)\n\n   Q2. Execution Mode (if no suffix):\n     A) Autonomous -- all iterations without approval\n     B) Interactive -- pause at each iteration for review\n\n   Q3. Max Iterations (if not set via flag):\n     Default is 10. Change? [Enter number or press enter for default]\n\n   Q-Exec. Executor (optional, press enter for default):\n     A) Native (default) — dispatch via @deep-research agent with Opus.\n     B) cli-codex — `codex exec` with --model X -c model_reasoning_effort -c service_tier.\n      C) cli-claude-code — `claude -p \"PROMPT\" --model X --permission-mode acceptEdits` with optional --effort and optional `--config-dir=PATH` for CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR. No service-tier.\n     D) cli-opencode — `opencode run --model X --format json --dangerously-skip-permissions --pure --dir {repo_root} [--variant Y] \"PROMPT\" </dev/null` (no `--agent`: current opencode rejects top-level `--agent general` — default agent runs; required for MiniMax/Xiaomi token-plan models). `reasoningEffort` maps to `--variant`. No service-tier.\n\n   Reply format examples:\n   - `\"A, A\"`\n   - `\"WebSocket research, A, B, 15\"`\n   - `\"WebSocket reconnection strategies, B, A, 10, 0.05, B, gpt-5.4, high, fast\"`\n   - `\"agent execution guardrails research, B, A, 15, 0.05, C, gpt-5.4, _, _\"`\n\n7. WAIT for user response (DO NOT PROCEED)\n\n8. Parse response and store ALL results:\n   - research_topic = [from Q0 or $ARGUMENTS]\n   - spec_choice = [A/B/C/D from Q1]\n   - spec_path = [derived path]\n   - execution_mode = [AUTONOMOUS/INTERACTIVE]\n   - maxIterations = [from Q3 or flag or default 10]\n   - convergenceThreshold = [from flag or default 0.05]\n    - executor config = [CLI flags, compact reply, config file, or default `native`; map compact reply fields to `config.executor.type/model/configDir/reasoningEffort/serviceTier`, and accept an optional volunteered convergence value before executor fields]\n\n9. SET STATUS: PASSED\n\nSTOP HERE - Wait for user answers before continuing.\n\nDO NOT proceed until user explicitly answers\nNEVER auto-create spec folders without confirmation\nNEVER split questions into multiple prompts\n```\n\n**Phase Output:**\n- `research_topic` | `spec_choice` | `spec_path`\n- `execution_mode` | `maxIterations` | `convergenceThreshold`\n\n## 2. Dashboard / Checkpoint Layout\n\n### Deep Research\n\nConduct autonomous iterative deep research with convergence detection. Each iteration dispatches a fresh LEAF agent (`@deep-research`) that reads externalized state, performs focused investigation, and writes findings to files.\n\nFor code review and quality auditing, see `/deep:start-review-loop`.\n\n### Convergence Threshold Semantics\n\n**Default:** 0.05 on newInfoRatio (fully-new=1.0, partially-new=0.5, +0.10 simplicity bonus, capped 1.0)\n\n**Semantic:** `convergenceThreshold` compares newly discovered information against accumulated research knowledge with negative-knowledge emphasis. Lower = more iterations / higher signal threshold.\n\n**NOT INTERCHANGEABLE with siblings:**\n- `deep-review` uses 0.10 default on weighted P0/P1/P2 severity ratio\n- `deep-ai-council` (proposed) uses 0.20 default on adjudicator-verdict stability\n\nCarrying threshold expectations across siblings will cause unexpected iteration counts. See 116 research at `.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/z_archive/116-deep-skill-evolution/006-deep-stack-cross-cutting/001-unique-value-differentiation/research/research.md` §2 F56/F78, §5 Recommendation, and §6 Parity Invariants.\n\n```yaml\nrole: Deep Research Loop Manager\npurpose: Run iterative research cycles until convergence or max iterations\naction: Execute YAML workflow managing init, loop, synthesis, and save phases\noperating_mode:\n  workflow: iterative_loop\n  compliance: MANDATORY\n  execution: autonomous_or_interactive\n  validation: convergence_detection\n```\n\n### Purpose\n\nRun an iterative loop for deep research: Initialize state under `{artifact_dir}` (resolved via `resolveArtifactRoot()` — root specs use `{spec_folder}/research/`; child phases and sub-phases use `{spec_folder}/research/{packet}-pt-{NN}/`), dispatch `@deep-research` agent per iteration, evaluate convergence, synthesize findings into `{artifact_dir}/research.md`, and emit `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` at convergence unless `--no-resource-map` disables it. Use when deep investigation requiring multiple rounds of discovery.\n\n### Contract\n\n**Inputs:** `$ARGUMENTS` -- Research topic with optional flags and mode suffix\n**Outputs:** Spec folder with `{artifact_dir}/` packet (`{spec_folder}/research/` for root specs or `{spec_folder}/research/{packet}-pt-{NN}/` for nested phases), `research.md`, optional `resource-map.md`, state files, and `STATUS=<OK|FAIL|CANCELLED>`\n\n### Workflow Overview\n\n| Phase | Name | Purpose | Outputs |\n|-------|------|---------|---------|\n| Init | Initialize | Create config, strategy (with research charter), state files | State files in `research/` |\n| Loop | Iterate | Dispatch @deep-research agent, evaluate convergence + quality guards, generate dashboard | iteration-NNN.md files, deep-research-dashboard.md |\n| Synth | Synthesize | Emit `research/resource-map.md` and compile final research/research.md | research/resource-map.md, research/research.md (17 sections) |\n| Save | Preserve | Refresh continuity update in canonical spec docs | canonical spec doc updated via `generate-context.js` |\n\n### Execution Modes\n\n| Mode | Invocation | Behavior |\n|------|-----------|----------|\n| `:auto` | `/deep:start-research-loop:auto \"topic\"` | All iterations without approval |\n| `:confirm` | `/deep:start-research-loop:confirm \"topic\"` | Multi-gate review at setup, iteration, and synthesis |\n| (default) | `/deep:start-research-loop \"topic\"` | Ask user to choose mode during setup |\n\n### Memory Integration Before Starting\n\n- `memory_context({ input: topic, intent: \"understand\" })` -- Load prior research\n- Inject results into strategy.md \"Known Context\" section\n\n### Code Context Bootstrap\n\n- Use Code Graph (`code_graph_query`) to find relevant code examples before starting research\n- Query: 2-5 word concept descriptions related to the research topic\n- Inject discovered code patterns into strategy.md \"Known Context\" section alongside memory findings\n\n## 3. Results Display\n\n### Output Formats\n\n**Success:**\n```\nDeep research complete.\nIterations: [N] | Stop reason: [converged|max_iterations|all_answered]\nArtifacts: research/research.md, research/resource-map.md (unless `--no-resource-map`), [N] iteration files, continuity update in canonical spec docs refreshed\nReady for: /speckit:plan [feature-description]\nSTATUS=OK PATH=[spec-folder-path]\n```\n\n**Failure:**\n```\nError: [error description]  Phase: [phase name]\nSTATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"[message]\"\n```\n\n### Memory Integration After Completing\n\n- `node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js /tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json [spec-folder]`\n- Verify that the canonical save routed continuity into the expected packet doc (decision-record.md / implementation-summary.md / handover.md)\n\n### Anchor Tags (Automatic)\n\n`ANCHOR:deep-research-[topic]`, `ANCHOR:findings`, `ANCHOR:convergence-report`\n\n### Error Handling\n\n| Error | Action |\n|-------|--------|\n| Agent dispatch timeout | Retry once with reduced scope, then mark timeout |\n| State file missing | Reconstruct from iteration files |\n| 3+ consecutive failures | Halt loop, enter synthesis with partial findings |\n| Memory save failure | Save to `scratch/` as backup |\n\n## 4. Next-Step Suggestions\n\n### Skill Reference\n\nFull protocol documentation: `.opencode/skills/deep-research/SKILL.md`\n\nKey references:\n- Loop protocol: `deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md`\n- Spec check protocol: `deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md`","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":300,"totalLines":374,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-research-loop_presentation.txt","time":{"start":1781420777235,"end":1781420777239}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_03b34aadf3fdd607016a2e52e917a081918bbe216aa472e2fe"}},"id":"prt_ec4f3def300132Or08vTcz1STN","sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","messageID":"msg_ec4f3baae001KbqlDyNudWl7Zx"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781420777248,"sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_LWPkYKNpEEDSIUlvbhc3Vm7H","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json","offset":1,"limit":240},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"topic\": \"\",\n3:   \"maxIterations\": 10,\n4:   \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.05,\n5:   \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n6:   \"maxDurationMinutes\": 120,\n7:   \"maxToolCallsPerIteration\": 12,\n8:   \"maxMinutesPerIteration\": 10,\n9:   \"progressiveSynthesis\": true,\n10:   \"specFolder\": \"\",\n11:   \"createdAt\": \"\",\n12:   \"status\": \"initialized\",\n13:   \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n14:   \"executor\": {\n15:     \"kind\": \"native\",\n16:     \"model\": null,\n17:     \"reasoningEffort\": null,\n18:     \"serviceTier\": null,\n19:     \"sandboxMode\": null,\n20:     \"timeoutSeconds\": 900\n21:   },\n22:   \"lineage\": {\n23:     \"sessionId\": \"\",\n24:     \"parentSessionId\": null,\n25:     \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n26:     \"allowedModes\": [\n27:       \"new\",\n28:       \"resume\",\n29:       \"restart\"\n30:     ],\n31:     \"deferredModes\": [\n32:       \"fork\",\n33:       \"completed-continue\"\n34:     ],\n35:     \"generation\": 1,\n36:     \"continuedFromRun\": null\n37:   },\n38:   \"reducer\": {\n39:     \"enabled\": true,\n40:     \"version\": \"1.0\",\n41:     \"registryFile\": \"research/findings-registry.json\",\n42:     \"dashboardFile\": \"research/deep-research-dashboard.md\",\n43:     \"strategyFile\": \"research/deep-research-strategy.md\",\n44:     \"machineOwnedSections\": [\n45:       \"key-questions\",\n46:       \"answered-questions\",\n47:       \"what-worked\",\n48:       \"what-failed\",\n49:       \"exhausted-approaches\",\n50:       \"ruled-out-directions\",\n51:       \"next-focus\"\n52:     ]\n53:   },\n54:   \"capabilityMatrixPath\": \".opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/runtime_capabilities.json\",\n55:   \"capabilityMatrixDocPath\": \".opencode/skills/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md\",\n56:   \"runtimeCapabilityResolver\": \".opencode/skills/deep-research/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs\",\n57:   \"reducerScriptPath\": \".opencode/skills/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs\",\n58:   \"pauseSentinelPath\": \"research/.deep-research-pause\",\n59:   \"archiveRoot\": \"research_archive\",\n60:   \"migrationWindowDays\": 28,\n61:   \"fileProtection\": {\n62:     \"deep-research-config.json\": \"immutable\",\n63:     \"deep-research-state.jsonl\": \"append-only\",\n64:     \"deep-research-strategy.md\": \"mutable\",\n65:     \"deep-research-dashboard.md\": \"auto-generated\",\n66:     \"findings-registry.json\": \"auto-generated\",\n67:     \"iteration-*.md\": \"write-once\",\n68:     \"research/research.md\": \"mutable\"\n69:   },\n70:   \"_optimizerManaged\": {\n71:     \"description\": \"Fields managed by the offline loop optimizer (042.004). See optimizer-manifest.json for the canonical tunable/locked field registry.\",\n72:     \"manifestPath\": \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/optimizer/optimizer-manifest.json\",\n73:     \"tunableFields\": [\"convergenceThreshold\", \"stuckThreshold\", \"maxIterations\"],\n74:     \"lockedFields\": [\"lineage\", \"reducer\", \"fileProtection\", \"sessionId\", \"status\"],\n75:     \"promotionMode\": \"advisory-only\"\n76:   }\n77: }\n\n(End of file - total 77 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"topic\": \"\",\n  \"maxIterations\": 10,\n  \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.05,\n  \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n  \"maxDurationMinutes\": 120,\n  \"maxToolCallsPerIteration\": 12,\n  \"maxMinutesPerIteration\": 10,\n  \"progressiveSynthesis\": true,\n  \"specFolder\": \"\",\n  \"createdAt\": \"\",\n  \"status\": \"initialized\",\n  \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n  \"executor\": {\n    \"kind\": \"native\",\n    \"model\": null,\n    \"reasoningEffort\": null,\n    \"serviceTier\": null,\n    \"sandboxMode\": null,\n    \"timeoutSeconds\": 900","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json","text":"{\n  \"topic\": \"\",\n  \"maxIterations\": 10,\n  \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.05,\n  \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n  \"maxDurationMinutes\": 120,\n  \"maxToolCallsPerIteration\": 12,\n  \"maxMinutesPerIteration\": 10,\n  \"progressiveSynthesis\": true,\n  \"specFolder\": \"\",\n  \"createdAt\": \"\",\n  \"status\": \"initialized\",\n  \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n  \"executor\": {\n    \"kind\": \"native\",\n    \"model\": null,\n    \"reasoningEffort\": null,\n    \"serviceTier\": null,\n    \"sandboxMode\": null,\n    \"timeoutSeconds\": 900\n  },\n  \"lineage\": {\n    \"sessionId\": \"\",\n    \"parentSessionId\": null,\n    \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n    \"allowedModes\": [\n      \"new\",\n      \"resume\",\n      \"restart\"\n    ],\n    \"deferredModes\": [\n      \"fork\",\n      \"completed-continue\"\n    ],\n    \"generation\": 1,\n    \"continuedFromRun\": null\n  },\n  \"reducer\": {\n    \"enabled\": true,\n    \"version\": \"1.0\",\n    \"registryFile\": \"research/findings-registry.json\",\n    \"dashboardFile\": \"research/deep-research-dashboard.md\",\n    \"strategyFile\": \"research/deep-research-strategy.md\",\n    \"machineOwnedSections\": [\n      \"key-questions\",\n      \"answered-questions\",\n      \"what-worked\",\n      \"what-failed\",\n      \"exhausted-approaches\",\n      \"ruled-out-directions\",\n      \"next-focus\"\n    ]\n  },\n  \"capabilityMatrixPath\": \".opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/runtime_capabilities.json\",\n  \"capabilityMatrixDocPath\": \".opencode/skills/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md\",\n  \"runtimeCapabilityResolver\": \".opencode/skills/deep-research/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs\",\n  \"reducerScriptPath\": \".opencode/skills/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs\",\n  \"pauseSentinelPath\": \"research/.deep-research-pause\",\n  \"archiveRoot\": \"research_archive\",\n  \"migrationWindowDays\": 28,\n  \"fileProtection\": {\n    \"deep-research-config.json\": \"immutable\",\n    \"deep-research-state.jsonl\": \"append-only\",\n    \"deep-research-strategy.md\": \"mutable\",\n    \"deep-research-dashboard.md\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \"findings-registry.json\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \"iteration-*.md\": \"write-once\",\n    \"research/research.md\": \"mutable\"\n  },\n  \"_optimizerManaged\": {\n    \"description\": \"Fields managed by the offline loop optimizer (042.004). See optimizer-manifest.json for the canonical tunable/locked field registry.\",\n    \"manifestPath\": \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/optimizer/optimizer-manifest.json\",\n    \"tunableFields\": [\"convergenceThreshold\", \"stuckThreshold\", \"maxIterations\"],\n    \"lockedFields\": [\"lineage\", \"reducer\", \"fileProtection\", \"sessionId\", \"status\"],\n    \"promotionMode\": \"advisory-only\"\n  }\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":77,"totalLines":77,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json","time":{"start":1781420777245,"end":1781420777247}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_03b34aadf3fdd607016a2e52e917a8819185dac961859aa568"}},"id":"prt_ec4f3df140014jc0nlONAaNTa7","sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","messageID":"msg_ec4f3baae001KbqlDyNudWl7Zx"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781420777311,"sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_t9GkSierXnuUn5KWYoLnCuzd","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md","offset":1,"limit":240},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research Strategy Template\n3: description: Runtime template copied to research/ during initialization to track research progress, focus decisions, and outcomes across iterations.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep research strategy\"\n6:   - \"research strategy template\"\n7:   - \"research session tracking\"\n8:   - \"exhausted research approaches\"\n9:   - \"research stop conditions\"\n10:   - \"ruled out research directions\"\n11: importance_tier: normal\n12: contextType: planning\n13: ---\n14: \n15: # Deep Research Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n16: \n17: Runtime template copied to `{spec_folder}/research/` during initialization. Tracks research progress across iterations.\n18: \n19: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n20: \n21: ### Purpose\n22: \n23: Serves as the \"persistent brain\" for a deep research session. Records what to investigate, what worked, what failed, and where to focus next. Read by the orchestrator and agents at every iteration.\n24: \n25: ### Usage\n26: \n27: - **Init:** Orchestrator copies this template to `{spec_folder}/research/deep-research-strategy.md` and populates Topic, Key Questions, Known Context, and Research Boundaries from config and memory context.\n28: - **Per iteration:** Agent reads Next Focus, writes iteration evidence, and the reducer refreshes What Worked/Failed, answered questions, ruled-out directions, and Next Focus.\n29: - **Mutability:** Mutable — analyst-owned sections remain stable, while machine-owned sections are rewritten by the reducer after each iteration.\n30: - **Protection:** Shared state with explicit ownership boundaries. Orchestrator validates consistency on resume.\n31: \n32: ---\n33: \n34: ## 2. TOPIC\n35: [Research topic from config -- set during initialization]\n36: \n37: ---\n38: \n39: ## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n40: - [ ] [Question 1 -- identified during initialization or iteration 1]\n41: - [ ] [Question 2]\n42: - [ ] [Question 3]\n43: \n44: ---\n45: \n46: ## 4. NON-GOALS\n47: [What this research session is NOT trying to answer -- populated during initialization]\n48: \n49: ---\n50: \n51: ## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n52: [Explicit conditions beyond convergence that should end the session -- populated during initialization]\n53: \n54: ---\n55: \n56: ## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n57: [None yet -- populated as iterations answer questions]\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n62: ## 7. WHAT WORKED\n63: [First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n64: - [Approach]: [Why it worked] (iteration N)\n65: \n66: ---\n67: \n68: ## 8. WHAT FAILED\n69: [First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n70: - [Approach]: [Why it failed] (iteration N)\n71: \n72: ---\n73: \n74: ## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n75: [Populated when an approach has been tried from multiple angles without success]\n76: \n77: ### [Category Name] -- BLOCKED (iteration N, N attempts)\n78: - What was tried: [specific approaches attempted]\n79: - Why blocked: [root cause of exhaustion]\n80: - Do NOT retry: [explicit prohibition]\n81: \n82: ### [Category Name] -- PRODUCTIVE (iteration N)\n83: - What worked: [successful approaches in this category]\n84: - Prefer for: [related questions where this category may help]\n85: \n86: ---\n87: \n88: ## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n89: [Approaches that were investigated and definitively eliminated -- consolidated from iteration dead-end data]\n90: - [Approach]: [Why ruled out] (iteration N, evidence: [source])\n91: \n92: ---\n93: \n94: ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n95: [Recommended focus area for the next iteration -- updated at end of each iteration]\n96: \n97: ---\n98: \n99: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n100: ## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n101: [Populated during initialization from memory_context() results, if any prior work exists]\n102: \n103: ---\n104: \n105: ## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n106: - Max iterations: [from config]\n107: - Convergence threshold: [from config]\n108: - Per-iteration budget: [from config.maxToolCallsPerIteration] tool calls, [from config.maxMinutesPerIteration] minutes\n109: - Progressive synthesis: true (default)\n110: - research/research.md ownership: workflow-owned canonical synthesis output\n111: - Lifecycle branches: `resume`, `restart` (live); `fork`, `completed-continue` (deferred, not runtime-wired)\n112: - Machine-owned sections: reducer controls Sections 3, 6, 7-11\n113: - Canonical pause sentinel: `research/.deep-research-pause`\n114: - Capability matrix: `.opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/runtime_capabilities.json`\n115: - Capability matrix doc: `.opencode/skills/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md`\n116: - Capability resolver: `.opencode/skills/deep-research/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs`\n117: - Current generation: [from config.lineage.generation]\n118: - Started: [timestamp]\n\n(End of file - total 118 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Strategy Template\ndescription: Runtime template copied to research/ during initialization to track research progress, focus decisions, and outcomes across iterations.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep research strategy\"\n  - \"research strategy template\"\n  - \"research session tracking\"\n  - \"exhausted research approaches\"\n  - \"research stop conditions\"\n  - \"ruled out research directions\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: planning\n---\n\n# Deep Research Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n\nRuntime template copied to `{spec_folder}/research/` during initialization. Tracks research progress across iterations.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Strategy Template\ndescription: Runtime template copied to research/ during initialization to track research progress, focus decisions, and outcomes across iterations.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep research strategy\"\n  - \"research strategy template\"\n  - \"research session tracking\"\n  - \"exhausted research approaches\"\n  - \"research stop conditions\"\n  - \"ruled out research directions\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: planning\n---\n\n# Deep Research Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n\nRuntime template copied to `{spec_folder}/research/` during initialization. Tracks research progress across iterations.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nServes as the \"persistent brain\" for a deep research session. Records what to investigate, what worked, what failed, and where to focus next. Read by the orchestrator and agents at every iteration.\n\n### Usage\n\n- **Init:** Orchestrator copies this template to `{spec_folder}/research/deep-research-strategy.md` and populates Topic, Key Questions, Known Context, and Research Boundaries from config and memory context.\n- **Per iteration:** Agent reads Next Focus, writes iteration evidence, and the reducer refreshes What Worked/Failed, answered questions, ruled-out directions, and Next Focus.\n- **Mutability:** Mutable — analyst-owned sections remain stable, while machine-owned sections are rewritten by the reducer after each iteration.\n- **Protection:** Shared state with explicit ownership boundaries. Orchestrator validates consistency on resume.\n\n---\n\n## 2. TOPIC\n[Research topic from config -- set during initialization]\n\n---\n\n## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n- [ ] [Question 1 -- identified during initialization or iteration 1]\n- [ ] [Question 2]\n- [ ] [Question 3]\n\n---\n\n## 4. NON-GOALS\n[What this research session is NOT trying to answer -- populated during initialization]\n\n---\n\n## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n[Explicit conditions beyond convergence that should end the session -- populated during initialization]\n\n---\n\n## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n[None yet -- populated as iterations answer questions]\n\n---\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n## 7. WHAT WORKED\n[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n- [Approach]: [Why it worked] (iteration N)\n\n---\n\n## 8. WHAT FAILED\n[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n- [Approach]: [Why it failed] (iteration N)\n\n---\n\n## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n[Populated when an approach has been tried from multiple angles without success]\n\n### [Category Name] -- BLOCKED (iteration N, N attempts)\n- What was tried: [specific approaches attempted]\n- Why blocked: [root cause of exhaustion]\n- Do NOT retry: [explicit prohibition]\n\n### [Category Name] -- PRODUCTIVE (iteration N)\n- What worked: [successful approaches in this category]\n- Prefer for: [related questions where this category may help]\n\n---\n\n## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n[Approaches that were investigated and definitively eliminated -- consolidated from iteration dead-end data]\n- [Approach]: [Why ruled out] (iteration N, evidence: [source])\n\n---\n\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n[Recommended focus area for the next iteration -- updated at end of each iteration]\n\n---\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n[Populated during initialization from memory_context() results, if any prior work exists]\n\n---\n\n## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n- Max iterations: [from config]\n- Convergence threshold: [from config]\n- Per-iteration budget: [from config.maxToolCallsPerIteration] tool calls, [from config.maxMinutesPerIteration] minutes\n- Progressive synthesis: true (default)\n- research/research.md ownership: workflow-owned canonical synthesis output\n- Lifecycle branches: `resume`, `restart` (live); `fork`, `completed-continue` (deferred, not runtime-wired)\n- Machine-owned sections: reducer controls Sections 3, 6, 7-11\n- Canonical pause sentinel: `research/.deep-research-pause`\n- Capability matrix: `.opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/runtime_capabilities.json`\n- Capability matrix doc: `.opencode/skills/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md`\n- Capability resolver: `.opencode/skills/deep-research/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs`\n- Current generation: [from config.lineage.generation]\n- Started: [timestamp]","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":118,"totalLines":118,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md","time":{"start":1781420777307,"end":1781420777309}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_03b34aadf3fdd607016a2e52e917ac81918a8e5d2d1f5dc168"}},"id":"prt_ec4f3df3e0015OUzZ1KaeK2OO2","sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","messageID":"msg_ec4f3baae001KbqlDyNudWl7Zx"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781420777315,"sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_aCZYcEOrAJsnMaR3wbqbAhe8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/deep_research_dashboard.md","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/deep_research_dashboard.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research Dashboard Template\n3: description: Template for the auto-generated dashboard file regenerated after every iteration from JSONL + strategy data. Provides human-readable session overview and recovery surface.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep research dashboard\"\n6:   - \"research session overview\"\n7:   - \"research dashboard template\"\n8:   - \"research convergence trend\"\n9:   - \"research dead ends section\"\n10: importance_tier: normal\n11: contextType: general\n12: ---\n13: \n14: # Deep Research Dashboard - Session Overview\n15: \n16: Auto-generated from JSONL state log and strategy file. Regenerated after every iteration evaluation. Never manually edited.\n17: \n18: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n19: \n20: ### Purpose\n21: \n22: Provides a compact, human-readable summary of the current research session. Serves three roles:\n23: 1. **Observability** — quick status check during long autonomous runs\n24: 2. **Recovery surface** — second recovery channel alongside JSONL after context compaction\n25: 3. **Lifecycle decision** — in confirm mode, shown before `resume` or `restart`\n26: \n27: ### Usage\n28: \n29: - **Location:** `{artifact_dir}/deep-research-dashboard.md`\n30: - **Generated by:** Orchestrator (step_generate_dashboard in YAML workflow)\n31: - **Data sources:** `deep-research-state.jsonl` + `findings-registry.json` + `deep-research-strategy.md`\n32: - **Protection:** `auto-generated` — overwritten each iteration, never manually edited\n33: \n34: ---\n35: \n36: ## 2. STATUS\n37: - Topic: [from config]\n38: - Started: [from config.createdAt]\n39: - Status: [ITERATING | CONVERGING | STUCK_RECOVERY | COMPLETE]\n40: - Iteration: [N] of [maxIterations]\n41: - Session ID: [from config.lineage.sessionId]\n42: - Parent Session: [from config.lineage.parentSessionId or none]\n43: - Lifecycle Mode: [new | resume | restart]\n44: - Generation: [from config.lineage.generation]\n45: \n46: ---\n47: \n48: ## 3. PROGRESS\n49: \n50: | # | Focus | Track | Ratio | Findings | Status |\n51: |---|-------|-------|-------|----------|--------|\n52: | [per iteration from JSONL] |\n53: \n54: - iterationsCompleted: [from findings registry metrics]\n55: - keyFindings: [from findings registry metrics]\n56: - openQuestions: [from findings registry metrics]\n57: - resolvedQuestions: [from findings registry metrics]\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: ## 4. QUESTIONS\n62: - Answered: [X/Y]\n63: - [x] Q1: [summary] (iteration N)\n64: - [ ] Q2: [remaining]\n65: \n66: ---\n67: \n68: ## 5. TREND\n69: - Last 3 ratios: [0.XX -> 0.XX -> 0.XX] [improving | stable | declining]\n70: - Stuck count: [N]\n71: - Guard violations: [none | list]\n72: - convergenceScore: [from reducer metrics]\n73: - coverageBySources: [from reducer metrics]\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ## 6. DEAD ENDS\n78: - [approach]: [reason] (iteration N)\n79: \n80: ---\n81: \n82: ## 7. NEXT FOCUS\n83: [from strategy.md \"Next Focus\" section]\n84: \n85: ---\n86: \n87: ## 8. ACTIVE RISKS\n88: - [guard violations, high stuck count, declining trend, etc.]\n89: - [migration events, reducer warnings, lifecycle conflicts]\n90: \n91: ---\n92: \n93: ## 9. EXAMPLE (POPULATED)\n94: \n95: Reference snippet showing what a rendered dashboard looks like after iteration 5 of a 10-iteration run. Use this as a visual anchor when inspecting a live dashboard.\n96: \n97: ```markdown\n98: # Deep Research Dashboard - Session Overview\n99: \n100: ## 2. STATUS\n101: - Topic: OpenCode plugin loader resilience\n102: - Started: 2026-04-20T09:14:22+02:00\n103: - Status: ITERATING\n104: - Iteration: 5 of 10\n105: - Session ID: dr-20260420-091422\n106: - Parent Session: none\n107: - Lifecycle Mode: new\n108: - Generation: 1\n109: \n110: ## 3. PROGRESS\n111: \n112: | # | Focus                       | Track        | Ratio | Findings | Status     |\n113: |---|-----------------------------|--------------|-------|----------|------------|\n114: | 1 | Entry-point discovery rules | architecture | 0.82  | 4        | converging |\n115: | 2 | ESM vs CommonJS interop     | runtime      | 0.64  | 3        | converging |\n116: | 3 | Plugin-load error surfaces  | observability| 0.47  | 2        | converging |\n117: | 4 | Host/plugin version gating  | lifecycle    | 0.35  | 2        | converging |\n118: | 5 | Cross-runtime parity        | portability  | 0.28  | 1        | converging |\n119: \n120: ## 5. CONVERGENCE TREND\n121: - Last 3 ratios: 0.47 -> 0.35 -> 0.28 (declining)\n122: - Stuck count: 0\n123: - Guard violations: none\n124: - convergenceScore: 0.71\n125: - coverageBySources: 0.83\n126: ```\n\n(End of file - total 126 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Dashboard Template\ndescription: Template for the auto-generated dashboard file regenerated after every iteration from JSONL + strategy data. Provides human-readable session overview and recovery surface.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep research dashboard\"\n  - \"research session overview\"\n  - \"research dashboard template\"\n  - \"research convergence trend\"\n  - \"research dead ends section\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: general\n---\n\n# Deep Research Dashboard - Session Overview\n\nAuto-generated from JSONL state log and strategy file. Regenerated after every iteration evaluation. Never manually edited.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/deep_research_dashboard.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Dashboard Template\ndescription: Template for the auto-generated dashboard file regenerated after every iteration from JSONL + strategy data. Provides human-readable session overview and recovery surface.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep research dashboard\"\n  - \"research session overview\"\n  - \"research dashboard template\"\n  - \"research convergence trend\"\n  - \"research dead ends section\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: general\n---\n\n# Deep Research Dashboard - Session Overview\n\nAuto-generated from JSONL state log and strategy file. Regenerated after every iteration evaluation. Never manually edited.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nProvides a compact, human-readable summary of the current research session. Serves three roles:\n1. **Observability** — quick status check during long autonomous runs\n2. **Recovery surface** — second recovery channel alongside JSONL after context compaction\n3. **Lifecycle decision** — in confirm mode, shown before `resume` or `restart`\n\n### Usage\n\n- **Location:** `{artifact_dir}/deep-research-dashboard.md`\n- **Generated by:** Orchestrator (step_generate_dashboard in YAML workflow)\n- **Data sources:** `deep-research-state.jsonl` + `findings-registry.json` + `deep-research-strategy.md`\n- **Protection:** `auto-generated` — overwritten each iteration, never manually edited\n\n---\n\n## 2. STATUS\n- Topic: [from config]\n- Started: [from config.createdAt]\n- Status: [ITERATING | CONVERGING | STUCK_RECOVERY | COMPLETE]\n- Iteration: [N] of [maxIterations]\n- Session ID: [from config.lineage.sessionId]\n- Parent Session: [from config.lineage.parentSessionId or none]\n- Lifecycle Mode: [new | resume | restart]\n- Generation: [from config.lineage.generation]\n\n---\n\n## 3. PROGRESS\n\n| # | Focus | Track | Ratio | Findings | Status |\n|---|-------|-------|-------|----------|--------|\n| [per iteration from JSONL] |\n\n- iterationsCompleted: [from findings registry metrics]\n- keyFindings: [from findings registry metrics]\n- openQuestions: [from findings registry metrics]\n- resolvedQuestions: [from findings registry metrics]\n\n---\n\n## 4. QUESTIONS\n- Answered: [X/Y]\n- [x] Q1: [summary] (iteration N)\n- [ ] Q2: [remaining]\n\n---\n\n## 5. TREND\n- Last 3 ratios: [0.XX -> 0.XX -> 0.XX] [improving | stable | declining]\n- Stuck count: [N]\n- Guard violations: [none | list]\n- convergenceScore: [from reducer metrics]\n- coverageBySources: [from reducer metrics]\n\n---\n\n## 6. DEAD ENDS\n- [approach]: [reason] (iteration N)\n\n---\n\n## 7. NEXT FOCUS\n[from strategy.md \"Next Focus\" section]\n\n---\n\n## 8. ACTIVE RISKS\n- [guard violations, high stuck count, declining trend, etc.]\n- [migration events, reducer warnings, lifecycle conflicts]\n\n---\n\n## 9. EXAMPLE (POPULATED)\n\nReference snippet showing what a rendered dashboard looks like after iteration 5 of a 10-iteration run. Use this as a visual anchor when inspecting a live dashboard.\n\n```markdown\n# Deep Research Dashboard - Session Overview\n\n## 2. STATUS\n- Topic: OpenCode plugin loader resilience\n- Started: 2026-04-20T09:14:22+02:00\n- Status: ITERATING\n- Iteration: 5 of 10\n- Session ID: dr-20260420-091422\n- Parent Session: none\n- Lifecycle Mode: new\n- Generation: 1\n\n## 3. PROGRESS\n\n| # | Focus                       | Track        | Ratio | Findings | Status     |\n|---|-----------------------------|--------------|-------|----------|------------|\n| 1 | Entry-point discovery rules | architecture | 0.82  | 4        | converging |\n| 2 | ESM vs CommonJS interop     | runtime      | 0.64  | 3        | converging |\n| 3 | Plugin-load error surfaces  | observability| 0.47  | 2        | converging |\n| 4 | Host/plugin version gating  | lifecycle    | 0.35  | 2        | converging |\n| 5 | Cross-runtime parity        | portability  | 0.28  | 1        | converging |\n\n## 5. CONVERGENCE TREND\n- Last 3 ratios: 0.47 -> 0.35 -> 0.28 (declining)\n- Stuck count: 0\n- Guard violations: none\n- convergenceScore: 0.71\n- coverageBySources: 0.83\n```","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":126,"totalLines":126,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/deep_research_dashboard.md","time":{"start":1781420777312,"end":1781420777314}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_03b34aadf3fdd607016a2e52e917b48191b1d59b5b4664ec3e"}},"id":"prt_ec4f3df5f001zeaRklVnh08xFC","sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","messageID":"msg_ec4f3baae001KbqlDyNudWl7Zx"}}
