{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781420784841,"sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_OePOkQbDPAzI67JBjJCmB45Q","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-research-loop_auto.yaml","offset":501,"limit":360},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-research-loop_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n501:                  gate_evidence_density_pass = no blocker named sourceDiversity or evidenceDepth\n502:                  gate_evidence_density_sources = graph_signals_json.sourceDiversity or 0\n503:                  gate_hotspot_saturation_pass = true\n504:                  recovery_strategy = first blocker reason/message, else \"Collect deeper graph evidence before stopping.\"\n505:                else if inline_stop_candidate and (graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\" or graph_decision is absent):\n506:                  decision = \"STOP\"\n507:                  reason = \"composite_converged\"\n508:                  stop_blocked = false\n509:           5. else: CONTINUE\n510:           6. if decision == \"STOP\" and reason != \"maxIterationsReached\":\n511:                guardResult = checkQualityGuards(state, strategy)\n512:                if not guardResult.passed:\n513:                  log: \"Quality guard failed: {guardResult.violations}. Overriding STOP to CONTINUE.\"\n514:                  decision = \"CONTINUE\"\n515:           See convergence.md for full pseudocode and signal definitions.\n516:           Segment-aware convergence is experimental/reference-only; live workflow uses the current session as a single segment.\n517:         outputs:\n518:           - decision: \"STOP | BLOCKED | STUCK_RECOVERY | CONTINUE\"\n519:           - reason: \"Human-readable stop reason\"\n520:           - stop_blocked: \"Boolean marker set when graph convergence vetoes an inline STOP candidate\"\n521:           - blocked_by_json: \"JSON array of graph blocker names when decision == BLOCKED\"\n522:           - blocked_by_csv: \"Comma-separated graph blocker names when decision == BLOCKED\"\n523:           - gate_convergence_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for the graph-assisted convergence gate\"\n524:           - gate_convergence_score: \"Numeric score recorded from graph convergence\"\n525:           - gate_key_question_coverage_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail derived from graph blocker coverage signals\"\n526:           - gate_evidence_density_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail derived from graph blocker evidence-depth signals\"\n527:           - gate_evidence_density_sources: \"Source-diversity count or equivalent evidence-depth proxy\"\n528:           - gate_hotspot_saturation_pass: \"Research placeholder gate; true unless an explicit blocker sets otherwise\"\n529:           - recovery_strategy: \"One-line hint describing the next research action when decision == BLOCKED or STUCK_RECOVERY\"\n530: \n531:       step_emit_blocked_stop:\n532:         action: \"Persist a first-class blocked_stop event when the legal-stop decision tree returns blocked\"\n533:         if_blocked:\n534:           append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"blockedBy\":{blocked_by_json},\"gateResults\":{\"convergence\":{\"pass\":{gate_convergence_pass},\"score\":{gate_convergence_score}},\"keyQuestionCoverage\":{\"pass\":{gate_key_question_coverage_pass},\"answered\":{answered_count},\"total\":{total_questions}},\"evidenceDensity\":{\"pass\":{gate_evidence_density_pass},\"sources\":{gate_evidence_density_sources}},\"hotspotSaturation\":{\"pass\":{gate_hotspot_saturation_pass}}},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n535:           log: \"Graph convergence blocked STOP. Failed blockers: {blocked_by_csv}. Recovery strategy: {recovery_strategy}\"\n536:           set:\n537:             decision: \"CONTINUE\"\n538:             reason: \"blockedStop\"\n539:             stop_blocked: false\n540: \n541:       step_handle_convergence:\n542:         action: \"Act on convergence decision\"\n543:         if_stop:\n544:           log: \"Loop stopping. Reason: {reason}\"\n545:           skip_to: phase_synthesis\n546:         if_stuck_recovery:\n547:           append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"outcome\":\"recovered\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n548:           log: \"Stuck detected ({stuck_count} consecutive no-progress). Entering recovery.\"\n549:           set: { next_focus: \"RECOVERY: Widen scope. Try fundamentally different approach. Least-explored question: {least_explored}\" }\n550:           reset: { stuck_count: 0 }\n551:         if_continue:\n552:           log: \"Iteration {current_iteration}: Continuing. Focus: {next_focus}\"\n553: \n554:       step_normalize_pause_events:\n555:         action: \"Normalize pause and recovery lifecycle events to the frozen STOP_REASONS enum at emission time\"\n556:         stop_reasons_enum: [converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused]\n557:         rule_pause_sentinel:\n558:           raw_event_forbidden: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"paused\"}'\n559:           canonical_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n560:         rule_stuck_recovery:\n561:           raw_event_forbidden: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuck_recovery\"}'\n562:           canonical_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"outcome\":\"recovered\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n563: \n564:       step_marker_scan:\n565:         action: \"H-2 loop-prevention guard: scan previous iteration's rendered prompt for nested research marker\"\n566:         algorithm: |\n567:           if current_iteration > 1:\n568:             PREV_PROMPT_PATH = \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{previous_iteration}.md\"\n569:             if file_exists(PREV_PROMPT_PATH):\n570:               PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE = head -1 of PREV_PROMPT_PATH\n571:               if PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE matches ^(DEEP-REVIEW|DEEP-RESEARCH|CODE-REVIEW)$:\n572:                 log \"ERROR: nested research-of-review loop detected (marker found in previous iteration prompt). Aborting.\"\n573:                 halt with exit code 2\n574:         note: |\n575:           False-positive prevention: only matches when the first line is exactly one of the\n576:           three canonical markers. Markers appearing in comments or body text are ignored.\n577:           True-positive triggers only when a previous iteration's rendered prompt literally\n578:           starts with a deep-loop marker, indicating a nested research-of-review dispatch.\n579: \n580:       step_dispatch_iteration:\n581:         action: \"Dispatch one iteration via the selected executor\"\n582:         resolve_executor:\n583:           source: \"config.executor\"\n584:           loader: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts#parseExecutorConfig\"\n585:         pre_dispatch:\n586:           generate_summary: |\n587:             STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n588:             Segment: {current_segment} | Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n589:             Questions: {answered_count}/{total_questions} answered | Last focus: {last_focus}\n590:             Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest} | Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n591:             {resource_map_prompt_line}\n592:             Next focus: {next_focus}\n593:           render_prompt_pack:\n594:             template_path: \".opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl\"\n595:             renderer: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/prompt-pack.ts#renderPromptPack\"\n596:             output_path: \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md\"\n597:             variables:\n598:               state_summary: \"{state_summary}\"\n599:               research_topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n600:               current_iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n601:               max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n602:               next_focus: \"{next_focus}\"\n603:               remaining_questions_list: \"{remaining_questions_list}\"\n604:               last_3_summaries: \"{last_3_summaries}\"\n605:               state_paths_config: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n606:               state_paths_state_log: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n607:               state_paths_strategy: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n608:               state_paths_registry: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n609:               state_paths_iteration_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n610:               state_paths_delta_pattern: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n611:         pre_dispatch_audit:\n612:           skip_when: \"config.executor.type == 'native'\"\n613:           call: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts#writeFirstRecordExecutor\"\n614:           args:\n615:             stateLogPath: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n616:             executor: \"{config.executor}\"\n617:             iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n618:         branch_on: \"config.executor.type\"\n619:         if_native:\n620:           dispatch:\n621:             agent: deep-research\n622:             model: opus\n623:             context_source: \"rendered_prompt_pack\"\n624:           wait_for_completion: true\n625:         if_cli_codex:\n626:           command: |\n627:             node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n628:             import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n629: \n630:             import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n631:             import { resolveCodexSandboxMode } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n632: \n633:             const executor = {\n634:               kind: 'cli-codex',\n635:               model: '{config.executor.model}',\n636:               reasoningEffort: '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}',\n637:               serviceTier: '{config.executor.serviceTier}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.serviceTier}',\n638:               sandboxMode: '{config.executor.sandboxMode}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.sandboxMode}',\n639:               timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n640:             };\n641: \n642:             process.exit(\n643:               runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n644:                 command: 'codex',\n645:                 args: [\n646:                   'exec',\n647:                   '--model',\n648:                   executor.model,\n649:                   '-c',\n650:                   `model_reasoning_effort=${executor.reasoningEffort}`,\n651:                   '-c',\n652:                   `service_tier=${executor.serviceTier}`,\n653:                   '-c',\n654:                   'approval_policy=never',\n655:                   '--sandbox',\n656:                   resolveCodexSandboxMode(executor.sandboxMode),\n657:                   '-',\n658:                 ],\n659:                 cwd: '{repo_root}',\n660:                 timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n661:                 stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n662:                 executor,\n663:                 iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n664:                 input: readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8'),\n665:               }),\n666:             );\n667:             EOF\n668:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n669:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n670:           wait_for_completion: true\n671:         if_cli_claude_code:\n672:           command: |\n673:             node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n674:             import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n675: \n676:             import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n677:             import { resolveClaudePermissionMode } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n678: \n679:             const executor = {\n680:               kind: 'cli-claude-code',\n681:               model: '{config.executor.model}',\n682:               reasoningEffort: '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}',\n683:               serviceTier: '{config.executor.serviceTier}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.serviceTier}',\n684:               sandboxMode: '{config.executor.sandboxMode}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.sandboxMode}',\n685:               timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n686:             };\n687:             const args = [\n688:               '-p',\n689:               readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8'),\n690:               '--model',\n691:               executor.model,\n692:               '--permission-mode',\n693:               resolveClaudePermissionMode(executor.sandboxMode),\n694:               '--output-format',\n695:               'text',\n696:             ];\n697:             if (executor.reasoningEffort) {\n698:               args.push('--effort', executor.reasoningEffort);\n699:             }\n700: \n701:             process.exit(\n702:               runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n703:                 command: 'claude',\n704:                 args,\n705:                 cwd: '{repo_root}',\n706:                 timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n707:                 stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n708:                 executor,\n709:                 iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n710:               }),\n711:             );\n712:             EOF\n713:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n714:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n715:           wait_for_completion: true\n716:           notes:\n717:             - \"sandboxMode maps to permission-mode: read-only -> plan, workspace-write -> acceptEdits, danger-full-access -> bypassPermissions\"\n718:             - \"claude-code has no serviceTier flag\"\n719:             - \"claude-code supports --effort for reasoning depth\"\n720:         record_executor_audit:\n721:           skip_when: \"config.executor.type == 'native'\"\n722:           target: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n723:           field: \"executor\"\n724:           value:\n725:             kind: \"{config.executor.type}\"\n726:             model: \"{config.executor.model}\"\n727:             reasoningEffort: \"{config.executor.reasoningEffort}\"\n728:             serviceTier: \"{config.executor.serviceTier}\"\n729:         if_cli_opencode:\n730:           command: |\n731:             opencode run \\\n732:               --model \"{config.executor.model}\" \\\n733:               --format json \\\n734:               --dangerously-skip-permissions \\\n735:               --pure \\\n736:               --dir \"{repo_root}\" \\\n737:               {optional_variant_flag} \\\n738:               \"$(cat '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md')\" \\\n739:               </dev/null\n740:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n741:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n742:           wait_for_completion: true\n743:           render_hint:\n744:             optional_variant_flag: |\n745:               If config.executor.reasoningEffort is set and non-null, expand to: --variant {config.executor.reasoningEffort}\n746:               Otherwise expand to empty string.\n747:           notes:\n748:             - \"opencode run takes a positional message; prompt is fed via command substitution\"\n749:             - \"--variant maps reasoningEffort to opencode's provider-specific reasoning lever (e.g., high, medium, minimal)\"\n750:             - \"--dangerously-skip-permissions enables hands-off automation; sandboxMode='read-only' is not currently honored (no opencode equivalent)\"\n751:             - \"cli-opencode self-invocation guard: this branch must only run from a non-OpenCode dispatch surface (Claude/Codex/raw shell). The cli-opencode skill SKILL.md §SELF-INVOCATION PROHIBITED contract is the authoritative gate\"\n752:             - \"</dev/null required: opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup before session creation. Without explicit closed stdin, automation that redirects stdout/stderr hangs at 0% CPU after `+60s snapshot prune cleanup`. See cli-opencode SKILL.md §4 ALWAYS rule + memory feedback_opencode_run_requires_dev_null_stdin.md.\"\n753:         post_dispatch_validate:\n754:           validator: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/post-dispatch-validate.ts#validateIterationOutputs\"\n755:           assert_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n756:           assert_appended: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n757:           assert_jsonl_fields: [type, iteration, newInfoRatio, status, focus]\n758:           assert_canonical_type: \"iteration\"\n759:           assert_delta_file_exists: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n760:           assert_delta_file_has_iteration_record: true\n761:           on_failure:\n762:             action: \"emit schema_mismatch canonical conflict event\"\n763:             escalation: \"After 3 consecutive failures, trigger stuck_recovery event with diagnostic context\"\n764:           failure_reasons_reference:\n765:             - \"iteration_file_missing — iteration narrative markdown not written\"\n766:             - \"iteration_file_empty — iteration narrative markdown is zero bytes\"\n767:             - \"jsonl_not_appended — state log file did not grow since pre-dispatch snapshot\"\n768:             - \"jsonl_missing_fields — last state-log record omits required schema fields\"\n769:             - \"jsonl_parse_error — last state-log line is not valid JSON\"\n770:             - \"jsonl_wrong_type — last state-log record uses type!='iteration' (e.g. 'iteration_delta'); reducer will silently drop\"\n771:             - \"delta_file_missing — per-iteration deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl not written\"\n772:             - \"delta_file_empty — per-iteration delta file exists but has zero bytes\"\n773:             - \"delta_file_missing_iteration_record — delta file lacks any record with type='iteration'\"\n774:             - \"executor_missing — non-native executor did not record provenance\"\n775:             - \"dispatch_failure_logged — last record is an explicit dispatch_failure event\"\n776: \n777:       step_reduce_state:\n778:         action: \"Run the reducer to synchronize registry, dashboard, and strategy\"\n779:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}\"\n780:         inputs:\n781:           latestJSONLDelta: \"Latest JSONL records written since the previous iteration\"\n782:           newIterationFile: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n783:           priorReducedState: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n784:         outputs:\n785:           - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n786:           - \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n787:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n788:         failure_modes:\n789:           malformed_delta: \"skip + warn\"\n790:           missing_iteration_file: \"no-op + error\"\n791:           schema_mismatch: \"reject + conflict event\"\n792:         guarantee: \"Idempotent for identical inputs\"\n793: \n794:       step_graph_upsert:\n795:         action: \"Persist the latest iteration graph delta after the reducer refresh and after the iteration file exists\"\n796:         read:\n797:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n798:         extract:\n799:           - latest_graph_events: \"Read graphEvents from the latest iteration record, else []\"\n800:           - graph_upsert_nodes_json: \"Map latest_graph_events where type == 'node' to node payloads with label -> name and preserve remaining node fields\"\n801:           - graph_upsert_edges_json: \"Map latest_graph_events where type == 'edge' to edge payloads with source -> sourceId, target -> targetId, relation -> uppercase(relation), and preserve remaining edge fields\"\n802:           - graph_upsert_event_count: \"Count mapped node and edge events\"\n803:         if_graph_events_present:\n804:           bash: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs --spec-folder \\\"{spec_folder}\\\" --loop-type \\\"research\\\" --session-id \\\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\\\" --nodes '{graph_upsert_nodes_json}' --edges '{graph_upsert_edges_json}'\"\n805:           note: \"Skip silently when graphEvents is missing or empty.\"\n806:         if_graph_events_missing:\n807:           proceed: true\n808: \n809:       step_evaluate_results:\n810:         action: \"Verify iteration outputs and extract metrics\"\n811:         verify:\n812:           - file_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n813:           - jsonl_appended: \"New iteration record in state.jsonl\"\n814:           - strategy_updated: \"Reducer refreshed strategy machine-owned sections\"\n815:           - registry_updated: \"Reducer refreshed deep-research-findings-registry.json\"\n816:         extract:\n817:           - newInfoRatio: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n818:           - findings_count: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n819:           - status: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n820:           - latest_focus: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n821:         on_missing_outputs:\n822:           action: \"Mark iteration as 'error', continue to next\"\n823:           # <!-- F-010-B5-02 -->\n824:           # Canonical iteration record: include mode, sessionId, generation, durationMs, keyQuestions, answeredQuestions\n825:           # so the reducer can persist the failure without dropping the iteration. Schema source: state_format.md §Iteration Records.\n826:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"error\",\"focus\":\"{next_focus}\",\"findingsCount\":0,\"newInfoRatio\":0.0,\"keyQuestions\":[],\"answeredQuestions\":[],\"durationMs\":0,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n827: \n828:       step_generate_dashboard:\n829:         action: \"Generate or refresh the human-readable dashboard\"\n830:         read:\n831:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n832:           - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n833:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n834:         template: .opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/deep_research_dashboard.md\n835:         output: \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n836:         note: \"Auto-generated from JSONL + reducer registry + strategy. Never manually edited.\"\n837: \n838:       step_update_tracking:\n839:         action: \"Update loop tracking variables\"\n840:         set:\n841:           current_iteration: \"{current_iteration + 1}\"\n842:           stuck_count: \"if status == 'thought': unchanged (skip). if status == 'insight': 0 (reset). if newInfoRatio < convergence_threshold: stuck_count + 1, else: 0\"\n843:         log: \"Iteration {N} complete. newInfoRatio: {newInfoRatio}. Findings: {findings_count}. Stuck count: {stuck_count}.\"\n844: \n845:       step_loop_decision:\n846:         action: \"Return to step_read_state for next iteration\"\n847:         goto: step_read_state\n848: \n849:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n850:   # PHASE 3: SYNTHESIS\n851:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n852:   phase_synthesis:\n853:     purpose: Compile all iteration findings into final research/research.md\n854:     steps:\n855: \n856:       step_fanout_merge:\n857:         description: \"Merge N lineage registries into one consolidated registry; skip when single-executor\"\n858:         skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n859:         command: |\n860:           node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-merge.cjs \\\n\n(Showing lines 501-860 of 1079. Use offset=861 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"                 gate_evidence_density_pass = no blocker named sourceDiversity or evidenceDepth\n                 gate_evidence_density_sources = graph_signals_json.sourceDiversity or 0\n                 gate_hotspot_saturation_pass = true\n                 recovery_strategy = first blocker reason/message, else \"Collect deeper graph evidence before stopping.\"\n               else if inline_stop_candidate and (graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\" or graph_decision is absent):\n                 decision = \"STOP\"\n                 reason = \"composite_converged\"\n                 stop_blocked = false\n          5. else: CONTINUE\n          6. if decision == \"STOP\" and reason != \"maxIterationsReached\":\n               guardResult = checkQualityGuards(state, strategy)\n               if not guardResult.passed:\n                 log: \"Quality guard failed: {guardResult.violations}. Overriding STOP to CONTINUE.\"\n                 decision = \"CONTINUE\"\n          See convergence.md for full pseudocode and signal definitions.\n          Segment-aware convergence is experimental/reference-only; live workflow uses the current session as a single segment.\n        outputs:\n          - decision: \"STOP | BLOCKED | STUCK_RECOVERY | CONTINUE\"\n          - reason: \"Human-readable stop reason\"\n          - stop_blocked: \"Boolean marker set when graph convergence vetoes an inline STOP candidate\"","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-research-loop_auto.yaml","text":"                 gate_evidence_density_pass = no blocker named sourceDiversity or evidenceDepth\n                 gate_evidence_density_sources = graph_signals_json.sourceDiversity or 0\n                 gate_hotspot_saturation_pass = true\n                 recovery_strategy = first blocker reason/message, else \"Collect deeper graph evidence before stopping.\"\n               else if inline_stop_candidate and (graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\" or graph_decision is absent):\n                 decision = \"STOP\"\n                 reason = \"composite_converged\"\n                 stop_blocked = false\n          5. else: CONTINUE\n          6. if decision == \"STOP\" and reason != \"maxIterationsReached\":\n               guardResult = checkQualityGuards(state, strategy)\n               if not guardResult.passed:\n                 log: \"Quality guard failed: {guardResult.violations}. Overriding STOP to CONTINUE.\"\n                 decision = \"CONTINUE\"\n          See convergence.md for full pseudocode and signal definitions.\n          Segment-aware convergence is experimental/reference-only; live workflow uses the current session as a single segment.\n        outputs:\n          - decision: \"STOP | BLOCKED | STUCK_RECOVERY | CONTINUE\"\n          - reason: \"Human-readable stop reason\"\n          - stop_blocked: \"Boolean marker set when graph convergence vetoes an inline STOP candidate\"\n          - blocked_by_json: \"JSON array of graph blocker names when decision == BLOCKED\"\n          - blocked_by_csv: \"Comma-separated graph blocker names when decision == BLOCKED\"\n          - gate_convergence_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for the graph-assisted convergence gate\"\n          - gate_convergence_score: \"Numeric score recorded from graph convergence\"\n          - gate_key_question_coverage_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail derived from graph blocker coverage signals\"\n          - gate_evidence_density_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail derived from graph blocker evidence-depth signals\"\n          - gate_evidence_density_sources: \"Source-diversity count or equivalent evidence-depth proxy\"\n          - gate_hotspot_saturation_pass: \"Research placeholder gate; true unless an explicit blocker sets otherwise\"\n          - recovery_strategy: \"One-line hint describing the next research action when decision == BLOCKED or STUCK_RECOVERY\"\n\n      step_emit_blocked_stop:\n        action: \"Persist a first-class blocked_stop event when the legal-stop decision tree returns blocked\"\n        if_blocked:\n          append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"blockedBy\":{blocked_by_json},\"gateResults\":{\"convergence\":{\"pass\":{gate_convergence_pass},\"score\":{gate_convergence_score}},\"keyQuestionCoverage\":{\"pass\":{gate_key_question_coverage_pass},\"answered\":{answered_count},\"total\":{total_questions}},\"evidenceDensity\":{\"pass\":{gate_evidence_density_pass},\"sources\":{gate_evidence_density_sources}},\"hotspotSaturation\":{\"pass\":{gate_hotspot_saturation_pass}}},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          log: \"Graph convergence blocked STOP. Failed blockers: {blocked_by_csv}. Recovery strategy: {recovery_strategy}\"\n          set:\n            decision: \"CONTINUE\"\n            reason: \"blockedStop\"\n            stop_blocked: false\n\n      step_handle_convergence:\n        action: \"Act on convergence decision\"\n        if_stop:\n          log: \"Loop stopping. Reason: {reason}\"\n          skip_to: phase_synthesis\n        if_stuck_recovery:\n          append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"outcome\":\"recovered\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          log: \"Stuck detected ({stuck_count} consecutive no-progress). Entering recovery.\"\n          set: { next_focus: \"RECOVERY: Widen scope. Try fundamentally different approach. Least-explored question: {least_explored}\" }\n          reset: { stuck_count: 0 }\n        if_continue:\n          log: \"Iteration {current_iteration}: Continuing. Focus: {next_focus}\"\n\n      step_normalize_pause_events:\n        action: \"Normalize pause and recovery lifecycle events to the frozen STOP_REASONS enum at emission time\"\n        stop_reasons_enum: [converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused]\n        rule_pause_sentinel:\n          raw_event_forbidden: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"paused\"}'\n          canonical_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n        rule_stuck_recovery:\n          raw_event_forbidden: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuck_recovery\"}'\n          canonical_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"outcome\":\"recovered\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n\n      step_marker_scan:\n        action: \"H-2 loop-prevention guard: scan previous iteration's rendered prompt for nested research marker\"\n        algorithm: |\n          if current_iteration > 1:\n            PREV_PROMPT_PATH = \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{previous_iteration}.md\"\n            if file_exists(PREV_PROMPT_PATH):\n              PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE = head -1 of PREV_PROMPT_PATH\n              if PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE matches ^(DEEP-REVIEW|DEEP-RESEARCH|CODE-REVIEW)$:\n                log \"ERROR: nested research-of-review loop detected (marker found in previous iteration prompt). Aborting.\"\n                halt with exit code 2\n        note: |\n          False-positive prevention: only matches when the first line is exactly one of the\n          three canonical markers. Markers appearing in comments or body text are ignored.\n          True-positive triggers only when a previous iteration's rendered prompt literally\n          starts with a deep-loop marker, indicating a nested research-of-review dispatch.\n\n      step_dispatch_iteration:\n        action: \"Dispatch one iteration via the selected executor\"\n        resolve_executor:\n          source: \"config.executor\"\n          loader: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts#parseExecutorConfig\"\n        pre_dispatch:\n          generate_summary: |\n            STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n            Segment: {current_segment} | Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n            Questions: {answered_count}/{total_questions} answered | Last focus: {last_focus}\n            Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest} | Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n            {resource_map_prompt_line}\n            Next focus: {next_focus}\n          render_prompt_pack:\n            template_path: \".opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl\"\n            renderer: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/prompt-pack.ts#renderPromptPack\"\n            output_path: \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md\"\n            variables:\n              state_summary: \"{state_summary}\"\n              research_topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n              current_iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n              max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n              next_focus: \"{next_focus}\"\n              remaining_questions_list: \"{remaining_questions_list}\"\n              last_3_summaries: \"{last_3_summaries}\"\n              state_paths_config: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n              state_paths_state_log: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n              state_paths_strategy: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n              state_paths_registry: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n              state_paths_iteration_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n              state_paths_delta_pattern: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n        pre_dispatch_audit:\n          skip_when: \"config.executor.type == 'native'\"\n          call: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts#writeFirstRecordExecutor\"\n          args:\n            stateLogPath: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n            executor: \"{config.executor}\"\n            iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n        branch_on: \"config.executor.type\"\n        if_native:\n          dispatch:\n            agent: deep-research\n            model: opus\n            context_source: \"rendered_prompt_pack\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n        if_cli_codex:\n          command: |\n            node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n            import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n\n            import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n            import { resolveCodexSandboxMode } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n\n            const executor = {\n              kind: 'cli-codex',\n              model: '{config.executor.model}',\n              reasoningEffort: '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}',\n              serviceTier: '{config.executor.serviceTier}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.serviceTier}',\n              sandboxMode: '{config.executor.sandboxMode}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.sandboxMode}',\n              timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n            };\n\n            process.exit(\n              runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n                command: 'codex',\n                args: [\n                  'exec',\n                  '--model',\n                  executor.model,\n                  '-c',\n                  `model_reasoning_effort=${executor.reasoningEffort}`,\n                  '-c',\n                  `service_tier=${executor.serviceTier}`,\n                  '-c',\n                  'approval_policy=never',\n                  '--sandbox',\n                  resolveCodexSandboxMode(executor.sandboxMode),\n                  '-',\n                ],\n                cwd: '{repo_root}',\n                timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n                stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n                executor,\n                iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n                input: readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8'),\n              }),\n            );\n            EOF\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n        if_cli_claude_code:\n          command: |\n            node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n            import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n\n            import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n            import { resolveClaudePermissionMode } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n\n            const executor = {\n              kind: 'cli-claude-code',\n              model: '{config.executor.model}',\n              reasoningEffort: '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}',\n              serviceTier: '{config.executor.serviceTier}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.serviceTier}',\n              sandboxMode: '{config.executor.sandboxMode}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.sandboxMode}',\n              timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n            };\n            const args = [\n              '-p',\n              readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8'),\n              '--model',\n              executor.model,\n              '--permission-mode',\n              resolveClaudePermissionMode(executor.sandboxMode),\n              '--output-format',\n              'text',\n            ];\n            if (executor.reasoningEffort) {\n              args.push('--effort', executor.reasoningEffort);\n            }\n\n            process.exit(\n              runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n                command: 'claude',\n                args,\n                cwd: '{repo_root}',\n                timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n                stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n                executor,\n                iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n              }),\n            );\n            EOF\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          notes:\n            - \"sandboxMode maps to permission-mode: read-only -> plan, workspace-write -> acceptEdits, danger-full-access -> bypassPermissions\"\n            - \"claude-code has no serviceTier flag\"\n            - \"claude-code supports --effort for reasoning depth\"\n        record_executor_audit:\n          skip_when: \"config.executor.type == 'native'\"\n          target: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          field: \"executor\"\n          value:\n            kind: \"{config.executor.type}\"\n            model: \"{config.executor.model}\"\n            reasoningEffort: \"{config.executor.reasoningEffort}\"\n            serviceTier: \"{config.executor.serviceTier}\"\n        if_cli_opencode:\n          command: |\n            opencode run \\\n              --model \"{config.executor.model}\" \\\n              --format json \\\n              --dangerously-skip-permissions \\\n              --pure \\\n              --dir \"{repo_root}\" \\\n              {optional_variant_flag} \\\n              \"$(cat '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md')\" \\\n              </dev/null\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          render_hint:\n            optional_variant_flag: |\n              If config.executor.reasoningEffort is set and non-null, expand to: --variant {config.executor.reasoningEffort}\n              Otherwise expand to empty string.\n          notes:\n            - \"opencode run takes a positional message; prompt is fed via command substitution\"\n            - \"--variant maps reasoningEffort to opencode's provider-specific reasoning lever (e.g., high, medium, minimal)\"\n            - \"--dangerously-skip-permissions enables hands-off automation; sandboxMode='read-only' is not currently honored (no opencode equivalent)\"\n            - \"cli-opencode self-invocation guard: this branch must only run from a non-OpenCode dispatch surface (Claude/Codex/raw shell). The cli-opencode skill SKILL.md §SELF-INVOCATION PROHIBITED contract is the authoritative gate\"\n            - \"</dev/null required: opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup before session creation. Without explicit closed stdin, automation that redirects stdout/stderr hangs at 0% CPU after `+60s snapshot prune cleanup`. See cli-opencode SKILL.md §4 ALWAYS rule + memory feedback_opencode_run_requires_dev_null_stdin.md.\"\n        post_dispatch_validate:\n          validator: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/post-dispatch-validate.ts#validateIterationOutputs\"\n          assert_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          assert_appended: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          assert_jsonl_fields: [type, iteration, newInfoRatio, status, focus]\n          assert_canonical_type: \"iteration\"\n          assert_delta_file_exists: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n          assert_delta_file_has_iteration_record: true\n          on_failure:\n            action: \"emit schema_mismatch canonical conflict event\"\n            escalation: \"After 3 consecutive failures, trigger stuck_recovery event with diagnostic context\"\n          failure_reasons_reference:\n            - \"iteration_file_missing — iteration narrative markdown not written\"\n            - \"iteration_file_empty — iteration narrative markdown is zero bytes\"\n            - \"jsonl_not_appended — state log file did not grow since pre-dispatch snapshot\"\n            - \"jsonl_missing_fields — last state-log record omits required schema fields\"\n            - \"jsonl_parse_error — last state-log line is not valid JSON\"\n            - \"jsonl_wrong_type — last state-log record uses type!='iteration' (e.g. 'iteration_delta'); reducer will silently drop\"\n            - \"delta_file_missing — per-iteration deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl not written\"\n            - \"delta_file_empty — per-iteration delta file exists but has zero bytes\"\n            - \"delta_file_missing_iteration_record — delta file lacks any record with type='iteration'\"\n            - \"executor_missing — non-native executor did not record provenance\"\n            - \"dispatch_failure_logged — last record is an explicit dispatch_failure event\"\n\n      step_reduce_state:\n        action: \"Run the reducer to synchronize registry, dashboard, and strategy\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}\"\n        inputs:\n          latestJSONLDelta: \"Latest JSONL records written since the previous iteration\"\n          newIterationFile: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          priorReducedState: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n        outputs:\n          - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        failure_modes:\n          malformed_delta: \"skip + warn\"\n          missing_iteration_file: \"no-op + error\"\n          schema_mismatch: \"reject + conflict event\"\n        guarantee: \"Idempotent for identical inputs\"\n\n      step_graph_upsert:\n        action: \"Persist the latest iteration graph delta after the reducer refresh and after the iteration file exists\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n        extract:\n          - latest_graph_events: \"Read graphEvents from the latest iteration record, else []\"\n          - graph_upsert_nodes_json: \"Map latest_graph_events where type == 'node' to node payloads with label -> name and preserve remaining node fields\"\n          - graph_upsert_edges_json: \"Map latest_graph_events where type == 'edge' to edge payloads with source -> sourceId, target -> targetId, relation -> uppercase(relation), and preserve remaining edge fields\"\n          - graph_upsert_event_count: \"Count mapped node and edge events\"\n        if_graph_events_present:\n          bash: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs --spec-folder \\\"{spec_folder}\\\" --loop-type \\\"research\\\" --session-id \\\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\\\" --nodes '{graph_upsert_nodes_json}' --edges '{graph_upsert_edges_json}'\"\n          note: \"Skip silently when graphEvents is missing or empty.\"\n        if_graph_events_missing:\n          proceed: true\n\n      step_evaluate_results:\n        action: \"Verify iteration outputs and extract metrics\"\n        verify:\n          - file_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          - jsonl_appended: \"New iteration record in state.jsonl\"\n          - strategy_updated: \"Reducer refreshed strategy machine-owned sections\"\n          - registry_updated: \"Reducer refreshed deep-research-findings-registry.json\"\n        extract:\n          - newInfoRatio: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - findings_count: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - status: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - latest_focus: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n        on_missing_outputs:\n          action: \"Mark iteration as 'error', continue to next\"\n          # <!-- F-010-B5-02 -->\n          # Canonical iteration record: include mode, sessionId, generation, durationMs, keyQuestions, answeredQuestions\n          # so the reducer can persist the failure without dropping the iteration. Schema source: state_format.md §Iteration Records.\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"error\",\"focus\":\"{next_focus}\",\"findingsCount\":0,\"newInfoRatio\":0.0,\"keyQuestions\":[],\"answeredQuestions\":[],\"durationMs\":0,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n\n      step_generate_dashboard:\n        action: \"Generate or refresh the human-readable dashboard\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/deep_research_dashboard.md\n        output: \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n        note: \"Auto-generated from JSONL + reducer registry + strategy. Never manually edited.\"\n\n      step_update_tracking:\n        action: \"Update loop tracking variables\"\n        set:\n          current_iteration: \"{current_iteration + 1}\"\n          stuck_count: \"if status == 'thought': unchanged (skip). if status == 'insight': 0 (reset). if newInfoRatio < convergence_threshold: stuck_count + 1, else: 0\"\n        log: \"Iteration {N} complete. newInfoRatio: {newInfoRatio}. Findings: {findings_count}. Stuck count: {stuck_count}.\"\n\n      step_loop_decision:\n        action: \"Return to step_read_state for next iteration\"\n        goto: step_read_state\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 3: SYNTHESIS\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_synthesis:\n    purpose: Compile all iteration findings into final research/research.md\n    steps:\n\n      step_fanout_merge:\n        description: \"Merge N lineage registries into one consolidated registry; skip when single-executor\"\n        skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n        command: |\n          node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-merge.cjs \\","lineStart":501,"lineEnd":860,"totalLines":1079,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-research-loop_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1781420784831,"end":1781420784840}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09bae70769a22d2a016a2e52f0c9748191acb502ba98ec2b55"}},"id":"prt_ec4f3fcaf001R1eDwpwtoSNW7u","sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","messageID":"msg_ec4f3e19d0013AT9kgTZ1SOMKZ"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781420784886,"sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_n32ayDQoaWVaE0hO9cUIuZVQ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Spec Check Protocol\n3: description: Canonical contract for late-INIT spec.md detection, bounded mutation, advisory locking, and post-synthesis write-back in deep-research.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"spec check protocol\"\n6:   - \"research advisory lock\"\n7:   - \"spec folder state classification\"\n8:   - \"post-synthesis write-back\"\n9:   - \"research spec conflict detection\"\n10: importance_tier: important\n11: contextType: implementation\n12: ---\n13: \n14: # Spec Check Protocol\n15: \n16: Canonical contract for how `/deep:start-research-loop` inspects and mutates `spec.md` without turning that work into an unbounded side effect.\n17: \n18: ---\n19: \n20: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n21: \n22: ### Purpose\n23: Define the bounded `spec.md` integration points for deep-research:\n24: - Late-INIT lock acquisition and folder-state detection\n25: - Pre-init seed or context mutation before LOOP starts\n26: - Post-synthesis generated-fence write-back before save or cancellation cleanup\n27: \n28: ### Scope\n29: This protocol applies only to deep-research-owned `spec.md` mutations:\n30: - Seeded Level 1 `spec.md` creation when no spec exists\n31: - Anchor-bounded pre-init context updates to an existing `spec.md`\n32: - One generated findings block written after synthesis\n33: \n34: This protocol does not own the shared intake contract in `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/intake_contract.md`, nor `/speckit:plan` or `/speckit:complete` delegation behavior.\n35: \n36: ### Relation to the Deep-Research Loop\n37: The workflow remains four-phase:\n38: 1. INIT resolves canonical paths, acquires the advisory lock, and classifies `folder_state`\n39: 2. LOOP runs only after the pre-init spec branch is complete\n40: 3. SYNTHESIS compiles `research/research.md` and then performs bounded write-back\n41: 4. SAVE handles continuity refresh and lock release\n42: \n43: `research/research.md` remains the source of truth. `spec.md` receives only the bounded seed markers, pre-init context note, and the generated findings block described below.\n44: \n45: ---\n46: \n47: ## 2. ADVISORY LOCK LIFECYCLE\n48: \n49: ### Lock File\n50: - Path: `{spec_folder}/research/.deep-research.lock`\n51: - Scope: one live deep-research writer per spec folder\n52: - Ownership: acquired by the deep-research workflow, not by the leaf agent\n53: \n54: ### Lifecycle\n55: 1. Resolve canonical research packet paths.\n56: 2. Acquire the lock in late INIT before `folder_state` classification.\n57: 3. Hold the lock through:\n58:    - pre-init seed or append work\n59:    - every LOOP iteration\n60:    - synthesis compilation\n61:    - post-synthesis generated-block replacement\n62: 4. Release the lock only after the save, skip-save, or cancel path has resolved.\n63: \n64: ### Semantics\n65: - Locking is advisory, not mandatory.\n66: - macOS and BSD follow POSIX advisory lock semantics for `flock()` and `fcntl()` style coordination.\n67: - Lock contention is fail-closed. A second live writer does not merge or override.\n68: - Stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\n69: \n70: ### Required Audit Behavior\n71: - Successful acquisition records the resolved lock path and session lineage.\n72: - Release records whether the workflow ended with save, skip-save, or cancellation cleanup.\n73: \n74: ---\n75: \n76: ## 3. FOLDER STATE CLASSIFICATION\n77: \n78: `step_detect_spec_present` outputs exactly one `folder_state` value:\n79: \n80: | `folder_state` | Meaning | Expected next action |\n81: |----------------|---------|----------------------|\n82: | `no-spec` | `spec.md` does not exist yet | Seed a Level 1 `spec.md` before LOOP |\n83: | `spec-present` | `spec.md` exists and approved host anchors are available | Apply bounded pre-init context updates |\n84: | `spec-just-created-by-this-run` | This run already seeded `spec.md` and can verify the DR seed markers | Do not reseed or duplicate pre-init context |\n85: | `conflict-detected` | Host anchors, markers, or human-authored content make mutation ambiguous | Emit typed audit and halt fail-closed |\n86: \n87: ### Detection Inputs\n88: - `spec_folder`\n89: - `research_topic`\n90: - `normalized_topic`\n91: - resolved host anchors in `spec.md`\n92: - existing `<!-- DR-SEED:... -->` markers\n93: - existing generated findings fence markers\n94: \n95: ### Detection Guarantees\n96: - Classification happens after config, JSONL, strategy, and registry exist.\n97: - The result is passed into INIT and SYNTHESIS.\n98: - The workflow records a typed `spec_check_result` audit event before any mutation branch executes.\n99: \n100: ---\n101: \n102: ## 4. PRE-INIT BRANCHES\n103: \n104: ### `no-spec`\n105: - Create a Level 1 `spec.md` seeded from the research ask.\n106: - Insert tracked seed markers:\n107:   - `<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->` under Requirements\n108:   - `<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->` under Scope\n109: - Emit `spec_seed_created`.\n110: - Set `folder_state = spec-just-created-by-this-run` before LOOP begins.\n111: \n112: ### `spec-present`\n113: - Normalize the research topic before any append.\n114: - Append the topic only at bounded host locations:\n115:   - `Open Questions`\n116:   - a compact `Research Context` note\n117: - Do not rewrite adjacent prose or broaden the scope of the packet.\n118: - Emit `spec_preinit_context_added`.\n119: \n120: ### `spec-just-created-by-this-run`\n121: - Re-check the DR seed markers and continue without reseeding.\n122: - Treat marker verification as a no-op guard, not as another mutation.\n123: \n124: ### `conflict-detected`\n125: - Emit `spec_mutation_conflict`.\n126: - Halt before LOOP.\n127: - Do not attempt fallback rewrites or inferred merges.\n128: \n129: ---\n130: \n131: ## 5. POST-SYNTHESIS WRITE-BACK\n132: \n133: ### Timing\n134: Run after `research/research.md` compilation during SYNTHESIS and before config completion or any memory-save branch.\n135: \n136: ### Write-Back Shape\n137: The workflow writes or replaces exactly one machine-owned fence nested under the chosen host anchor:\n138: \n139: ```md\n140: <!-- BEGIN GENERATED: deep-research/spec-findings -->\n141: [abridged findings derived from research/research.md]\n142: <!-- END GENERATED: deep-research/spec-findings -->\n143: ```\n144: \n145: ### Contract\n146: - `research/research.md` remains the source of truth.\n147: - The generated block is an abridged sync, not a second canonical narrative.\n148: - The workflow replaces the full block atomically when content changes.\n149: - Interrupted synthesis does not leave a partial block behind; emit `spec_synthesis_deferred` instead.\n150: \n151: ### Host Anchor Rules\n152: - The host anchor must already exist or be deterministically created by the seed path.\n153: - The generated block must be nested under that one chosen host anchor only.\n154: - The workflow must not create duplicate generated blocks in sibling sections.\n155: \n156: ---\n157: \n158: ## 6. AUDIT EVENTS\n159: \n160: All protocol events are appended to `research/deep-research-state.jsonl`.\n161: \n162: Every audit payload is typed. At minimum, emit:\n163: - `type`\n164: - `event`\n165: - `timestamp`\n166: - `specPath` or `specFolder`\n167: - the contextual discriminator for the event (`folder_state`, `normalized_topic`, `generatedFence`, `packetIds`, `conflictKind`, or similar)\n168: \n169: | Event | Minimum payload schema |\n170: |-------|------------------------|\n171: | `spec_check_result` | `{ \"type\": \"event\", \"event\": \"spec_check_result\", \"folder_state\": \"...\", \"normalized_topic\": \"...\", \"specPath\": \"...\", \"hostAnchor\": \"...\", \"timestamp\": \"...\" }` |\n172: | `spec_seed_created` | `{ \"type\": \"spec_mutation\", \"event\": \"spec_seed_created\", \"folder_state\": \"spec-just-created-by-this-run\", \"anchors_touched\": [\"Scope\", \"Requirements\"], \"diff_summary\": \"...\", \"seed_markers\": [\"DR-SEED:SCOPE\", \"DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS\"], \"timestamp\": \"...\" }` |\n173: | `spec_preinit_context_added` | `{ \"type\": \"spec_mutation\", \"event\": \"spec_preinit_context_added\", \"folder_state\": \"spec-present\", \"anchors_touched\": [\"Open Questions\", \"Research Context\"], \"diff_summary\": \"...\", \"normalized_topic\": \"...\", \"timestamp\": \"...\" }` |\n174: | `spec_preinit_context_deduped` | `{ \"type\": \"spec_mutation\", \"event\": \"spec_preinit_context_deduped\", \"folder_state\": \"spec-present\", \"anchors_touched\": [\"Open Questions\"], \"diff_summary\": \"...\", \"normalized_topic\": \"...\", \"specPath\": \"...\", \"timestamp\": \"...\" }` |\n175: | `spec_mutation` | `{ \"type\": \"spec_mutation\", \"event\": \"spec_mutation\", \"phase\": \"post-synthesis\", \"anchors_touched\": [\"<chosen host anchor>\"], \"diff_summary\": \"...\", \"generatedFence\": \"deep-research/spec-findings\", \"timestamp\": \"...\" }` |\n176: | `spec_mutation_conflict` | `{ \"type\": \"spec_mutation\", \"event\": \"spec_mutation_conflict\", \"folder_state\": \"conflict-detected\", \"reason\": \"...\", \"hostAnchor\": \"...\", \"specPath\": \"...\", \"generatedFence\": \"deep-research/spec-findings\", \"conflictKind\": \"...\", \"timestamp\": \"...\" }` |\n177: | `spec_synthesis_deferred` | `{ \"type\": \"spec_mutation\", \"event\": \"spec_synthesis_deferred\", \"reason\": \"...\", \"generatedFence\": \"deep-research/spec-findings\", \"timestamp\": \"...\" }` |\n178: \n179: ### Audit Requirements\n180: - Every real `spec.md` mutation records `anchors_touched` and `diff_summary`.\n181: - The protocol never relies on prose logs alone.\n182: - Conflict exits and deferred write-back are auditable from JSONL without opening the mutated file.\n183: \n184: ---\n185: \n186: ## 7. IDEMPOTENCY RULES\n187: \n188: ### Topic Dedupe\n189: - Lowercase, strip punctuation, collapse whitespace, and trim before comparing research topics.\n190: - Re-running with the same `normalized_topic` must no-op instead of appending another pre-init note.\n191: - The shared intake contract (`.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/intake_contract.md` §5-§6) applies the same normalization before writing `feature_description` into `spec.md` Problem Statement or Purpose; equivalent normalized phrases emit `intake_topic_deduped` instead of overwriting the existing prose.\n192: \n193: ### Marker-Based Placeholder Detection\n194: - Seed behavior depends on deterministic `<!-- DR-SEED:... -->` markers, not fuzzy prose matching.\n195: - If the required seed markers already exist, treat the seed path as already satisfied.\n196: - The shared intake contract used by `/speckit:plan --intake-only`, `/speckit:plan`, and `/speckit:complete` classifies any retained DR seed marker as `placeholder-upgrade` and persists `resume_question_id` plus `reentry_reason` for REQ-011 re-entry.\n197: \n198: ### Relation-Object Dedupe\n199: - Manual relationship arrays dedupe by `packet_id` within each relation type (`depends_on`, `related_to`, `supersedes`) before emitting `graph-metadata.json`.\n200: - Dedupe outcomes emit `relationship_deduped` with typed payload fields such as `dedupedCount` and `packetIds`.\n201: \n202: ### Generated-Block Replacement\n203: - The generated findings block is matched by the exact marker pair:\n204:   - `<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: deep-research/spec-findings -->`\n205:   - `<!-- END GENERATED: deep-research/spec-findings -->`\n206: - Same host anchor plus same generated content resolves to a no-op.\n207: - If the existing generated block fails checksum validation or carries an explicit manual-edit marker, emit `spec_mutation_conflict` and halt instead of overwriting.\n208: \n209: ### Cross-Command Compatibility\n210: - Relation objects shared with sibling intake flows dedupe by `packet_id`.\n211: - This protocol does not create manual relationship edges itself, but it must not reintroduce duplicate relation objects if that metadata is surfaced during a future delegated sync.\n212: \n213: ---\n214: \n215: ## 8. CONFLICT EXITS\n216: \n217: Fail closed when any of the following is true:\n218: - The chosen host anchor is missing.\n219: - Duplicate DR seed markers are present.\n220: - Duplicate generated fence markers are present.\n221: - Human edits are detected inside the machine-owned generated block.\n222: - The generated block checksum drifts or an explicit manual-edit marker is present inside the existing fence.\n223: - Pre-init append intent conflicts with the semantic purpose of the host section.\n224: \n225: ### Exit Behavior\n226: 1. Emit `spec_mutation_conflict`.\n227: 2. Keep existing `spec.md` content unchanged.\n228: 3. Stop before LOOP or before SAVE, depending on the phase.\n229: 4. Surface the exact blocking reason to the operator.\n230: \n231: No silent merge, overwrite, or best-effort repair is allowed on a conflict path.\n\n(End of file - total 231 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Spec Check Protocol\ndescription: Canonical contract for late-INIT spec.md detection, bounded mutation, advisory locking, and post-synthesis write-back in deep-research.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"spec check protocol\"\n  - \"research advisory lock\"\n  - \"spec folder state classification\"\n  - \"post-synthesis write-back\"\n  - \"research spec conflict detection\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\n---\n\n# Spec Check Protocol\n\nCanonical contract for how `/deep:start-research-loop` inspects and mutates `spec.md` without turning that work into an unbounded side effect.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md","text":"---\ntitle: Spec Check Protocol\ndescription: Canonical contract for late-INIT spec.md detection, bounded mutation, advisory locking, and post-synthesis write-back in deep-research.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"spec check protocol\"\n  - \"research advisory lock\"\n  - \"spec folder state classification\"\n  - \"post-synthesis write-back\"\n  - \"research spec conflict detection\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\n---\n\n# Spec Check Protocol\n\nCanonical contract for how `/deep:start-research-loop` inspects and mutates `spec.md` without turning that work into an unbounded side effect.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\nDefine the bounded `spec.md` integration points for deep-research:\n- Late-INIT lock acquisition and folder-state detection\n- Pre-init seed or context mutation before LOOP starts\n- Post-synthesis generated-fence write-back before save or cancellation cleanup\n\n### Scope\nThis protocol applies only to deep-research-owned `spec.md` mutations:\n- Seeded Level 1 `spec.md` creation when no spec exists\n- Anchor-bounded pre-init context updates to an existing `spec.md`\n- One generated findings block written after synthesis\n\nThis protocol does not own the shared intake contract in `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/intake_contract.md`, nor `/speckit:plan` or `/speckit:complete` delegation behavior.\n\n### Relation to the Deep-Research Loop\nThe workflow remains four-phase:\n1. INIT resolves canonical paths, acquires the advisory lock, and classifies `folder_state`\n2. LOOP runs only after the pre-init spec branch is complete\n3. SYNTHESIS compiles `research/research.md` and then performs bounded write-back\n4. SAVE handles continuity refresh and lock release\n\n`research/research.md` remains the source of truth. `spec.md` receives only the bounded seed markers, pre-init context note, and the generated findings block described below.\n\n---\n\n## 2. ADVISORY LOCK LIFECYCLE\n\n### Lock File\n- Path: `{spec_folder}/research/.deep-research.lock`\n- Scope: one live deep-research writer per spec folder\n- Ownership: acquired by the deep-research workflow, not by the leaf agent\n\n### Lifecycle\n1. Resolve canonical research packet paths.\n2. Acquire the lock in late INIT before `folder_state` classification.\n3. Hold the lock through:\n   - pre-init seed or append work\n   - every LOOP iteration\n   - synthesis compilation\n   - post-synthesis generated-block replacement\n4. Release the lock only after the save, skip-save, or cancel path has resolved.\n\n### Semantics\n- Locking is advisory, not mandatory.\n- macOS and BSD follow POSIX advisory lock semantics for `flock()` and `fcntl()` style coordination.\n- Lock contention is fail-closed. A second live writer does not merge or override.\n- Stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\n\n### Required Audit Behavior\n- Successful acquisition records the resolved lock path and session lineage.\n- Release records whether the workflow ended with save, skip-save, or cancellation cleanup.\n\n---\n\n## 3. FOLDER STATE CLASSIFICATION\n\n`step_detect_spec_present` outputs exactly one `folder_state` value:\n\n| `folder_state` | Meaning | Expected next action |\n|----------------|---------|----------------------|\n| `no-spec` | `spec.md` does not exist yet | Seed a Level 1 `spec.md` before LOOP |\n| `spec-present` | `spec.md` exists and approved host anchors are available | Apply bounded pre-init context updates |\n| `spec-just-created-by-this-run` | This run already seeded `spec.md` and can verify the DR seed markers | Do not reseed or duplicate pre-init context |\n| `conflict-detected` | Host anchors, markers, or human-authored content make mutation ambiguous | Emit typed audit and halt fail-closed |\n\n### Detection Inputs\n- `spec_folder`\n- `research_topic`\n- `normalized_topic`\n- resolved host anchors in `spec.md`\n- existing `<!-- DR-SEED:... -->` markers\n- existing generated findings fence markers\n\n### Detection Guarantees\n- Classification happens after config, JSONL, strategy, and registry exist.\n- The result is passed into INIT and SYNTHESIS.\n- The workflow records a typed `spec_check_result` audit event before any mutation branch executes.\n\n---\n\n## 4. PRE-INIT BRANCHES\n\n### `no-spec`\n- Create a Level 1 `spec.md` seeded from the research ask.\n- Insert tracked seed markers:\n  - `<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->` under Requirements\n  - `<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->` under Scope\n- Emit `spec_seed_created`.\n- Set `folder_state = spec-just-created-by-this-run` before LOOP begins.\n\n### `spec-present`\n- Normalize the research topic before any append.\n- Append the topic only at bounded host locations:\n  - `Open Questions`\n  - a compact `Research Context` note\n- Do not rewrite adjacent prose or broaden the scope of the packet.\n- Emit `spec_preinit_context_added`.\n\n### `spec-just-created-by-this-run`\n- Re-check the DR seed markers and continue without reseeding.\n- Treat marker verification as a no-op guard, not as another mutation.\n\n### `conflict-detected`\n- Emit `spec_mutation_conflict`.\n- Halt before LOOP.\n- Do not attempt fallback rewrites or inferred merges.\n\n---\n\n## 5. POST-SYNTHESIS WRITE-BACK\n\n### Timing\nRun after `research/research.md` compilation during SYNTHESIS and before config completion or any memory-save branch.\n\n### Write-Back Shape\nThe workflow writes or replaces exactly one machine-owned fence nested under the chosen host anchor:\n\n```md\n<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: deep-research/spec-findings -->\n[abridged findings derived from research/research.md]\n<!-- END GENERATED: deep-research/spec-findings -->\n```\n\n### Contract\n- `research/research.md` remains the source of truth.\n- The generated block is an abridged sync, not a second canonical narrative.\n- The workflow replaces the full block atomically when content changes.\n- Interrupted synthesis does not leave a partial block behind; emit `spec_synthesis_deferred` instead.\n\n### Host Anchor Rules\n- The host anchor must already exist or be deterministically created by the seed path.\n- The generated block must be nested under that one chosen host anchor only.\n- The workflow must not create duplicate generated blocks in sibling sections.\n\n---\n\n## 6. AUDIT EVENTS\n\nAll protocol events are appended to `research/deep-research-state.jsonl`.\n\nEvery audit payload is typed. At minimum, emit:\n- `type`\n- `event`\n- `timestamp`\n- `specPath` or `specFolder`\n- the contextual discriminator for the event (`folder_state`, `normalized_topic`, `generatedFence`, `packetIds`, `conflictKind`, or similar)\n\n| Event | Minimum payload schema |\n|-------|------------------------|\n| `spec_check_result` | `{ \"type\": \"event\", \"event\": \"spec_check_result\", \"folder_state\": \"...\", \"normalized_topic\": \"...\", \"specPath\": \"...\", \"hostAnchor\": \"...\", \"timestamp\": \"...\" }` |\n| `spec_seed_created` | `{ \"type\": \"spec_mutation\", \"event\": \"spec_seed_created\", \"folder_state\": \"spec-just-created-by-this-run\", \"anchors_touched\": [\"Scope\", \"Requirements\"], \"diff_summary\": \"...\", \"seed_markers\": [\"DR-SEED:SCOPE\", \"DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS\"], \"timestamp\": \"...\" }` |\n| `spec_preinit_context_added` | `{ \"type\": \"spec_mutation\", \"event\": \"spec_preinit_context_added\", \"folder_state\": \"spec-present\", \"anchors_touched\": [\"Open Questions\", \"Research Context\"], \"diff_summary\": \"...\", \"normalized_topic\": \"...\", \"timestamp\": \"...\" }` |\n| `spec_preinit_context_deduped` | `{ \"type\": \"spec_mutation\", \"event\": \"spec_preinit_context_deduped\", \"folder_state\": \"spec-present\", \"anchors_touched\": [\"Open Questions\"], \"diff_summary\": \"...\", \"normalized_topic\": \"...\", \"specPath\": \"...\", \"timestamp\": \"...\" }` |\n| `spec_mutation` | `{ \"type\": \"spec_mutation\", \"event\": \"spec_mutation\", \"phase\": \"post-synthesis\", \"anchors_touched\": [\"<chosen host anchor>\"], \"diff_summary\": \"...\", \"generatedFence\": \"deep-research/spec-findings\", \"timestamp\": \"...\" }` |\n| `spec_mutation_conflict` | `{ \"type\": \"spec_mutation\", \"event\": \"spec_mutation_conflict\", \"folder_state\": \"conflict-detected\", \"reason\": \"...\", \"hostAnchor\": \"...\", \"specPath\": \"...\", \"generatedFence\": \"deep-research/spec-findings\", \"conflictKind\": \"...\", \"timestamp\": \"...\" }` |\n| `spec_synthesis_deferred` | `{ \"type\": \"spec_mutation\", \"event\": \"spec_synthesis_deferred\", \"reason\": \"...\", \"generatedFence\": \"deep-research/spec-findings\", \"timestamp\": \"...\" }` |\n\n### Audit Requirements\n- Every real `spec.md` mutation records `anchors_touched` and `diff_summary`.\n- The protocol never relies on prose logs alone.\n- Conflict exits and deferred write-back are auditable from JSONL without opening the mutated file.\n\n---\n\n## 7. IDEMPOTENCY RULES\n\n### Topic Dedupe\n- Lowercase, strip punctuation, collapse whitespace, and trim before comparing research topics.\n- Re-running with the same `normalized_topic` must no-op instead of appending another pre-init note.\n- The shared intake contract (`.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/intake_contract.md` §5-§6) applies the same normalization before writing `feature_description` into `spec.md` Problem Statement or Purpose; equivalent normalized phrases emit `intake_topic_deduped` instead of overwriting the existing prose.\n\n### Marker-Based Placeholder Detection\n- Seed behavior depends on deterministic `<!-- DR-SEED:... -->` markers, not fuzzy prose matching.\n- If the required seed markers already exist, treat the seed path as already satisfied.\n- The shared intake contract used by `/speckit:plan --intake-only`, `/speckit:plan`, and `/speckit:complete` classifies any retained DR seed marker as `placeholder-upgrade` and persists `resume_question_id` plus `reentry_reason` for REQ-011 re-entry.\n\n### Relation-Object Dedupe\n- Manual relationship arrays dedupe by `packet_id` within each relation type (`depends_on`, `related_to`, `supersedes`) before emitting `graph-metadata.json`.\n- Dedupe outcomes emit `relationship_deduped` with typed payload fields such as `dedupedCount` and `packetIds`.\n\n### Generated-Block Replacement\n- The generated findings block is matched by the exact marker pair:\n  - `<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: deep-research/spec-findings -->`\n  - `<!-- END GENERATED: deep-research/spec-findings -->`\n- Same host anchor plus same generated content resolves to a no-op.\n- If the existing generated block fails checksum validation or carries an explicit manual-edit marker, emit `spec_mutation_conflict` and halt instead of overwriting.\n\n### Cross-Command Compatibility\n- Relation objects shared with sibling intake flows dedupe by `packet_id`.\n- This protocol does not create manual relationship edges itself, but it must not reintroduce duplicate relation objects if that metadata is surfaced during a future delegated sync.\n\n---\n\n## 8. CONFLICT EXITS\n\nFail closed when any of the following is true:\n- The chosen host anchor is missing.\n- Duplicate DR seed markers are present.\n- Duplicate generated fence markers are present.\n- Human edits are detected inside the machine-owned generated block.\n- The generated block checksum drifts or an explicit manual-edit marker is present inside the existing fence.\n- Pre-init append intent conflicts with the semantic purpose of the host section.\n\n### Exit Behavior\n1. Emit `spec_mutation_conflict`.\n2. Keep existing `spec.md` content unchanged.\n3. Stop before LOOP or before SAVE, depending on the phase.\n4. Surface the exact blocking reason to the operator.\n\nNo silent merge, overwrite, or best-effort repair is allowed on a conflict path.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":231,"totalLines":231,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md","time":{"start":1781420784880,"end":1781420784884}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09bae70769a22d2a016a2e52f0c99081918d16bdd49a4619ca"}},"id":"prt_ec4f3fcef001OkivwXbA7mA9EZ","sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","messageID":"msg_ec4f3e19d0013AT9kgTZ1SOMKZ"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781420784887,"sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_lqx8xBYwn9lllPkhGlhJAeYK","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-research-loop_auto.yaml","offset":861,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-research-loop_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n861:             --loop-type research \\\n862:             --artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n863:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n864:         wait_for_completion: true\n865: \n866:       step_hydrate_summary_metrics:\n867:         action: \"Hydrate summary metrics before synthesis\"\n868:         read:\n869:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n870:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n871:           - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n872:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n873:         extract:\n874:           - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n875:           - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n876:           - current_segment: \"Latest segment_start event segment, else 1\"\n877:           - last_focus: \"Extract focus from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n878:           - ratio_prev: \"Extract newInfoRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n879:           - ratio_latest: \"Extract newInfoRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n880:           - remaining_questions: \"Count unchecked items in 'Key Questions'\"\n881:           - remaining_questions_list: \"List unchecked key questions from strategy.md\"\n882:           - answered_count: \"Count answered questions from strategy.md\"\n883:           - total_questions: \"Count total questions tracked in strategy.md\"\n884:           - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'run N: focus (ratio)'\"\n885:           - reason: \"Use the latest synthesis/recovery stop reason if present, else the frozen default 'converged'. (Must be a member of the STOP_REASONS enum: converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused.)\"\n886: \n887:       step_read_all_iterations:\n888:         action: \"Read all iteration files and strategy\"\n889:         read_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_dir}/iteration-*.md\"\n890:         read_also: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n891: \n892:       step_emit_resource_map:\n893:         action: \"Emit {state_paths.resource_map_output} from converged research deltas unless config.resource_map.emit is false\"\n894:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder} --emit-resource-map\"\n895:         read:\n896:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n897:           - \"{state_paths.delta_dir}/iter-*.jsonl\"\n898:         write:\n899:           - \"{state_paths.resource_map_output}\"\n900:         guarantee: \"Reducer skips cleanly when config.resource_map.emit == false and writes a deterministic resource-map when enabled.\"\n901: \n902:       step_compile_research:\n903:         action: \"Compile or finalize research/research.md\"\n904:         instructions: |\n905:           If research/research.md exists (progressive synthesis was active):\n906:             1. Read current research/research.md\n907:             2. Consolidate and deduplicate findings across all iterations\n908:             3. Fill any empty sections with findings from iteration files\n909:             4. Remove redundancy while preserving all unique findings\n910:             5. Add convergence report as appendix\n911:             6. If `resource_map_present` is true, cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in References; otherwise omit any placeholder map citation\n912: \n913:           If research/research.md does not exist:\n914:             1. Create research/research.md following 17-section template\n915:             2. Populate sections from iteration files\n916:             3. Add citations from original sources\n917:             4. Note unanswered questions in Open Questions section\n918:             5. If `resource_map_present` is true, cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in References; otherwise omit any placeholder map citation\n919:           Preserve machine-owned markers so the reducer-owned registry, dashboard, and strategy anchors can be refreshed on re-run without mutating prior synthesis. (Note: `completed-continue` lineage branch is deferred — see `deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branch Contract`.)\n920:         output: \"{state_paths.research_output}\"\n921: \n922:       step_convergence_report:\n923:         action: \"Generate and append convergence report\"\n924:         report: |\n925:           ## Convergence Report\n926:           - Stop reason: {reason}\n927:           - Total iterations: {iteration_count}\n928:           - Questions answered: {answered_count} / {total_questions}\n929:           - Remaining questions: {remaining_questions}\n930:           - Last 3 iteration summaries: {last_3_summaries}\n931:           - Convergence threshold: {convergence_threshold}\n932:           - Segment transitions, wave scores, and checkpoint metrics are experimental and omitted from the live report.\n933:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"synthesis_complete\",\"totalIterations\":{iteration_count},\"answeredCount\":{answered_count},\"totalQuestions\":{total_questions},\"stopReason\":\"{reason}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n934: \n935:       step_writeback_spec_findings:\n936:         action: \"Write or replace the bounded generated findings block in spec.md before config completion\"\n937:         edit: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n938:         host_anchor: \"Use the chosen host anchor required by spec_check_protocol\"\n939:         generated_fence_begin: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: deep-research/spec-findings -->\"\n940:         generated_fence_end: \"<!-- END GENERATED: deep-research/spec-findings -->\"\n941:         fail_closed_conflict_check:\n942:           if_existing_generated_fence_present:\n943:             detect_manual_edits: \"Use generated checksum metadata or an explicit MANUAL-EDIT marker inside the existing fence to detect human edits before overwrite.\"\n944:             on_manual_edit_conflict:\n945:               append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_mutation_conflict\",\"folder_state\":\"conflict-detected\",\"reason\":\"Manual edits detected inside existing generated findings fence.\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"generatedFence\":\"deep-research/spec-findings\",\"conflictKind\":\"generated-fence-manual-edit\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n946:               halt: true\n947:         instructions:\n948:           - \"Read `{state_paths.research_output}` as the canonical synthesis source.\"\n949:           - \"Replace exactly one generated findings block under the chosen host anchor.\"\n950:           - \"Fail closed if the host anchor is missing, duplicate markers exist, or human edits are detected inside the generated block.\"\n951:           - \"Do not overwrite a generated block that fails checksum validation or carries an explicit MANUAL-EDIT marker.\"\n952:           - \"Emit `spec_synthesis_deferred` instead of partial output when synthesis cannot safely write back.\"\n953:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_mutation\",\"phase\":\"post-synthesis\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"<chosen host anchor>\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Replaced generated deep-research findings fence from research/research.md.\",\"generatedFence\":\"deep-research/spec-findings\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n954: \n955:       step_validate_post_synthesis_spec_doc:\n956:         action: \"Run targeted strict validation after deep-research writes back into spec.md\"\n957:         command: \"SPECKIT_RULES=FRONTMATTER_VALID,LEVEL_DECLARED,TEMPLATE_SOURCE,TEMPLATE_HEADERS,PLACEHOLDER_FILLED,SECTIONS_PRESENT,ANCHORS_VALID,SPEC_DOC_INTEGRITY,TOC_POLICY bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh {spec_folder} --strict\"\n958:         note: \"Fail closed before completion if the deep-research spec.md sync breaks the authored-spec structural contract. This targeted check uses the fast Node validation orchestrator.\"\n959: \n960:       step_update_config_status:\n961:         action: \"Mark config as complete\"\n962:         edit: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n963:         set_field: { status: \"complete\" }\n964: \n965:       step_stage_artifact_dir:\n966:         action: \"Stage all skill-owned artifacts under artifact_dir for the operator's next git commit\"\n967:         command: \"git add {state_paths.packet_dir}\"\n968:         note: \"Skill-owned contract fix (028): without this stage step, operators who do `git add research-report.md` lose the iteration trail (iterations/, deltas/, state.jsonl, strategy, etc.). Staging the whole artifact_dir keeps the audit trail intact. Operators retain commit authority and can `git restore --staged {path}` to unstage anything before commit. Failure is non-fatal — log warning and continue.\"\n969:         on_fail: \"Log warning. Do not block synthesis. The artifact_dir may be outside a git repo (e.g., temp test fixture) which is a valid case.\"\n970: \n971:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n972:   # PHASE 4: SAVE\n973:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n974:   phase_save:\n975:     purpose: Preserve research context to memory system\n976:     steps:\n977: \n978:       step_compose_save_payload:\n979:         action: \"Compose the structured JSON payload consumed by generate-context.js\"\n980:         output: \"/tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json\"\n981:         requirements:\n982:           - \"Write this file before invoking generate-context.js; the loader fails closed if the explicit JSON file is absent.\"\n983:           - \"Include `specFolder`, a concise `sessionSummary`, curated `observations`, `recent_context`, `toolCalls`, and `exchanges` from the completed research loop.\"\n984:           - \"Use a session-scoped temp filename; do not use the retired shared `/tmp/save-context-data.json` path.\"\n985:         example_payload: |\n986:           {\n987:             \"specFolder\": \"{spec_folder}\",\n988:             \"sessionSummary\": \"Deep research completed; see research/research.md for synthesized findings.\",\n989:             \"observations\": [\"Summarize the final research conclusions and evidence.\"],\n990:             \"recent_context\": [\"Point to the generated research artifacts and next action.\"],\n991:             \"exchanges\": [],\n992:             \"toolCalls\": []\n993:           }\n994: \n995:       step_generate_context:\n996:         action: \"Route continuity content into the correct canonical spec document via generate-context.js\"\n997:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js /tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json {spec_folder}\"\n998:         critical_rule: \"NEVER manually author files under retired memory/ paths (the runtime rejects them); use generate-context.js so the save routes into decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md\"\n999: \n1000:       step_index_memory:\n1001:         action: \"Index the routed canonical spec document with memory_save when immediate MCP visibility is required\"\n1002:         mcp_tool: memory_save\n1003:         invocation: 'memory_save({ filePath: \"[routed-canonical-spec-doc-path]\" })'\n1004:         note: \"Use the actual canonical spec-doc path returned by generate-context.js (decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md); memory_index_scan remains the bulk fallback\"\n1005: \n1006:       step_verify_save:\n1007:         action: \"Verify canonical save routed content into the correct spec document\"\n1008:         check: \"Does {spec_folder}/implementation-summary.md, {spec_folder}/decision-record.md, or {spec_folder}/handover.md carry the new continuity update?\"\n1009:         on_fail: \"Log warning but do not block completion\"\n1010: \n1011:       step_release_lock:\n1012:         action: \"Release the advisory lock after save, skip-save, or cancellation cleanup has resolved\"\n1013:         command: \"Close or unlock {state_paths.lock_file} using advisory semantics only.\"\n1014:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"lock_released\",\"path\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"releasePhase\":\"save\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n1015: \n1016:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1017:   # COMPLETION\n1018:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1019:   completion:\n1020:     message: |\n1021:       Deep research complete.\n1022:       Iterations: {iteration_count} | Stop reason: {reason}\n1023:       Questions answered: {answered_count}/{total_questions}\n1024: \n1025:       Artifacts:\n1026:         - research/research.md (compiled from {iteration_count} iterations)\n1027:         - {iteration_count} iteration files in research/\n1028:         - State files: config.json, state.jsonl, strategy.md, deep-research-findings-registry.json, dashboard.md\n1029:         - Memory context saved\n1030: \n1031:       STATUS=OK PATH={spec_folder}\n1032:     next_steps:\n1033:       - \"/speckit:plan [feature-description]\"\n1034:       - \"/deep:start-research-loop [new-topic] (for related deep research)\"\n1035:       - \"/memory:save {spec_folder} (refresh canonical continuity before the next session)\"\n1036: \n1037: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1038: # ERROR RECOVERY\n1039: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1040: error_recovery:\n1041:   agent_dispatch_timeout: \"Retry once with reduced scope (fewer research actions). If second timeout, mark as 'timeout' and continue.\"\n1042:   state_file_missing: \"If JSONL missing during loop, reconstruct from iteration files. If strategy missing, create minimal version.\"\n1043:   consecutive_failures: \"After 3 consecutive errors, halt loop and enter synthesis with partial findings.\"\n1044:   memory_save_failure: \"Preserve the research/ packet as backup. Log warning.\"\n1045: \n1046: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1047: # RULES\n1048: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1049: rules:\n1050:   ALWAYS:\n1051:     - follow_workflow_phases_in_order\n1052:     - dispatch_deep_research_agent_per_iteration\n1053:     - check_convergence_before_each_iteration\n1054:     - write_all_state_to_files\n1055:     - save_memory_context_after_synthesis\n1056:     - respect_max_iterations_cap\n1057:   NEVER:\n1058:     - skip_convergence_check\n1059:     - dispatch_non_leaf_agents\n1060:     - hold_iteration_findings_in_memory_only\n1061:     - modify_config_after_initialization\n1062:     - overwrite_jsonl_state_log\n1063:     - proceed_without_state_file_verification\n1064: \n1065: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1066: # REFERENCE-ONLY APPENDIX\n1067: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1068: reference_only_appendix:\n1069:   checkpoint_commit:\n1070:     note: \"Checkpoint commits are intentionally excluded from workflow.steps.\"\n1071:     commands:\n1072:       - \"git add {state_paths.iteration_pattern} {state_paths.state_log} {state_paths.strategy} {state_paths.research_output}\"\n1073:       - 'git commit -m \"chore(deep-research): iteration {NNN} complete\"'\n1074:   wave_orchestration:\n1075:     note: \"Wave execution is intentionally excluded from workflow.steps.\"\n1076:     summary:\n1077:       - \"Check whether 3+ independent unanswered questions justify a wave.\"\n1078:       - \"Dispatch up to 3 parallel agents on distinct questions.\"\n1079:       - \"Score wave results by median newInfoRatio and promote top branches.\"\n\n(End of file - total 1079 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"            --loop-type research \\\n            --artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        wait_for_completion: true\n\n      step_hydrate_summary_metrics:\n        action: \"Hydrate summary metrics before synthesis\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        extract:\n          - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n          - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n          - current_segment: \"Latest segment_start event segment, else 1\"\n          - last_focus: \"Extract focus from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n          - ratio_prev: \"Extract newInfoRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - ratio_latest: \"Extract newInfoRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - remaining_questions: \"Count unchecked items in 'Key Questions'\"","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-research-loop_auto.yaml","text":"            --loop-type research \\\n            --artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        wait_for_completion: true\n\n      step_hydrate_summary_metrics:\n        action: \"Hydrate summary metrics before synthesis\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        extract:\n          - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n          - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n          - current_segment: \"Latest segment_start event segment, else 1\"\n          - last_focus: \"Extract focus from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n          - ratio_prev: \"Extract newInfoRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - ratio_latest: \"Extract newInfoRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - remaining_questions: \"Count unchecked items in 'Key Questions'\"\n          - remaining_questions_list: \"List unchecked key questions from strategy.md\"\n          - answered_count: \"Count answered questions from strategy.md\"\n          - total_questions: \"Count total questions tracked in strategy.md\"\n          - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'run N: focus (ratio)'\"\n          - reason: \"Use the latest synthesis/recovery stop reason if present, else the frozen default 'converged'. (Must be a member of the STOP_REASONS enum: converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused.)\"\n\n      step_read_all_iterations:\n        action: \"Read all iteration files and strategy\"\n        read_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_dir}/iteration-*.md\"\n        read_also: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n\n      step_emit_resource_map:\n        action: \"Emit {state_paths.resource_map_output} from converged research deltas unless config.resource_map.emit is false\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder} --emit-resource-map\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.delta_dir}/iter-*.jsonl\"\n        write:\n          - \"{state_paths.resource_map_output}\"\n        guarantee: \"Reducer skips cleanly when config.resource_map.emit == false and writes a deterministic resource-map when enabled.\"\n\n      step_compile_research:\n        action: \"Compile or finalize research/research.md\"\n        instructions: |\n          If research/research.md exists (progressive synthesis was active):\n            1. Read current research/research.md\n            2. Consolidate and deduplicate findings across all iterations\n            3. Fill any empty sections with findings from iteration files\n            4. Remove redundancy while preserving all unique findings\n            5. Add convergence report as appendix\n            6. If `resource_map_present` is true, cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in References; otherwise omit any placeholder map citation\n\n          If research/research.md does not exist:\n            1. Create research/research.md following 17-section template\n            2. Populate sections from iteration files\n            3. Add citations from original sources\n            4. Note unanswered questions in Open Questions section\n            5. If `resource_map_present` is true, cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in References; otherwise omit any placeholder map citation\n          Preserve machine-owned markers so the reducer-owned registry, dashboard, and strategy anchors can be refreshed on re-run without mutating prior synthesis. (Note: `completed-continue` lineage branch is deferred — see `deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branch Contract`.)\n        output: \"{state_paths.research_output}\"\n\n      step_convergence_report:\n        action: \"Generate and append convergence report\"\n        report: |\n          ## Convergence Report\n          - Stop reason: {reason}\n          - Total iterations: {iteration_count}\n          - Questions answered: {answered_count} / {total_questions}\n          - Remaining questions: {remaining_questions}\n          - Last 3 iteration summaries: {last_3_summaries}\n          - Convergence threshold: {convergence_threshold}\n          - Segment transitions, wave scores, and checkpoint metrics are experimental and omitted from the live report.\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"synthesis_complete\",\"totalIterations\":{iteration_count},\"answeredCount\":{answered_count},\"totalQuestions\":{total_questions},\"stopReason\":\"{reason}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n      step_writeback_spec_findings:\n        action: \"Write or replace the bounded generated findings block in spec.md before config completion\"\n        edit: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n        host_anchor: \"Use the chosen host anchor required by spec_check_protocol\"\n        generated_fence_begin: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: deep-research/spec-findings -->\"\n        generated_fence_end: \"<!-- END GENERATED: deep-research/spec-findings -->\"\n        fail_closed_conflict_check:\n          if_existing_generated_fence_present:\n            detect_manual_edits: \"Use generated checksum metadata or an explicit MANUAL-EDIT marker inside the existing fence to detect human edits before overwrite.\"\n            on_manual_edit_conflict:\n              append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_mutation_conflict\",\"folder_state\":\"conflict-detected\",\"reason\":\"Manual edits detected inside existing generated findings fence.\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"generatedFence\":\"deep-research/spec-findings\",\"conflictKind\":\"generated-fence-manual-edit\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n              halt: true\n        instructions:\n          - \"Read `{state_paths.research_output}` as the canonical synthesis source.\"\n          - \"Replace exactly one generated findings block under the chosen host anchor.\"\n          - \"Fail closed if the host anchor is missing, duplicate markers exist, or human edits are detected inside the generated block.\"\n          - \"Do not overwrite a generated block that fails checksum validation or carries an explicit MANUAL-EDIT marker.\"\n          - \"Emit `spec_synthesis_deferred` instead of partial output when synthesis cannot safely write back.\"\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_mutation\",\"phase\":\"post-synthesis\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"<chosen host anchor>\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Replaced generated deep-research findings fence from research/research.md.\",\"generatedFence\":\"deep-research/spec-findings\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n      step_validate_post_synthesis_spec_doc:\n        action: \"Run targeted strict validation after deep-research writes back into spec.md\"\n        command: \"SPECKIT_RULES=FRONTMATTER_VALID,LEVEL_DECLARED,TEMPLATE_SOURCE,TEMPLATE_HEADERS,PLACEHOLDER_FILLED,SECTIONS_PRESENT,ANCHORS_VALID,SPEC_DOC_INTEGRITY,TOC_POLICY bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh {spec_folder} --strict\"\n        note: \"Fail closed before completion if the deep-research spec.md sync breaks the authored-spec structural contract. This targeted check uses the fast Node validation orchestrator.\"\n\n      step_update_config_status:\n        action: \"Mark config as complete\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n        set_field: { status: \"complete\" }\n\n      step_stage_artifact_dir:\n        action: \"Stage all skill-owned artifacts under artifact_dir for the operator's next git commit\"\n        command: \"git add {state_paths.packet_dir}\"\n        note: \"Skill-owned contract fix (028): without this stage step, operators who do `git add research-report.md` lose the iteration trail (iterations/, deltas/, state.jsonl, strategy, etc.). Staging the whole artifact_dir keeps the audit trail intact. Operators retain commit authority and can `git restore --staged {path}` to unstage anything before commit. Failure is non-fatal — log warning and continue.\"\n        on_fail: \"Log warning. Do not block synthesis. The artifact_dir may be outside a git repo (e.g., temp test fixture) which is a valid case.\"\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 4: SAVE\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_save:\n    purpose: Preserve research context to memory system\n    steps:\n\n      step_compose_save_payload:\n        action: \"Compose the structured JSON payload consumed by generate-context.js\"\n        output: \"/tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json\"\n        requirements:\n          - \"Write this file before invoking generate-context.js; the loader fails closed if the explicit JSON file is absent.\"\n          - \"Include `specFolder`, a concise `sessionSummary`, curated `observations`, `recent_context`, `toolCalls`, and `exchanges` from the completed research loop.\"\n          - \"Use a session-scoped temp filename; do not use the retired shared `/tmp/save-context-data.json` path.\"\n        example_payload: |\n          {\n            \"specFolder\": \"{spec_folder}\",\n            \"sessionSummary\": \"Deep research completed; see research/research.md for synthesized findings.\",\n            \"observations\": [\"Summarize the final research conclusions and evidence.\"],\n            \"recent_context\": [\"Point to the generated research artifacts and next action.\"],\n            \"exchanges\": [],\n            \"toolCalls\": []\n          }\n\n      step_generate_context:\n        action: \"Route continuity content into the correct canonical spec document via generate-context.js\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js /tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json {spec_folder}\"\n        critical_rule: \"NEVER manually author files under retired memory/ paths (the runtime rejects them); use generate-context.js so the save routes into decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md\"\n\n      step_index_memory:\n        action: \"Index the routed canonical spec document with memory_save when immediate MCP visibility is required\"\n        mcp_tool: memory_save\n        invocation: 'memory_save({ filePath: \"[routed-canonical-spec-doc-path]\" })'\n        note: \"Use the actual canonical spec-doc path returned by generate-context.js (decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md); memory_index_scan remains the bulk fallback\"\n\n      step_verify_save:\n        action: \"Verify canonical save routed content into the correct spec document\"\n        check: \"Does {spec_folder}/implementation-summary.md, {spec_folder}/decision-record.md, or {spec_folder}/handover.md carry the new continuity update?\"\n        on_fail: \"Log warning but do not block completion\"\n\n      step_release_lock:\n        action: \"Release the advisory lock after save, skip-save, or cancellation cleanup has resolved\"\n        command: \"Close or unlock {state_paths.lock_file} using advisory semantics only.\"\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"lock_released\",\"path\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"releasePhase\":\"save\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # COMPLETION\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  completion:\n    message: |\n      Deep research complete.\n      Iterations: {iteration_count} | Stop reason: {reason}\n      Questions answered: {answered_count}/{total_questions}\n\n      Artifacts:\n        - research/research.md (compiled from {iteration_count} iterations)\n        - {iteration_count} iteration files in research/\n        - State files: config.json, state.jsonl, strategy.md, deep-research-findings-registry.json, dashboard.md\n        - Memory context saved\n\n      STATUS=OK PATH={spec_folder}\n    next_steps:\n      - \"/speckit:plan [feature-description]\"\n      - \"/deep:start-research-loop [new-topic] (for related deep research)\"\n      - \"/memory:save {spec_folder} (refresh canonical continuity before the next session)\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# ERROR RECOVERY\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nerror_recovery:\n  agent_dispatch_timeout: \"Retry once with reduced scope (fewer research actions). If second timeout, mark as 'timeout' and continue.\"\n  state_file_missing: \"If JSONL missing during loop, reconstruct from iteration files. If strategy missing, create minimal version.\"\n  consecutive_failures: \"After 3 consecutive errors, halt loop and enter synthesis with partial findings.\"\n  memory_save_failure: \"Preserve the research/ packet as backup. Log warning.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# RULES\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrules:\n  ALWAYS:\n    - follow_workflow_phases_in_order\n    - dispatch_deep_research_agent_per_iteration\n    - check_convergence_before_each_iteration\n    - write_all_state_to_files\n    - save_memory_context_after_synthesis\n    - respect_max_iterations_cap\n  NEVER:\n    - skip_convergence_check\n    - dispatch_non_leaf_agents\n    - hold_iteration_findings_in_memory_only\n    - modify_config_after_initialization\n    - overwrite_jsonl_state_log\n    - proceed_without_state_file_verification\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# REFERENCE-ONLY APPENDIX\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nreference_only_appendix:\n  checkpoint_commit:\n    note: \"Checkpoint commits are intentionally excluded from workflow.steps.\"\n    commands:\n      - \"git add {state_paths.iteration_pattern} {state_paths.state_log} {state_paths.strategy} {state_paths.research_output}\"\n      - 'git commit -m \"chore(deep-research): iteration {NNN} complete\"'\n  wave_orchestration:\n    note: \"Wave execution is intentionally excluded from workflow.steps.\"\n    summary:\n      - \"Check whether 3+ independent unanswered questions justify a wave.\"\n      - \"Dispatch up to 3 parallel agents on distinct questions.\"\n      - \"Score wave results by median newInfoRatio and promote top branches.\"","lineStart":861,"lineEnd":1079,"totalLines":1079,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-research-loop_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1781420784878,"end":1781420784885}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09bae70769a22d2a016a2e52f0c9888191a69d660b86020b98"}},"id":"prt_ec4f3fcc30015D3gKSwE1PQsxO","sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","messageID":"msg_ec4f3e19d0013AT9kgTZ1SOMKZ"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781420784913,"sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_a8VcKW4fCvKGEILArct6SyIk","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/references/state/state_reducer_registry.md","offset":1,"limit":320},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/references/state/state_reducer_registry.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research Reducer And Registry Reference\n3: description: Reducer ownership, findings registry schema, validation, fault tolerance, and reconstruction rules.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"research reducer registry\"\n6:   - \"research findings registry\"\n7:   - \"reducer ownership contract\"\n8:   - \"research registry fingerprint\"\n9:   - \"reducer fault tolerance\"\n10:   - \"research dashboard derivation\"\n11: importance_tier: normal\n12: contextType: implementation\n13: ---\n14: \n15: # Deep Research Reducer And Registry Reference\n16: \n17: The reducer turns append-only iteration state into synchronized strategy, registry, dashboard, and synthesis metadata. It is the source of truth for derived packet state.\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n22: \n23: ### Purpose\n24: \n25: Define reducer ownership, findings registry shape, validation behavior, fault tolerance, file protection, dashboard derivation, and legacy aliases.\n26: \n27: ### When to Use\n28: \n29: Load this reference when rebuilding derived state, validating registry/dashboard outputs, or deciding whether a file is agent-owned or reducer-owned.\n30: \n31: ### Core Principle\n32: \n33: The reducer owns derived state. Manual edits to reducer-managed outputs are temporary and may be overwritten.\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ## 2. REDUCER CONTRACT\n38: \n39: The workflow reducer:\n40: \n41: - reads `deep-research-state.jsonl`, per-iteration deltas, strategy, and iteration markdown;\n42: - validates required iteration artifacts;\n43: - updates machine-owned strategy sections;\n44: - regenerates the findings registry;\n45: - regenerates the dashboard;\n46: - records convergence and blocked-stop summaries.\n47: \n48: It must fail closed before writing derived files when JSONL corruption is detected in strict mode.\n49: \n50: ---\n51: \n52: ## 3. FINDINGS REGISTRY\n53: \n54: The canonical registry stores open/resolved questions, findings, ruled-out directions, convergence state, and blocked-stop history.\n55: \n56: ```json\n57: {\n58:   \"openQuestions\": [],\n59:   \"resolvedQuestions\": [],\n60:   \"keyFindings\": [],\n61:   \"ruledOutDirections\": [],\n62:   \"coverageBySources\": {},\n63:   \"convergenceScore\": 0.42,\n64:   \"blockedStopHistory\": [],\n65:   \"graphConvergenceScore\": null,\n66:   \"graphDecision\": null,\n67:   \"graphBlockers\": [],\n68:   \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n69: }\n70: ```\n71: \n72: The currently documented live registry name is `deep-research-findings-registry.json` in command state paths, with `findings-registry.json` still appearing in older docs and packet examples. New docs should prefer the command state path and mention the older name only when explaining compatibility.\n73: \n74: ---\n75: \n76: ## 4. VALIDATION RULES\n77: \n78: Blocking validation:\n79: \n80: - config, state log, and strategy exist before a resume;\n81: - every dispatched iteration produces a non-empty iteration markdown file;\n82: - every dispatched iteration appends a JSONL delta record with required fields;\n83: - JSONL records parse in strict mode;\n84: - reducer-owned outputs refresh after iteration evaluation;\n85: - convergence STOP candidates record gate evidence.\n86: \n87: Post-dispatch failure codes include:\n88: \n89: | Code | Meaning |\n90: |------|---------|\n91: | `iteration_file_missing` | Expected iteration markdown file was not created |\n92: | `iteration_file_empty` | Iteration markdown exists but is empty |\n93: | `jsonl_not_appended` | JSONL state did not receive the iteration record |\n94: | `jsonl_missing_fields` | Required JSONL fields are absent |\n95: | `jsonl_parse_error` | JSONL line is malformed |\n96: \n97: Three consecutive failures route to stuck recovery or escalation.\n98: \n99: ---\n100: \n101: ## 5. FAULT TOLERANCE\n102: \n103: Fault-tolerant reads may skip malformed JSONL lines only in lenient recovery mode. Strict mode stops before derived writes.\n104: \n105: Safe recovery order:\n106: \n107: 1. Preserve the corrupted state file.\n108: 2. Read valid JSONL records.\n109: 3. Reconstruct missing iteration summaries from `iterations/iteration-NNN.md`.\n110: 4. Append explicit reconstructed records.\n111: 5. Regenerate registry and dashboard.\n112: 6. Record the recovery in JSONL.\n113: \n114: Example reconstructed record:\n115: \n116: ```json\n117: {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":3,\"status\":\"reconstructed\",\"focus\":\"extracted focus\",\"findingsCount\":0,\"newInfoRatio\":0.0}\n118: ```\n119: \n120: ---\n121: \n122: ## 6. FILE PROTECTION MAP\n123: \n124: The config may include:\n125: \n126: ```json\n127: {\n128:   \"fileProtection\": {\n129:     \"deep-research-config.json\": \"immutable\",\n130:     \"deep-research-state.jsonl\": \"append-only\",\n131:     \"deep-research-strategy.md\": \"mutable\",\n132:     \"deep-research-dashboard.md\": \"auto-generated\",\n133:     \"deep-research-findings-registry.json\": \"auto-generated\",\n134:     \"iteration-*.md\": \"write-once\",\n135:     \"research/research.md\": \"mutable\"\n136:   }\n137: }\n138: ```\n139: \n140: Protection is a workflow contract. It documents ownership and supports validation; it is not a substitute for command-level checks.\n141: \n142: ---\n143: \n144: ## 7. DASHBOARD DERIVATION\n145: \n146: Dashboard values are derived from raw state:\n147: \n148: | Dashboard Field | Source |\n149: |-----------------|--------|\n150: | iteration count | JSONL iteration records |\n151: | current status | latest lifecycle or synthesis event |\n152: | convergence trend | `convergenceSignals` |\n153: | blocked stops | registry `blockedStopHistory` |\n154: | graph convergence | registry graph fields |\n155: | next focus | strategy |\n156: \n157: `synthesis_complete` events are authoritative for terminal status when present.\n158: \n159: ---\n160: \n161: ## 8. LEGACY ALIASES\n162: \n163: The workflow may dual-read older names during migration windows, but new writes use canonical `deep-research-*` artifacts. Migration reads should append a migration event that records `legacyPath`, `canonicalPath`, and timestamp.\n\n(End of file - total 163 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Reducer And Registry Reference\ndescription: Reducer ownership, findings registry schema, validation, fault tolerance, and reconstruction rules.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research reducer registry\"\n  - \"research findings registry\"\n  - \"reducer ownership contract\"\n  - \"research registry fingerprint\"\n  - \"reducer fault tolerance\"\n  - \"research dashboard derivation\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\n---\n\n# Deep Research Reducer And Registry Reference\n\nThe reducer turns append-only iteration state into synchronized strategy, registry, dashboard, and synthesis metadata. It is the source of truth for derived packet state.\n\n---\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/references/state/state_reducer_registry.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Reducer And Registry Reference\ndescription: Reducer ownership, findings registry schema, validation, fault tolerance, and reconstruction rules.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research reducer registry\"\n  - \"research findings registry\"\n  - \"reducer ownership contract\"\n  - \"research registry fingerprint\"\n  - \"reducer fault tolerance\"\n  - \"research dashboard derivation\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\n---\n\n# Deep Research Reducer And Registry Reference\n\nThe reducer turns append-only iteration state into synchronized strategy, registry, dashboard, and synthesis metadata. It is the source of truth for derived packet state.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nDefine reducer ownership, findings registry shape, validation behavior, fault tolerance, file protection, dashboard derivation, and legacy aliases.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this reference when rebuilding derived state, validating registry/dashboard outputs, or deciding whether a file is agent-owned or reducer-owned.\n\n### Core Principle\n\nThe reducer owns derived state. Manual edits to reducer-managed outputs are temporary and may be overwritten.\n\n---\n\n## 2. REDUCER CONTRACT\n\nThe workflow reducer:\n\n- reads `deep-research-state.jsonl`, per-iteration deltas, strategy, and iteration markdown;\n- validates required iteration artifacts;\n- updates machine-owned strategy sections;\n- regenerates the findings registry;\n- regenerates the dashboard;\n- records convergence and blocked-stop summaries.\n\nIt must fail closed before writing derived files when JSONL corruption is detected in strict mode.\n\n---\n\n## 3. FINDINGS REGISTRY\n\nThe canonical registry stores open/resolved questions, findings, ruled-out directions, convergence state, and blocked-stop history.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"openQuestions\": [],\n  \"resolvedQuestions\": [],\n  \"keyFindings\": [],\n  \"ruledOutDirections\": [],\n  \"coverageBySources\": {},\n  \"convergenceScore\": 0.42,\n  \"blockedStopHistory\": [],\n  \"graphConvergenceScore\": null,\n  \"graphDecision\": null,\n  \"graphBlockers\": [],\n  \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nThe currently documented live registry name is `deep-research-findings-registry.json` in command state paths, with `findings-registry.json` still appearing in older docs and packet examples. New docs should prefer the command state path and mention the older name only when explaining compatibility.\n\n---\n\n## 4. VALIDATION RULES\n\nBlocking validation:\n\n- config, state log, and strategy exist before a resume;\n- every dispatched iteration produces a non-empty iteration markdown file;\n- every dispatched iteration appends a JSONL delta record with required fields;\n- JSONL records parse in strict mode;\n- reducer-owned outputs refresh after iteration evaluation;\n- convergence STOP candidates record gate evidence.\n\nPost-dispatch failure codes include:\n\n| Code | Meaning |\n|------|---------|\n| `iteration_file_missing` | Expected iteration markdown file was not created |\n| `iteration_file_empty` | Iteration markdown exists but is empty |\n| `jsonl_not_appended` | JSONL state did not receive the iteration record |\n| `jsonl_missing_fields` | Required JSONL fields are absent |\n| `jsonl_parse_error` | JSONL line is malformed |\n\nThree consecutive failures route to stuck recovery or escalation.\n\n---\n\n## 5. FAULT TOLERANCE\n\nFault-tolerant reads may skip malformed JSONL lines only in lenient recovery mode. Strict mode stops before derived writes.\n\nSafe recovery order:\n\n1. Preserve the corrupted state file.\n2. Read valid JSONL records.\n3. Reconstruct missing iteration summaries from `iterations/iteration-NNN.md`.\n4. Append explicit reconstructed records.\n5. Regenerate registry and dashboard.\n6. Record the recovery in JSONL.\n\nExample reconstructed record:\n\n```json\n{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":3,\"status\":\"reconstructed\",\"focus\":\"extracted focus\",\"findingsCount\":0,\"newInfoRatio\":0.0}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. FILE PROTECTION MAP\n\nThe config may include:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"fileProtection\": {\n    \"deep-research-config.json\": \"immutable\",\n    \"deep-research-state.jsonl\": \"append-only\",\n    \"deep-research-strategy.md\": \"mutable\",\n    \"deep-research-dashboard.md\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \"deep-research-findings-registry.json\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \"iteration-*.md\": \"write-once\",\n    \"research/research.md\": \"mutable\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\nProtection is a workflow contract. It documents ownership and supports validation; it is not a substitute for command-level checks.\n\n---\n\n## 7. DASHBOARD DERIVATION\n\nDashboard values are derived from raw state:\n\n| Dashboard Field | Source |\n|-----------------|--------|\n| iteration count | JSONL iteration records |\n| current status | latest lifecycle or synthesis event |\n| convergence trend | `convergenceSignals` |\n| blocked stops | registry `blockedStopHistory` |\n| graph convergence | registry graph fields |\n| next focus | strategy |\n\n`synthesis_complete` events are authoritative for terminal status when present.\n\n---\n\n## 8. LEGACY ALIASES\n\nThe workflow may dual-read older names during migration windows, but new writes use canonical `deep-research-*` artifacts. Migration reads should append a migration event that records `legacyPath`, `canonicalPath`, and timestamp.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":163,"totalLines":163,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-research/references/state/state_reducer_registry.md","time":{"start":1781420784905,"end":1781420784908}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09bae70769a22d2a016a2e52f0c9988191abbcc2a2059b0888"}},"id":"prt_ec4f3fcf1001PJpjq0KhXNr3Qs","sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","messageID":"msg_ec4f3e19d0013AT9kgTZ1SOMKZ"}}
