{"type":"text","timestamp":1781420871564,"sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","part":{"id":"prt_ec4f54f170015zUS2TgaZVndkA","messageID":"msg_ec4f53d92001t89jloGpGP7SCD","sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","type":"text","text":"Local constraints are clear: `sk-interface-design` owns judgment and anti-default critique; `mcp-magicpath` owns CLI/canvas operations and already delegates aesthetics back to the design skill. The 005 baseline already covered context snapshots, fidelity loops, and handoff manifests, so this lineage will focus on net-new competitor patterns.","time":{"start":1781420871447,"end":1781420871562},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_066767556685bc14016a2e5347697481919f622bf33deb7fda","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1781420884135,"sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","part":{"id":"prt_ec4f573f80010oSoRcrZPW46js","messageID":"msg_ec4f53d92001t89jloGpGP7SCD","sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","type":"text","text":"I’m moving into the evidence-gathering loop: each iteration will focus on one competitor cluster, then I’ll write the iteration markdown, JSONL, deltas, dashboard, resource map, and lineage synthesis under `gpt55fast`.","time":{"start":1781420880888,"end":1781420884134},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_066767556685bc14016a2e5350dc888191a6371d91ccf8349b","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781420884705,"sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"webfetch","callID":"call_wLqGHLGWZUcwjkXH9G9neaN8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"url":"https://vercel.com/docs/v0","format":"markdown","timeout":20},"output":"What is v0? | v0 Docs\n\n[Vercel](https://vercel.com/)Slash[](/docs/en)\n\n-   [Docs](/docs)\n-   [API](/docs/api)\n\nSearch...⌘KAsk AI\n\nAsk AI\n\n[](/docs)\n\nGetting Started\n\n[What is v0?](/docs)[Agentic features](/docs/agentic-features)[Sandbox](/docs/sandbox)[Vercel Integration](/docs/vercel-integration)[Quickstart](/docs/quickstart)[FAQs](/docs/faqs)\n\nPrompt\n\n[Text Prompting](/docs/text-prompting)[Screenshots and Files](/docs/screenshots)[Figma](/docs/figma)\n\nIterate\n\n[Code editing](/docs/code-editing)[Terminal commands](/docs/terminal-commands)[Design mode](/docs/design-mode)[Design systems](/docs/design-systems)[Images and videos](/docs/images-and-videos)[Versions](/docs/versions)\n\nIntegrate\n\n[AI models](/docs/ai-models)[Databases](/docs/databases)[Snowflake](/docs/snowflake)[External APIs](/docs/external-apis)[GitHub](/docs/github)[MCP Integrations](/docs/MCP)[Pre-installed Agents](/docs/pre-installed-agents)[Slack](/docs/slack)\n\nShip\n\n[Deployments](/docs/deployments)[Custom domain](/docs/custom-domains)[Sharing](/docs/sharing)[Templates](/docs/templates)\n\nManage\n\n[Account](/docs/account)[Enterprise](/docs/enterprise)[Instructions](/docs/instructions)[Folders](/docs/folders)[Projects](/docs/projects)[Pricing](/docs/pricing)[Teams](/docs/teams)[Security](/docs/security)\n\nGuides\n\n[Full-stack apps](/docs/full-stack-apps)[Prototyping](/docs/prototyping)[PRD design](/docs/prd-design)\n\nCompare\n\nEnglish\n\nOn this page\n\n# What is v0?\n\nv0 is an AI agent that helps anyone create real code and full-stack apps and agents.\n\nShip features, refine designs, update copy, and create live prototypes, all with a prompt. Deploy to production immediately, or open a pull request for review.\n\n## [What can you do with v0?](#what-can-you-do-with-v0)\n\n-   **Describe your idea** in your preferred language.\n-   **Create high-fidelity UIs** from your wireframes or mockups.\n-   **Connect to backend** to build rich, data driven applications.\n-   **Deploy with one click** to secure, scalable infrastructure powered by Vercel.\n-   **Automatically fix errors** in your code with intelligent diagnostics.\n\n[\n\nGetting Started\n\nQuickstart tutorial to create your first project.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n](/docs/quickstart)[\n\nPrompt Engineering\n\nBuild faster in v0 with effective prompting.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n](/docs/text-prompting)\n\n[\n\nFAQs\n\nFind commonly asked questions about v0.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n](/docs/faqs)[\n\nBlog\n\nStay up to date with new product features and announcements.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n](https://vercel.com/blog/category/v0)\n\n[\n\nWhy should I choose v0 instead of other tools?\n\n\n\n](/docs/faqs#why-should-i-choose-v0)\n\n## [Examples](#examples)\n\nYou can use v0 to build anything, from landing pages, dashboards, ecommerce stores, AI apps, to full-stack applications.\n\n-   [\n    \n    ![Dashboard – M.O.N.K.Y](/docs/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2F4nwqv0zkit3b9v6h.public.blob.vercel-storage.com%2Fexamples%2Fdashboard.png&w=3840&q=75)\n    \n    Dashboard – M.O.N.K.Y\n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    ](https://v0.app/templates/b7GDYVxuoGC)\n-   [\n    \n    ![Brillance SaaS Landing Page](/docs/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2F4nwqv0zkit3b9v6h.public.blob.vercel-storage.com%2Fexamples%2Flanding.png&w=3840&q=75)\n    \n    Brillance SaaS Landing Page\n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    ](https://v0.app/templates/zdiN8dHwaaT)\n-   [\n    \n    ![Shopify Ecommerce Template](/docs/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2F4nwqv0zkit3b9v6h.public.blob.vercel-storage.com%2Fexamples%2Fecoommerce.png&w=3840&q=75)\n    \n    Shopify Ecommerce Template\n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    ](https://v0.app/templates/XmzC9oi7g4m)\n-   [\n    \n    ![Nano Banana Pro Playground](/docs/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2F4nwqv0zkit3b9v6h.public.blob.vercel-storage.com%2Fexamples%2Fnanonananapro.png&w=3840&q=75)\n    \n    Nano Banana Pro Playground\n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    ](https://v0.app/templates/hkRpZoLOrJC)\n\n[\n\nExplore what our community is building\n\n\n\n](https://v0.app/templates)\n\n## [Who is v0 for?](#who-is-v0-for)\n\nv0 helps teams prototype, build, and ship faster. Here's how different roles are using it:\n\n### [Product Managers](#product-managers)\n\nQuickly prototype and iterate to align stakeholders, validate ideas early, and gather user feedback before using engineering resources.\n\nExamples:\n\n-   [Draft project plans and timelines](https://v0.app/chat/realtime-food-delivery-app-SYnS5F3f4eQ)\n-   [Generate user interview questions for researching new features](https://v0.app/chat/figma-integration-questions-tEygM4v11nr)\n-   [Create feedback forms where submissions are sent to a database](https://v0.app/chat/vercel-blob-form-AEdow4eYNT1?b=b_lL01SLSDPbg)\n-   [Create templates for new features or RFCs](https://v0.app/chat/rfc-template-creation-1SUWumwg7VA?b=b_r4q4NtEyq7L)\n\n### [Designers](#designers)\n\nTurn mockups into real, high-fidelity user interfaces that reflect user flows and constraints.\n\nExamples:\n\n-   [Clone pages with screenshots or Figma files](https://v0.app/chat/air-bn-b-clone-z2USwBXCUkt?b=b_wsRgLc7Q6Np)\n-   [Generate CSS and HTML for prototypes and landing pages](https://v0.app/chat/responsive-grid-layout-ORiwZhoEQJN?b=b_cbgUrNMYrUI)\n-   [Add accessibility improvements for basic design elements](https://v0.app/chat/accessible-form-component-cfAFpQlzYij?b=b_PLmcnssJsJT)\n-   [Create interactive components to handoff to developers](https://v0.app/chat/next-js-dark-mode-pU5dltJuOlC?b=b_woRepE69E8F)\n\n### [Engineers](#engineers)\n\nQuickly scaffold full-stack apps or components following best practices and modern standards. Focus on solving the harder problems while using v0 as your AI pair programmer.\n\nExamples:\n\n-   [Create React components](https://v0.app/chat/responsive-nav-bar-ndXU3P0uwkI?b=b_A63dydZKsmW)\n-   [Create custom hooks and functionality](https://v0.app/chat/custom-react-hook-mTAR0Mfr1fE?b=b_sHFhXDNCZq3)\n-   [Migrate to the latest Next.js features](https://v0.app/chat/migrating-to-new-api-s-BS2vObWxSnw)\n\n### [Data Scientists](#data-scientists)\n\nBuild and deploy data applications on Snowflake with v0. Work with Python and SQL to analyze data and create visualizations. Use tools like [Matplotlib](https://matplotlib.org/), [Pandas](https://pandas.pydata.org/), and more.\n\nExamples:\n\n-   [Learn SQL](https://v0.app/chat/sql-basics-QWHEeRIUuK8)\n-   [Write complex queries](https://v0.app/chat/sql-query-for-p99-4RhGamYCG2Q)\n-   [Generate code for data visualization and analysis](https://v0.app/chat/matplotlib-summary-plots-qSnMQHS5tYm)\n-   [Create dashboards for visualizations](https://v0.app/chat/next-js-charts-ky1gWd57Jbq?ref=TQT1P6)\n\n### [Marketing Teams](#marketing-teams)\n\nReduce time-to-market for promotional initiatives by launching custom marketing pages. Generate content ideas, copy, and draft email campaigns.\n\nExamples:\n\n-   [Generate ideas for blog posts, social media content, and ad copy](https://v0.app/chat/ai-blog-topic-ideas-g6gCHmftUFZ?b=b_G5a4ouPZyFk)\n-   [Research keywords and optimize your SEO](https://v0.app/chat/next-js-blog-component-liT74sXMshG?b=b_g2hXZa9ruMw)\n-   [Draft email campaigns and newsletters](https://v0.app/chat/MdfCDyWYFQw?b=b_d0dKVt93l1C)\n-   [Collaborate with developers on features like A/B testing](https://v0.app/chat/next-js-a-b-testing-AFjquiFstFY?b=b_wTb5bso8PDn)\n\n### [Content Creators and Educators](#content-creators-and-educators)\n\nCreate interactive examples and games that are easy to follow and understand. Write lesson plans and create engineering quizzes.\n\nExamples:\n\n-   [Help create lesson plans and educational content](https://v0.app/chat/next-js-lesson-plan-uDmldsC7TBg?b=b_2xwzGb1Nn85)\n-   [Generate practice exercises and quizzes](https://v0.app/chat/interactive-react-quiz-vXjFt7Xr2Ja?b=b_aoDHlI7JKat)\n-   [Assist in developing online course materials with progress tracking](https://v0.app/chat/progress-tracking-component-h4VLQZsiMjc?b=b_kTjunlFR2hE)\n-   [Provide visual explanations for complex concepts, especially related to engineering](https://v0.app/chat/git-basics-for-beginners-GI25SZGQtqP)\n\n### [Customer Support](#customer-support)\n\nHelp customers with technical issues, and build customer support tools.\n\nExamples:\n\n-   [Create a chatbot for customer support](https://v0.app/chat/chatbot-interface-component-eJquKqGe4l8?ref=TQT1P6)\n-   [Assist in creating a searchable knowledge base and articles](https://v0.app/chat/searchable-knowledge-base-QRwo0y9ClK1?b=b_CJpNHy3hUJe)\n-   [Design a customer feedback form](https://v0.app/chat/customer-feedback-form-jgRqnP9KYpF?b=b_fP8kTb5fldI)\n\n### [Founders](#founders)\n\nShip MVPs fast without hiring a dev team, and focus your time on refining product and market fit.\n\n## [What makes v0 different?](#what-makes-v0-different)\n\n-   **End-to-end Development**: Build both UI and backend logic, not just mockups.\n-   **Works with your stack**: Use modern tools like Next.js, Tailwind, shadcn/ui, and more.\n-   **Team-friendly**: Powers collaborative design, product, and engineering workflows.\n-   **Extensible**: Use your APIs, databases, and components.\n-   **Intelligent Agent**: Autonomous capabilities including web search, site inspection, error fixing, and external tool integration.\n-   **Real-time Feedback**: Real-time preview of your app, with visual progress indicators and rich UI feedback for all agent actions.\n-   **Multi-modal**: Combines code generation, web browsing, debugging, and external API interactions in one platform.\n\n### On this page\n\n[What can you do with v0?](#what-can-you-do-with-v0)[Examples](#examples)[Who is v0 for?](#who-is-v0-for)[Product Managers](#product-managers)[Designers](#designers)[Engineers](#engineers)[Data Scientists](#data-scientists)[Marketing Teams](#marketing-teams)[Content Creators and Educators](#content-creators-and-educators)[Customer Support](#customer-support)[Founders](#founders)[What makes v0 different?](#what-makes-v0-different)\n\nScroll to topGive feedbackCopy pageAsk AI about this pageOpen in chat\n\n[](/)\n\n## Product\n\n-   [Home](/)\n-   [Enterprise](/enterprise)\n-   [Pricing](/pricing)\n-   [v0 for Students](/students)\n\n## Company\n\n-   [Terms](https://vercel.com/legal/terms)\n-   [AI Policy](/policy)\n-   [Privacy](https://vercel.com/legal/privacy-policy)\n-   Cookies\n\n## Resources\n\n-   [FAQs](/faq)\n-   [Docs](/docs)\n-   [Ambassadors](/ambassador)\n-   [Vercel Community](https://community.vercel.com/c/v0/59)\n-   [Vercel](https://vercel.com/?utm_source=v0-site&utm_medium=banner&utm_campaign=home)\n\n## Social\n\n-   [Twitter](https://x.com/v0)\n-   [LinkedIn](https://linkedin.com/company/vercel)","metadata":{"truncated":false},"title":"https://vercel.com/docs/v0 (text/html; charset=utf-8)","time":{"start":1781420884210,"end":1781420884704}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_066767556685bc14016a2e535414048191abf386dcb237d532"}},"id":"prt_ec4f580a8001rdq3QJ18Oa5F1Z","sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","messageID":"msg_ec4f53d92001t89jloGpGP7SCD"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781420884784,"sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"webfetch","callID":"call_zLT2fwoJu2ySMkXm0FllrNyn","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"url":"https://v0.dev/docs","format":"markdown","timeout":20},"output":"What is v0? | v0 Docs\n\n[Vercel](https://vercel.com/)Slash[](/docs/en)\n\n-   [Docs](/docs)\n-   [API](/docs/api)\n\nSearch...⌘KAsk AI\n\nAsk AI\n\n[](/docs)\n\nGetting Started\n\n[What is v0?](/docs)[Agentic features](/docs/agentic-features)[Sandbox](/docs/sandbox)[Vercel Integration](/docs/vercel-integration)[Quickstart](/docs/quickstart)[FAQs](/docs/faqs)\n\nPrompt\n\n[Text Prompting](/docs/text-prompting)[Screenshots and Files](/docs/screenshots)[Figma](/docs/figma)\n\nIterate\n\n[Code editing](/docs/code-editing)[Terminal commands](/docs/terminal-commands)[Design mode](/docs/design-mode)[Design systems](/docs/design-systems)[Images and videos](/docs/images-and-videos)[Versions](/docs/versions)\n\nIntegrate\n\n[AI models](/docs/ai-models)[Databases](/docs/databases)[Snowflake](/docs/snowflake)[External APIs](/docs/external-apis)[GitHub](/docs/github)[MCP Integrations](/docs/MCP)[Pre-installed Agents](/docs/pre-installed-agents)[Slack](/docs/slack)\n\nShip\n\n[Deployments](/docs/deployments)[Custom domain](/docs/custom-domains)[Sharing](/docs/sharing)[Templates](/docs/templates)\n\nManage\n\n[Account](/docs/account)[Enterprise](/docs/enterprise)[Instructions](/docs/instructions)[Folders](/docs/folders)[Projects](/docs/projects)[Pricing](/docs/pricing)[Teams](/docs/teams)[Security](/docs/security)\n\nGuides\n\n[Full-stack apps](/docs/full-stack-apps)[Prototyping](/docs/prototyping)[PRD design](/docs/prd-design)\n\nCompare\n\nEnglish\n\nOn this page\n\n# What is v0?\n\nv0 is an AI agent that helps anyone create real code and full-stack apps and agents.\n\nShip features, refine designs, update copy, and create live prototypes, all with a prompt. Deploy to production immediately, or open a pull request for review.\n\n## [What can you do with v0?](#what-can-you-do-with-v0)\n\n-   **Describe your idea** in your preferred language.\n-   **Create high-fidelity UIs** from your wireframes or mockups.\n-   **Connect to backend** to build rich, data driven applications.\n-   **Deploy with one click** to secure, scalable infrastructure powered by Vercel.\n-   **Automatically fix errors** in your code with intelligent diagnostics.\n\n[\n\nGetting Started\n\nQuickstart tutorial to create your first project.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n](/docs/quickstart)[\n\nPrompt Engineering\n\nBuild faster in v0 with effective prompting.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n](/docs/text-prompting)\n\n[\n\nFAQs\n\nFind commonly asked questions about v0.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n](/docs/faqs)[\n\nBlog\n\nStay up to date with new product features and announcements.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n](https://vercel.com/blog/category/v0)\n\n[\n\nWhy should I choose v0 instead of other tools?\n\n\n\n](/docs/faqs#why-should-i-choose-v0)\n\n## [Examples](#examples)\n\nYou can use v0 to build anything, from landing pages, dashboards, ecommerce stores, AI apps, to full-stack applications.\n\n-   [\n    \n    ![Dashboard – M.O.N.K.Y](/docs/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2F4nwqv0zkit3b9v6h.public.blob.vercel-storage.com%2Fexamples%2Fdashboard.png&w=3840&q=75)\n    \n    Dashboard – M.O.N.K.Y\n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    ](https://v0.app/templates/b7GDYVxuoGC)\n-   [\n    \n    ![Brillance SaaS Landing Page](/docs/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2F4nwqv0zkit3b9v6h.public.blob.vercel-storage.com%2Fexamples%2Flanding.png&w=3840&q=75)\n    \n    Brillance SaaS Landing Page\n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    ](https://v0.app/templates/zdiN8dHwaaT)\n-   [\n    \n    ![Shopify Ecommerce Template](/docs/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2F4nwqv0zkit3b9v6h.public.blob.vercel-storage.com%2Fexamples%2Fecoommerce.png&w=3840&q=75)\n    \n    Shopify Ecommerce Template\n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    ](https://v0.app/templates/XmzC9oi7g4m)\n-   [\n    \n    ![Nano Banana Pro Playground](/docs/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2F4nwqv0zkit3b9v6h.public.blob.vercel-storage.com%2Fexamples%2Fnanonananapro.png&w=3840&q=75)\n    \n    Nano Banana Pro Playground\n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    ](https://v0.app/templates/hkRpZoLOrJC)\n\n[\n\nExplore what our community is building\n\n\n\n](https://v0.app/templates)\n\n## [Who is v0 for?](#who-is-v0-for)\n\nv0 helps teams prototype, build, and ship faster. Here's how different roles are using it:\n\n### [Product Managers](#product-managers)\n\nQuickly prototype and iterate to align stakeholders, validate ideas early, and gather user feedback before using engineering resources.\n\nExamples:\n\n-   [Draft project plans and timelines](https://v0.app/chat/realtime-food-delivery-app-SYnS5F3f4eQ)\n-   [Generate user interview questions for researching new features](https://v0.app/chat/figma-integration-questions-tEygM4v11nr)\n-   [Create feedback forms where submissions are sent to a database](https://v0.app/chat/vercel-blob-form-AEdow4eYNT1?b=b_lL01SLSDPbg)\n-   [Create templates for new features or RFCs](https://v0.app/chat/rfc-template-creation-1SUWumwg7VA?b=b_r4q4NtEyq7L)\n\n### [Designers](#designers)\n\nTurn mockups into real, high-fidelity user interfaces that reflect user flows and constraints.\n\nExamples:\n\n-   [Clone pages with screenshots or Figma files](https://v0.app/chat/air-bn-b-clone-z2USwBXCUkt?b=b_wsRgLc7Q6Np)\n-   [Generate CSS and HTML for prototypes and landing pages](https://v0.app/chat/responsive-grid-layout-ORiwZhoEQJN?b=b_cbgUrNMYrUI)\n-   [Add accessibility improvements for basic design elements](https://v0.app/chat/accessible-form-component-cfAFpQlzYij?b=b_PLmcnssJsJT)\n-   [Create interactive components to handoff to developers](https://v0.app/chat/next-js-dark-mode-pU5dltJuOlC?b=b_woRepE69E8F)\n\n### [Engineers](#engineers)\n\nQuickly scaffold full-stack apps or components following best practices and modern standards. Focus on solving the harder problems while using v0 as your AI pair programmer.\n\nExamples:\n\n-   [Create React components](https://v0.app/chat/responsive-nav-bar-ndXU3P0uwkI?b=b_A63dydZKsmW)\n-   [Create custom hooks and functionality](https://v0.app/chat/custom-react-hook-mTAR0Mfr1fE?b=b_sHFhXDNCZq3)\n-   [Migrate to the latest Next.js features](https://v0.app/chat/migrating-to-new-api-s-BS2vObWxSnw)\n\n### [Data Scientists](#data-scientists)\n\nBuild and deploy data applications on Snowflake with v0. Work with Python and SQL to analyze data and create visualizations. Use tools like [Matplotlib](https://matplotlib.org/), [Pandas](https://pandas.pydata.org/), and more.\n\nExamples:\n\n-   [Learn SQL](https://v0.app/chat/sql-basics-QWHEeRIUuK8)\n-   [Write complex queries](https://v0.app/chat/sql-query-for-p99-4RhGamYCG2Q)\n-   [Generate code for data visualization and analysis](https://v0.app/chat/matplotlib-summary-plots-qSnMQHS5tYm)\n-   [Create dashboards for visualizations](https://v0.app/chat/next-js-charts-ky1gWd57Jbq?ref=TQT1P6)\n\n### [Marketing Teams](#marketing-teams)\n\nReduce time-to-market for promotional initiatives by launching custom marketing pages. Generate content ideas, copy, and draft email campaigns.\n\nExamples:\n\n-   [Generate ideas for blog posts, social media content, and ad copy](https://v0.app/chat/ai-blog-topic-ideas-g6gCHmftUFZ?b=b_G5a4ouPZyFk)\n-   [Research keywords and optimize your SEO](https://v0.app/chat/next-js-blog-component-liT74sXMshG?b=b_g2hXZa9ruMw)\n-   [Draft email campaigns and newsletters](https://v0.app/chat/MdfCDyWYFQw?b=b_d0dKVt93l1C)\n-   [Collaborate with developers on features like A/B testing](https://v0.app/chat/next-js-a-b-testing-AFjquiFstFY?b=b_wTb5bso8PDn)\n\n### [Content Creators and Educators](#content-creators-and-educators)\n\nCreate interactive examples and games that are easy to follow and understand. Write lesson plans and create engineering quizzes.\n\nExamples:\n\n-   [Help create lesson plans and educational content](https://v0.app/chat/next-js-lesson-plan-uDmldsC7TBg?b=b_2xwzGb1Nn85)\n-   [Generate practice exercises and quizzes](https://v0.app/chat/interactive-react-quiz-vXjFt7Xr2Ja?b=b_aoDHlI7JKat)\n-   [Assist in developing online course materials with progress tracking](https://v0.app/chat/progress-tracking-component-h4VLQZsiMjc?b=b_kTjunlFR2hE)\n-   [Provide visual explanations for complex concepts, especially related to engineering](https://v0.app/chat/git-basics-for-beginners-GI25SZGQtqP)\n\n### [Customer Support](#customer-support)\n\nHelp customers with technical issues, and build customer support tools.\n\nExamples:\n\n-   [Create a chatbot for customer support](https://v0.app/chat/chatbot-interface-component-eJquKqGe4l8?ref=TQT1P6)\n-   [Assist in creating a searchable knowledge base and articles](https://v0.app/chat/searchable-knowledge-base-QRwo0y9ClK1?b=b_CJpNHy3hUJe)\n-   [Design a customer feedback form](https://v0.app/chat/customer-feedback-form-jgRqnP9KYpF?b=b_fP8kTb5fldI)\n\n### [Founders](#founders)\n\nShip MVPs fast without hiring a dev team, and focus your time on refining product and market fit.\n\n## [What makes v0 different?](#what-makes-v0-different)\n\n-   **End-to-end Development**: Build both UI and backend logic, not just mockups.\n-   **Works with your stack**: Use modern tools like Next.js, Tailwind, shadcn/ui, and more.\n-   **Team-friendly**: Powers collaborative design, product, and engineering workflows.\n-   **Extensible**: Use your APIs, databases, and components.\n-   **Intelligent Agent**: Autonomous capabilities including web search, site inspection, error fixing, and external tool integration.\n-   **Real-time Feedback**: Real-time preview of your app, with visual progress indicators and rich UI feedback for all agent actions.\n-   **Multi-modal**: Combines code generation, web browsing, debugging, and external API interactions in one platform.\n\n### On this page\n\n[What can you do with v0?](#what-can-you-do-with-v0)[Examples](#examples)[Who is v0 for?](#who-is-v0-for)[Product Managers](#product-managers)[Designers](#designers)[Engineers](#engineers)[Data Scientists](#data-scientists)[Marketing Teams](#marketing-teams)[Content Creators and Educators](#content-creators-and-educators)[Customer Support](#customer-support)[Founders](#founders)[What makes v0 different?](#what-makes-v0-different)\n\nScroll to topGive feedbackCopy pageAsk AI about this pageOpen in chat\n\n[](/)\n\n## Product\n\n-   [Home](/)\n-   [Enterprise](/enterprise)\n-   [Pricing](/pricing)\n-   [v0 for Students](/students)\n\n## Company\n\n-   [Terms](https://vercel.com/legal/terms)\n-   [AI Policy](/policy)\n-   [Privacy](https://vercel.com/legal/privacy-policy)\n-   Cookies\n\n## Resources\n\n-   [FAQs](/faq)\n-   [Docs](/docs)\n-   [Ambassadors](/ambassador)\n-   [Vercel Community](https://community.vercel.com/c/v0/59)\n-   [Vercel](https://vercel.com/?utm_source=v0-site&utm_medium=banner&utm_campaign=home)\n\n## Social\n\n-   [Twitter](https://x.com/v0)\n-   [LinkedIn](https://linkedin.com/company/vercel)","metadata":{"truncated":false},"title":"https://v0.dev/docs (text/html; charset=utf-8)","time":{"start":1781420884225,"end":1781420884783}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_066767556685bc14016a2e535414188191a2de15cbe6ac8373"}},"id":"prt_ec4f580f3001KKhOJ5LIq7K3jY","sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","messageID":"msg_ec4f53d92001t89jloGpGP7SCD"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781420884820,"sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"webfetch","callID":"call_44Ha1HgBzxYVCooZL838YUHy","state":{"status":"error","input":{"url":"https://docs.lovable.dev/features/visual-edits","format":"markdown","timeout":20},"error":"StatusCode: non 2xx status code (404 GET https://docs.lovable.dev/features/visual-edits)","time":{"start":1781420884237,"end":1781420884819}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_066767556685bc14016a2e535414308191b0caa815a6b9fe38"}},"id":"prt_ec4f58106001ETdSPXDlm6zeBp","sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","messageID":"msg_ec4f53d92001t89jloGpGP7SCD"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781420884895,"sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"webfetch","callID":"call_9JpnAfid9oyNVYCKoU5lWuku","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"url":"https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/23954856027159-Use-Figma-Make","format":"markdown","timeout":20},"output":"  Navigating UI3 – Figma Learn - Help Center                         \n\n[\n\n**Figma** Learn\n\n](/hc/en-us \"Home\")\n\n[Get started](https://help.figma.com/hc/categories/360002051613-Get-started) Product documentation Administration Courses, tutorials, projects Help\n\nenterto select ↑↓to navigate escto close\n\n![](/hc/theming_assets/01JYKS7CZ94QTYRX1XR0HPP9MS)\n\n[\n\nFigma Design\n\nDesign and prototype in one place\n\n\n\n](https://help.figma.com/hc/categories/360002042553)\n\n[\n\nDev Mode\n\nTranslate designs into code\n\n\n\n](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/15023066873239)\n\n[\n\nFigJam\n\nCollaborate with a digital whiteboard\n\n\n\n](https://help.figma.com/hc/categories/360002051633)\n\n[\n\nFigma Slides\n\nCo-create presentations\n\n\n\n](https://help.figma.com/hc/categories/24146015318551)\n\n[\n\nFigma Draw\n\nNew\n\nIllustrate with advanced vector tools\n\n\n\n](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/31830768959511)\n\n[\n\nFigma Buzz\n\nBeta\n\nProduce on-brand assets at scale\n\n\n\n](https://help.figma.com/hc/categories/31194838351767)\n\n[\n\nFigma Sites\n\nBeta\n\nPublish fully responsive websites\n\n\n\n](https://help.figma.com/hc/categories/31823555275671)\n\n[\n\nFigma Make\n\nPrompt to code anything you can imagine\n\n\n\n](https://help.figma.com/hc/categories/31304285531543)\n\n[\n\nAI\n\nExplore all Figma AI features\n\n\n\n](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/sections/24369548041111)\n\n[\n\nAccessibility\n\nMake Figma accessible for you and others\n\n\n\n](https://help.figma.com/hc/articles/35063862380311)\n\n[\n\nDeveloper docs\n\nWork with APIs, embeds, and more\n\n\n\n](https://www.figma.com/developers)\n\n[\n\nFigma Community\n\nDiscover resources from other Figma creators\n\n\n\n](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/categories/360002772634)\n\nFor everyone\n\n[Account](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/360006479433)\n\n-   [Manage settings](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/4403936365591)\n-   [Change preferences](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/4403936364311)\n\n[Files and projects](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/360006050633)\n\n-   [Use the file browser](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/13166486919191)\n-   [Manage files and projects](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/13166489863319)\n\nFor administration\n\n[Billing](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/4421076253719)\n\n-   [Overview](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/4403936381463)\n-   [Manage seats](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/20830735292567)\n-   [Manage your plan](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/4403929058327)\n-   [Pay for Figma](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/1500001018842)\n\n[Teams](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/360006457394)\n\n-   [Manage a team](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/360006457394)\n\n[Organizations](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/360006606913)\n\n-   [Overview](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/20832795476375)\n-   [Login and authentication](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/4403936348311)\n-   [Deploy Figma](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/4403928836759)\n-   [Members and guests](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/4403928781847)\n-   [Teams](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/20832780119959)\n-   [Libraries and resources](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/4403928823063)\n\n[Enterprise](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/20832705104407)\n\n-   [Billing groups](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/19100866155543)\n-   [Workspaces](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/4419363208855)\n-   [Security features](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/20833164749719)\n\nFind out more\n\n[\n\nCourses and collections\n\nNew\n\nLevel up your Figma skills with these comprehensive skill-based courses.\n\n](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/23691657321239)[\n\nProjects\n\nGet hands-on experience in Figma with these practical bite-sized projects.\n\n](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/13148624530967)[\n\nTutorials\n\nExplore tools and features by watching and following along with these expert-led video tutorials.\n\n](https://www.youtube.com/@Figma)\n\nGet solutions\n\n[\n\nTroubleshoot\n\nGet help with common issues and troubleshoot unexpected behavior.\n\n](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/1500000378401)[\n\nWork with support\n\nSubmit a bug report, get help collecting log files, and find your system information.\n\n](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/19818052690455)[\n\nCommon questions\n\nGet answers to frequently asked questions.\n\n](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/13148115222551)\n\n[\n\nFigma Community Forum\n\nAsk the community, share ideas, and connect with other Figma users.\n\n\n\n](https://forum.figma.com/)\n\n[Get started](https://help.figma.com/hc/categories/360002051613-Get-started)\n\nProduct documentation\n\nProducts [Figma Design](https://help.figma.com/hc/categories/360002042553) [Dev Mode](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/15023066873239) [FigJam](https://help.figma.com/hc/categories/360002051633) [Figma Slides](https://help.figma.com/hc/categories/24146015318551)[\n\nFigma Draw\n\nNew](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/31830768959511)[\n\nFigma Sites\n\nBeta](https://help.figma.com/hc/categories/31823555275671)[\n\nFigma Make\n\n](https://help.figma.com/hc/categories/31304285531543)[\n\nFigma Buzz\n\nBeta](https://help.figma.com/hc/categories/31194838351767)\n\nFeatures [AI](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/sections/24369548041111) [Accessibility](https://help.figma.com/hc/articles/35063862380311) [Developer docs](https://www.figma.com/developers) [Figma Community](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/categories/360002772634)\n\nAdministration\n\nFor everyone [Account](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/360006479433) [Files and projects](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/360006050633)\n\nFor administration [Billing](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/4421076253719) [Teams](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/360006457394) [Organizations](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/360006606913) [Enterprise](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/20832705104407)\n\nCourses, tutorials, projects\n\nFind out more [Courses and collections](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/23691657321239) [Projects](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/13148624530967) [Tutorials](https://www.youtube.com/@Figma)\n\nHelp\n\nGet solutions [Troubleshoot](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/1500000378401) [Work with support](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/19818052690455) [Common questions](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/13148115222551) [Figma Community Forum](https://forum.figma.com/)\n\n1.  [Figma Learn - Help Center](/hc/en-us)\n2.  [Figma Design](/hc/en-us/categories/360002042553-Figma-Design)\n3.  [Tour the interface](/hc/en-us/sections/13148571463703-Tour-the-interface)\n4.  [Explore](/hc/en-us/sections/23539410052631-Explore)\n\n# Navigating UI3\n\n**We're slowly rolling out the new left navigation bar to users in Figma Design.** The navigation bar will provide access to your most essential workflows in a single place. Here is what's coming:\n\n-   Currently, the **variables modal** is not discoverable if you have a layer selected. With this update, the variables modal entry point is moving from the properties panel to the navigation bar, so you can access your variable collections anytime.\n-   The **assets tab** and **find and replace** are moving to the navigation bar\n-   File notifications, such as library updates and missing font alerts, will be found at the bottom of the navigation bar\n-   Property labels, which are labels that provide context for different sections of your properties panel and navigation bar, will be renamed to **Additional labels**. You’ll be able to toggle the labels by clicking \\> **View**.\n\nIf you need a bit more room on the canvas, you can still minimize your UI, which will collapse the navigation bar, navigation panel, and properties panel for an expanded view. To do this, click  **Minimize UI** from the top of the navigation panel (left panel) or press Shift \\\\.\n\n![left-navigation-bar.png](/hc/article_attachments/37507058339351)\n\nThe navigation bar will be available to everyone with a [Full seat](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/360039960434-Manage-seats-in-Figma). During the rollout period, you may see a different experience than your teammates as this feature becomes available.\n\n#### **Who can use this feature**\n\n-   Available on [all plans](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/360040328273)\n-   If you’re new to Figma, we recommend our [guide to exploring design files](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/15297425105303)\n\nAt Config 2024, we introduced a redesigned Figma, called UI3. This guide was created to help you switch over to the new designs and see how things have changed.\n\n### Why we redesigned Figma\n\nFigma has grown more complex over time, and UI3 is an effort to simplify your design experience. Our intent is to make Figma Design feel more focused for designers and more approachable for a broad range of people. We’re also creating a consistent foundation for our existing products—and products yet to come.\n\nThis new design:\n\n-   Gives you more control over the interface, with resizable and collapsible panels\n-   Draws more emphasis to your work on the canvas\n-   Makes features more intuitive by improving their placement, grouping, and how they adapt to different contexts\n-   Adds consistency with our other products, making it easier to switch between Figma Design, FigJam, Dev Mode, and Figma Slides\n\n**Tip:** Want to read more about the redesign? Check out our blog post: [Inside the redesigned Figma, where your work takes center stage](https://www.figma.com/blog/behind-our-redesign-ui3/)\n\n# What's changed\n\n## Navigation panel\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912749347735)\n\nWe’ve reorganized the navigation panel on the left side of the canvas to house all the information about your file and make it easier to use.\n\n#### Minimize the UI\n\nIf you need a bit more room on the canvas, you can now minimize the UI from the navigation panel. Click **Minimize UI** to collapse both the navigation panel and [properties panel](#h_01J0VQQE1QWDA65PXZNSJQ75WM).\n\nIf you select something on the canvas with the UI minimized, the properties panel temporarily opens back up so you can access each property’s controls.\n\n#### File name and location\n\nClick the dropdown icon next to the file name to take action on a file, like [moving it](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/360038511573), [publishing a library](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/360025508373), creating a [branch](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/360063144053), or showing the [version history](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/360038006754).\n\n#### Assets tab\n\nWe’ve made it easier to [search, browse, and insert components](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/360039831974) from the **Assets** tab.\n\n## Toolbar\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912749349911)\n\nThe [new toolbar](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/360041064174) moves design tools to the bottom of the editor. This frees up more working space on the canvas and introduces brand new AI capabilities via the new actions menu.\n\n#### Actions\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912749351319) [Actions](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/23570416033943) is a brand new item in the toolbar, and is all about helping you go from imagination to reality, faster. From here, you can access all Figma’s AI tools, common productivity actions, plugins and widgets, components, and more.\n\n#### Enter Dev Mode\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912764196759)You can now access [Dev Mode](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/15023124644247) in the toolbar, making it easier to switch between modes in Figma Design.\n\n## Properties panel\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912764199063)\n\nThe **Design** view of the properties panel is easier to use and properties are now grouped to match more modern workflows.\n\nYou can also resize the properties panel, which is handy for working with components with long names.\n\n#### Property labels\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912749356055)\n\nNew to UI3, you can now turn on **Property labels** to make it clearer what each property does.\n\nTo turn on property labels, click the dropdown menu next to the 100% zoom percentage in the properties panel and select **Property labels**.\n\n#### Selection actions\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912764201623)The properties panel now features a header row with actions you can perform on a selected object.\n\nFor example, you might find the buttons to apply a [mask](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/360040450253), create a [component](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/360038663154), or perform a boolean operation—or they might be tucked away in the **More** menu.\n\n#### Layout\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912749357847)**Layout** contains all the properties related to an object’s layout, like width and height.\n\nWhen you click **Use auto layout** on a frame, the **Layout** label changes to **Auto layout**, and all the auto layout properties become available.\n\n#### Position\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912749361431)You can now access all properties related to an object’s position on the canvas, including constraints, under **Position**.\n\n**Tip**: You can now [spotlight](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/360040322673) yourself from the properties panel. When people enter spotlight, we’ll minimize the left and right panels, and the toolbar, so you have more room to show off your work.\n\n# Where did a feature move to?\n\nTake a look at the list below to see everything that’s moved—and where you can find it.\n\n \n\n**Old design**\n\n**Redesign**\n\n#### Ask for edit access\n\nIf you have `can view` access to a file and would like to edit it, you can request edit access by clicking **Ask to edit** in the toolbar.\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912749362967)\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912764209047)\n\n#### Absolute position\n\n[Absolute position](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/360040451373-Explore-auto-layout-properties#h_01G2RPRBBKVKXK0JV59NCSKEE0) is now **Ignore auto layout.**\n\nWhen you ignore auto layout, you can manually position an object inside an auto layout frame without following the auto layout structure.\n\nTo ignore auto layout, select a child of an auto layout frame, then click in the properties panel.\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912749368599)\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912749369879)\n\n#### Align objects\n\nThe [alignment controls](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/360039956914) help you align an object to its parent layer, or align multiple objects to one another.\n\nSelect more than one object, then click one of the alignment tools under **Position** in the properties panel.\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912749370647)\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912764219927)\n\n#### Auto layout\n\nWhen you use [auto layout](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/360040451373-Explore-auto-layout-properties) on a frame, it will adjust dynamically to content changes and different screen sizes.\n\nTo use auto layout on a frame, click in the **Layout** section of the properties panel.\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912749375895)\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912749377175)\n\n#### Blend modes\n\n[Blend modes](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/360040667874) define how you want two layers to blend together.\n\nTo apply a blend mode, select an object, click next to **Appearance**, then select a mode.\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912749378839)\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912749380247)\n\n#### Clip content\n\nClip content allows you to hide parts of a layer that extend beyond the bounds of the parent frame.\n\nUse the **Clip content** checkbox under **Layout** to choose whether to clip or show content.\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912764227735)\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912749383575)\n\n#### Component properties\n\n[Component properties](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/5579474826519-Explore-component-properties) are the changeable aspects of a component. You can define which parts of a component others can change by tying them to specific properties.\n\nIf a component has component properties available, you can find them underneath the name of the frame in the properties panel.\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912749385239)\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912764232727)\n\n#### Constraints\n\n[Constraints](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/360039957734) tell Figma how layers should behave when you resize their parent frames.\n\nWith a child layer selected, the **Constraints** icon will appear next to the X and Y position values in the **Position** section of the properties panel.\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912764233623)\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912764236183)\n\n#### Corner radius\n\n[Corner radius](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/360050986854) is a property that allows you to round the corners of an object.\n\nWith an object selected, click the corner radius field under **Appearance** and change the value.\n\nYou can also click to modify each corner individually.\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912749389335)\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912764240151)\n\n#### File name, project name, and file actions\n\nThe name of a file, its project, and the file actions dropdown have moved to the navigation panel.\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912764241175)\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912749393303)\n\n#### Go to main component\n\nYou can navigate to the main component of an instance directly from the properties panel.\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912764249239)\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912764250263)\n\n#### Mask\n\nUse a [mask](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/360040450253) to show specific areas of an object while concealing the rest.\n\nWith an object selected, click **Use as mask** to create a mask group with the object as a mask. Depending on the number of available actions, **Use as mask** might be in the **More** menu.\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912764250775)\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912764251799)\n\n#### Multi-edit\n\n**[Multi-edit](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/21635177948567)** lets you select multiple layers across frames, groups, and sections and apply the same edits to them in bulk.\n\nClick in the properties panel to enable multi-edit.\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912764253207)\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912749405207)\n\n#### Plugins and widgets\n\nTo access [plugins](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/360042532714-Use-plugins-in-files) and [widgets](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/4410047809431), open **Actions** from the toolbar, then click the **Plugins & widgets** tab.\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912764255895)\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912749406743)\n\n#### Resize an object's width or height, or resize to fit\n\nChange an object’s width and height under **Layout**. You can also resize a frame to fit its child layers by clicking the icon.\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912764258327)\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912764259479)\n\n#### Rotate\n\n[Rotating or flipping](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/360039956914-Adjust-alignment-rotation-and-position#Rotating_objects) let you manipulate objects by changing their orientation. With an object selected, find **Position** and:\n\n-   Click to rotate an object 90° to the right\n-   Click to flip horizontally\n-   Click to flip vertically\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912749411863)\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912764261655)\n\n#### Show or hide an object\n\nTo [hide an object on the canvas](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/360041112614-Toggle-visibility-to-hide-layers), click next to **Appearance**. To show it again, click .\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912764266519)\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912764268055)\n\n#### Text\n\n**Text** is now called **Typography**.\n\n-   You can now resize a text layer under **Layout.**\n-   Paragraph spacing has moved to **Type settings**. From **Typography**, click to open the **Type settings** panel.\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912764272407)\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912749419415)\n\n#### Variable modes\n\n[Variable modes](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/15343816063383-Modes-for-variables) represent the different contexts of a design. A mode contains a list of values for [a variable within a collection](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/14506821864087).\n\nIf a variable collection has multiple modes, then you can switch modes on layers and elements to quickly change designs for different contexts.\n\nAs long as an object is bound to a variable with multiple modes, you can click next to **Appearance** to switch the variable mode.\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912764275735)\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912764277271)\n\n#### Add variant\n\n[Variants](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/360056440594-Create-and-use-variants) allow you to group and organize similar components into a single container. When you insert a component instance, you can switch between the variant properties of the component set.\n\nTo add a variant, select a main component, then click **Add a variant** next to the component name in the properties panel.\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912764278551)\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912749425559)\n\n#### Edit a vector path\n\nTo edit a vector path, click **[Edit object](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/360039957634-Edit-Object#h_01HXD3ZSMZNA6V6EEE64RB9F0P)** next to **Vector**.\n\nIf you select multiple vector paths, the [boolean operations](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/360039957534) menu will appear. From here, you can perform the following operations:\n\n-   Union\n-   Subtract\n-   Intersect\n-   Exclude\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912749426199)\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912764282903)\n\n#### Zoom / view options\n\nFrom the **Zoom / view options** menu, you can [adjust your zoom settings](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/360041065034-Adjust-your-zoom-and-view-options), or [configure view options](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/360041065034-Adjust-your-zoom-and-view-options) like layout grids or multiplayer cursors.\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912749435287)\n\n![](/hc/article_attachments/30912764296215)\n\nWas this article helpful?\n\nYes No\n\nHelp Center feedback Got a second? Tell us what we’re doing well.    Submit article feedback\n\nYour feedback helps us improve Figma’s Help Center. To get help from support, [submit a request through our contact form](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/requests/new).\n\nHelp Center feedback Thanks for letting us know! What was the issue?    \\-- Please choose an option -- Incorrect or missing information Hard to understand There are typos or broken links Issues with images, GIFs, or videos I wish the feature worked a different way Something else Submit article feedback\n\nYour feedback helps us improve Figma’s Help Center. To get help from support, [submit a request through our contact form](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/requests/new).\n\nThank you for helping us improve Figma’s Help Center!\n\n![](/hc/theming_assets/01HZFG1CK3ZD17MJD7X1K6QF2N)\n\n[](https://www.figma.com/)\n\n-   English (United States) Deutsch Español (Latinoamérica) Español (España) Français 日本語 한국어 Nederlands (Nederland) Polski (Polska) Português do Brasil\n\n-   [](https://x.com/figma \"X\")\n-   [](https://www.youtube.com/figmadesign \"YouTube\")\n-   [](https://www.instagram.com/figma \"Instagram\")\n-   [](https://www.facebook.com/figmadesign \"Facebook\")\n\n###### Use cases\n\n-   [UI design](https://www.figma.com/ui-design-tool/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [UX design](https://www.figma.com/ux-design-tool/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Prototyping](https://www.figma.com/prototyping/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Graphic design](https://www.figma.com/graphic-design-tool/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Wireframing](https://www.figma.com/wireframe-tool/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Brainstorming](https://www.figma.com/brainstorming-tool/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Templates](https://www.figma.com/templates/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Remote design](https://www.figma.com/remote-design/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n\n###### Explore\n\n-   [Design features](https://www.figma.com/design/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Prototyping features](https://www.figma.com/prototyping/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Design systems features](https://www.figma.com/design-systems/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Collaboration features](https://www.figma.com/collaboration/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [FigJam](https://www.figma.com/figjam/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Pricing](https://www.figma.com/pricing/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Enterprise](https://www.figma.com/organization/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Students and educators](https://www.figma.com/education/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Customers](https://www.figma.com/customers/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Security](https://www.figma.com/security/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Integrations](https://www.figma.com/product-integrations/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Contact](https://www.figma.com/contact/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n\n###### Resources\n\n-   [Blog](https://www.figma.com/blog/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Best practices](https://www.figma.com/best-practices/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Support](https://help.figma.com/hc/ \"Support\")\n-   [Developers](https://www.figma.com/developers/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Learn design](https://www.figma.com/resources/learn-design/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Downloads](https://www.figma.com/downloads/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [What's new](https://www.figma.com/whats-new/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Releases](https://releases.figma.com/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Careers](https://www.figma.com/careers/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [About us](https://www.figma.com/about/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Agency partners](https://www.figma.com/agency-partner-program/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Privacy](https://www.figma.com/summary-of-policy/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Status](https://status.figma.com/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)","metadata":{"truncated":false},"title":"https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/23954856027159-Use-Figma-Make (text/html; charset=utf-8)","time":{"start":1781420884342,"end":1781420884893}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_066767556685bc14016a2e535414388191be9aa1f642d59a69"}},"id":"prt_ec4f5810e001SYrx8jhlAw2yin","sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","messageID":"msg_ec4f53d92001t89jloGpGP7SCD"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781420884931,"sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"webfetch","callID":"call_x8EeCYNdCE3pQvsVxaxxQmPS","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"url":"https://docs.lovable.dev/","format":"markdown","timeout":20},"output":"> ## Documentation Index\n> Fetch the complete documentation index at: https://docs.lovable.dev/llms.txt\n> Use this file to discover all available pages before exploring further.\n\n# Welcome to Lovable\n\n> Lovable is a full-stack AI development platform for building, iterating on, and deploying web applications using natural language, with real code, security, and enterprise governance.\n\n<Frame>\n  <img src=\"https://mintcdn.com/lovable-f9060f1e/ybHXd0Cn2UWhku0A/images/welcome-lovable-dashboard.png?fit=max&auto=format&n=ybHXd0Cn2UWhku0A&q=85&s=7063addda22ec0066d45e5ece92559c4\" alt=\"Welcome Lovable Dashboard\" width=\"3292\" height=\"1898\" data-path=\"images/welcome-lovable-dashboard.png\" />\n</Frame>\n\nLovable lets individuals and teams build production-grade web applications using natural language. You describe what you want to build, and Lovable generates a working application that includes frontend, backend, database, authentication, and integrations, all backed by editable code.\n\nLovable supports the full lifecycle of modern product development, from early exploration and prototyping to deployment and ongoing operation.\n\nApplications are built inside shared workspaces, where people collaborate across one or more projects. Each project represents a single application and produces a codebase that can be synced to GitHub and integrated into existing engineering workflows. The platform is built to help people move faster while maintaining ownership, security, and operational control.\n\n## Why use Lovable\n\nLovable makes it easier to go from an idea to working software.\n\n**Faster iteration**\\\nMove from idea to working software by building through natural language instead of starting from a blank codebase.\n\n**Collaboration when you need it**\\\nWork solo or with a team. Lovable supports shared workspaces so people across roles can contribute in one place when collaboration matters.\n\n**Code ownership and flexibility**\\\nKeep full ownership of your code and integrate Lovable into existing workflows.\n\n**Built with enterprise needs in mind**\\\n[Security, privacy, and governance capabilities](/introduction/welcome#security,-privacy,-and-compliance) are built into the platform from the start.\n\n## Who Lovable is for\n\nLovable is used by people building software on their own, with teams, and across organizations of different sizes.\n\n**Individual builders**\n\n* Founders and entrepreneurs launching MVPs or testing early product ideas\n* Students and educators working on coursework, learning projects, or experiments\n* Independent makers building side projects, prototypes, or small products on their own\n\n**Product, design, and go-to-market teams**\n\n* Product managers creating realistic prototypes to validate workflows and requirements\n* Designers moving beyond static mockups to production-ready interfaces\n* Marketers building landing pages, campaign sites, and lightweight tools\n\n**Technical teams and agencies**\n\n* Developers using Lovable to quickly set up projects, internal tools, and early prototypes\n* Engineering teams reviewing, extending, and maintaining generated code through GitHub\n* Agencies delivering client projects where code ownership and portability matter\n\n**Enterprises**\n\n* Teams building internal tools or business-critical applications used across the organization\n* Organizations building and operating applications with [security, compliance, and governance](/introduction/welcome#security,-privacy,-and-compliance) requirements\n* Companies integrating AI-assisted development into established engineering workflows\n\n## What you can build with Lovable\n\nLovable supports a broad range of web applications, from early exploration to production systems.\n\n**SaaS and business applications**\\\nSubscription products, customer-facing dashboards, admin panels, and multi-user applications\n\n**Consumer-facing web applications**\\\nCommunity platforms, content platforms, and apps built for end users\n\n**Marketplaces and online commerce**\\\nBooking tools, storefronts, and marketplace apps\n\n**Internal tools**\\\nWorkflow tools, operational dashboards, and applications used by internal teams\n\n**Websites and marketing pages**\\\nCompany websites, landing pages, and campaign pages\n\n**Educational tools**\\\nLearning tools, course platforms, student portals, and experiments\n\n**Games and interactive content**\\\nSimple web-based games, quizzes, and simulations\n\n## Security, privacy, and compliance\n\nLovable is built to meet enterprise security and compliance requirements.\n\n### Certifications and standards\n\n* SOC 2 Type II\n* ISO 27001:2022\n* GDPR compliance\n\n[View compliance reports and security attestations](https://trust.lovable.dev/)\n\n### Access and identity\n\n* [Workspace-level roles and permissions](/features/collaboration)\n* [Secure authentication with two-factor authentication (2FA)](/introduction/faq#how-do-i-enable-two-factor-authentication-2fa)\n* [Single sign-on (SSO)](/features/business/sso)\n* [SCIM user provisioning](/features/business/scim)\n\n### Platform security and governance\n\n* Workspace-level administration and controls\n* [Built-in security checks and guidance](/features/security)\n* [Data usage controls and data opt-out options](/features/business/data-opt-out)\n\n[Learn more about Lovable’s approach to security](https://lovable.dev/security)\n\n### Legal and data protection\n\n* [Privacy Policy](https://lovable.dev/privacy)\n* [Terms of Service](https://lovable.dev/terms)\n* [Data Processing Agreement (DPA)](https://lovable.dev/data-processing-agreement)\n* [Platform Rules](https://lovable.dev/platform-rules) and [Abuse Policies](https://lovable.dev/abuse)\n\n## How Lovable fits into your workflow\n\nLovable is designed to complement existing tools and processes:\n\n1. Describe what you want to build\n2. Review and iterate on the generated application\n3. Sync code to GitHub\n4. Deploy, operate, and govern according to your standards\n\nLovable adapts to how you work, rather than forcing changes to your workflow.\n\n<CardGroup cols=\"3\">\n  <Card title=\"Getting Started\" icon=\"stairs\" href=\"/introduction/getting-started\">\n    Step-by-step tutorial to create your first project.\n  </Card>\n\n  <Card title=\"Features\" icon=\"toolbox\" href=\"/features\">\n    Lovable's core features.\n  </Card>\n\n  <Card title=\"Integrations\" icon=\"link\" href=\"/integrations\">\n    Extend functionality with integrations.\n  </Card>\n\n  <Card title=\"Tips & Tricks\" icon=\"lightbulb\" href=\"/tips-tricks\">\n    Get the most out of Lovable.\n  </Card>\n\n  <Card title=\"Prompt Engineering\" icon=\"robot\" href=\"/prompting\">\n    Learn effective prompting strategies.\n  </Card>\n\n  <Card title=\"Glossary\" icon=\"bookmark\" href=\"/glossary\">\n    Learn the key terms.\n  </Card>\n</CardGroup>\n","metadata":{"truncated":false},"title":"https://docs.lovable.dev/ (text/markdown; charset=utf-8)","time":{"start":1781420884229,"end":1781420884930}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_066767556685bc14016a2e5354142481919dfb23bb9aada4a1"}},"id":"prt_ec4f58102001a3iN2qUzfHUPAS","sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","messageID":"msg_ec4f53d92001t89jloGpGP7SCD"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781420885305,"sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"webfetch","callID":"call_q0AJknx9I3H2PoCFR9urvOlf","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"url":"https://docs.subframe.com/","format":"markdown","timeout":20},"output":"> ## Documentation Index\n> Fetch the complete documentation index at: https://docs.subframe.com/llms.txt\n> Use this file to discover all available pages before exploring further.\n\n# Why Subframe\n\n> Subframe is an AI design tool that outputs production-ready React code.\n\nDesigners and developers have always worked in separate tools: designers make mockups, developers translate them to code. But what ships never quite matches what was designed, and developers had wasted hours making it that way.\n\nSubframe is a design tool that eliminates the translation step. Designers use the same components you ship to production, so you spend more time building product, not translating designs.\n\n<Info>\n  This is the developer documentation. To learn how to use Subframe as a design tool, see the [product guide](/learn).\n</Info>\n\n## Code quality matters\n\nUnlike other AI design tools, **Subframe's code output is deterministic.** There's no LLM misinterpreting your design—what is designed is exactly what you get in clean React code, every time.\n\nOur code philosophy:\n\n* **Consistent** — All designs are created from the same consistent design system. No more custom, one-off implementations.\n\n* **Open code** — Avoid platform lock-in. Code generated by Subframe lives in your codebase, copy/pasted or [synced via the CLI](/concepts/syncing-components).\n\n* **Headless** — Subframe uses [Radix ↗](https://www.radix-ui.com/) under the hood, which maintains a cleaner separation of concerns between presentation and behavior.\n\n* **AI-ready** — The generated code follows best practices to be modified further by AI tools like Claude Code, Cursor, Codex, Copilot. You can even connect these tools to Subframe's [MCP server](/guides/mcp-server) to grant direct access to your designs.\n\n## Workflow example\n\nSuppose your designer designs a sign in page in Subframe:\n\n<Frame>\n  <img src=\"https://mintcdn.com/subframe-59800133/PZAsL35sSNLNRpRU/images/developers/signin-page-example.png?fit=max&auto=format&n=PZAsL35sSNLNRpRU&q=85&s=de12630bee565d9ffa9a49621526f9d3\" alt=\"Login page designed in Subframe\" width=\"1964\" height=\"1412\" data-path=\"images/developers/signin-page-example.png\" />\n</Frame>\n\nSubframe turns the designs into pixel-perfect React code determinstically. The generated code uses your design system components, with stubs for business logic:\n\n<CodeGroup>\n  ```tsx SignInPage.tsx expandable theme={null}\n  import React from \"react\"\n  import { Button } from \"@/ui/components/Button\"\n  import { SocialSignInButton } from \"@/ui/components/SocialSignInButton\"\n\n  function SignInPage() {\n    return (\n      <div className=\"flex h-full w-full flex-col items-center justify-center bg-white\">\n        <div className=\"flex w-64 flex-col items-center justify-center gap-8\">\n          <div className=\"flex flex-col items-center justify-center gap-1\">\n            <img\n              className=\"h-16 flex-none object-cover\"\n              src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/subframe/image/upload/v1767591134/uploads/302/zzfsz5tcwky0pkjkru9d.png\"\n            />\n            <span className=\"text-heading-2 font-heading-2 text-default-font\">Welcome</span>\n            <span className=\"text-body font-body text-subtext-color\">Login or sign up below</span>\n          </div>\n          <div className=\"flex w-full flex-col items-center gap-2\">\n            <SocialSignInButton\n              variant=\"google\"\n              onClick={(event: React.MouseEvent<HTMLButtonElement>) => {\n                // [!code highlight:1]\n                // TODO: Implement Google sign in\n              }}\n            />\n            <SocialSignInButton\n              variant=\"apple\"\n              onClick={(event: React.MouseEvent<HTMLButtonElement>) => {\n                // [!code highlight:1]\n                // TODO: Implement Apple sign in\n              }}\n            />\n          </div>\n          <div className=\"flex h-px w-full flex-none flex-col items-center gap-2 bg-neutral-border\" />\n          <Button\n            className=\"h-10 w-full flex-none\"\n            variant=\"brand-secondary\"\n            size=\"large\"\n            icon=\"FeatherMail\"\n            onClick={(event: React.MouseEvent<HTMLButtonElement>) => {\n              // [!code highlight:1]\n              // TODO: Implement email sign in\n            }}\n          >\n            Continue with email\n          </Button>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    )\n  }\n\n  export default SignInPage\n  ```\n\n  ```tsx Button.tsx expandable theme={null}\n  import React from \"react\"\n  import * as SubframeCore from \"@subframe/core\"\n  import * as SubframeUtils from \"../utils\"\n\n  interface ButtonRootProps extends React.ButtonHTMLAttributes<HTMLButtonElement> {\n    disabled?: boolean\n    variant?: \"brand-primary\" | \"brand-secondary\" | \"destructive-primary\"\n    size?: \"large\" | \"medium\" | \"small\"\n    children?: React.ReactNode\n    icon?: SubframeCore.IconName\n    iconRight?: SubframeCore.IconName\n    onClick?: (event: React.MouseEvent<HTMLButtonElement>) => void\n    className?: string\n  }\n\n  const ButtonRoot = React.forwardRef<HTMLButtonElement, ButtonRootProps>(function ButtonRoot(\n    {\n      disabled = false,\n      variant = \"brand-primary\",\n      size = \"medium\",\n      children,\n      icon = null,\n      iconRight = null,\n      className,\n      type = \"button\",\n      ...otherProps\n    }: ButtonRootProps,\n    ref,\n  ) {\n    return (\n      <button\n        className={SubframeUtils.twClassNames(\n          \"group/3b777358 flex h-8 cursor-pointer items-center justify-center gap-2 rounded-md border-none bg-brand-600 px-3 text-left hover:bg-brand-500 active:bg-brand-600 disabled:cursor-default disabled:bg-neutral-200 hover:disabled:cursor-default hover:disabled:bg-neutral-200 active:disabled:cursor-default active:disabled:bg-neutral-200\",\n          {\n            \"h-6 w-auto flex-row flex-nowrap gap-1 px-2 py-0\": size === \"small\",\n            \"h-10 w-auto px-4 py-0\": size === \"large\",\n            \"bg-error-600 hover:bg-error-500 active:bg-error-600\": variant === \"destructive-primary\",\n            \"bg-brand-50 hover:bg-brand-100 active:bg-brand-50\": variant === \"brand-secondary\",\n          },\n          className,\n        )}\n        ref={ref}\n        type={type}\n        disabled={disabled}\n        {...otherProps}\n      >\n        <SubframeCore.Icon\n          className={SubframeUtils.twClassNames(\n            \"text-body font-body text-white group-disabled/3b777358:text-neutral-400\",\n            {\n              \"text-heading-3 font-heading-3\": size === \"large\",\n              \"text-brand-700\": variant === \"brand-secondary\",\n            },\n          )}\n          name={icon}\n        />\n        <div\n          className={SubframeUtils.twClassNames(\"hidden h-4 w-4 flex-none items-center justify-center gap-2\", {\n            \"h-3 w-3 flex-none\": size === \"small\",\n          })}\n        >\n          <SubframeCore.Loader\n            className={SubframeUtils.twClassNames(\n              \"font-['Inter'] text-[12px] font-[400] leading-[20px] text-white group-disabled/3b777358:text-neutral-400\",\n              {\n                \"text-caption font-caption\": size === \"small\",\n                \"text-brand-700\": variant === \"brand-secondary\",\n              },\n            )}\n          />\n        </div>\n        {children ? (\n          <span\n            className={SubframeUtils.twClassNames(\n              \"whitespace-nowrap text-body-bold font-body-bold text-white group-disabled/3b777358:text-neutral-400\",\n              {\n                \"text-caption-bold font-caption-bold\": size === \"small\",\n                \"text-brand-700\": variant === \"brand-secondary\",\n              },\n            )}\n          >\n            {children}\n          </span>\n        ) : null}\n        <SubframeCore.Icon\n          className={SubframeUtils.twClassNames(\n            \"text-body font-body text-white group-disabled/3b777358:text-neutral-400\",\n            {\n              \"text-heading-3 font-heading-3\": size === \"large\",\n              \"text-brand-700\": variant === \"brand-secondary\",\n            },\n          )}\n          name={iconRight}\n        />\n      </button>\n    )\n  })\n\n  export const Button = ButtonRoot\n  ```\n\n  ```tsx SocialSignInButton.tsx expandable theme={null}\n  import React from \"react\"\n  import * as SubframeUtils from \"../utils\"\n\n  interface SocialSignInButtonRootProps extends React.ButtonHTMLAttributes<HTMLButtonElement> {\n    disabled?: boolean\n    variant?: \"facebook\" | \"google\" | \"apple\"\n    onClick?: (event: React.MouseEvent<HTMLButtonElement>) => void\n    className?: string\n  }\n\n  const SocialSignInButtonRoot = React.forwardRef<HTMLButtonElement, SocialSignInButtonRootProps>(\n    function SocialSignInButtonRoot(\n      { disabled = false, variant = \"facebook\", className, type = \"button\", ...otherProps }: SocialSignInButtonRootProps,\n      ref,\n    ) {\n      return (\n        <button\n          className={SubframeUtils.twClassNames(\n            \"group/f1948f75 flex h-10 w-full cursor-pointer items-center justify-center gap-2 rounded-md border border-solid border-neutral-border bg-white px-4 text-left hover:bg-neutral-50 active:bg-white disabled:cursor-default disabled:bg-white hover:disabled:cursor-default hover:disabled:bg-white active:disabled:cursor-default active:disabled:bg-white\",\n            className,\n          )}\n          ref={ref}\n          type={type}\n          disabled={disabled}\n          {...otherProps}\n        >\n          <img\n            className=\"h-5 w-5 flex-none object-cover\"\n            src={\n              variant === \"apple\"\n                ? \"https://res.cloudinary.com/subframe/image/upload/v1711417561/shared/kplo8lv2zjit3brqmadv.png\"\n                : variant === \"google\"\n                ? \"https://res.cloudinary.com/subframe/image/upload/v1711417516/shared/z0i3zyjjqkobzuaecgno.svg\"\n                : \"https://res.cloudinary.com/subframe/image/upload/v1711417550/shared/epocfym1zba2deri6krm.png\"\n            }\n          />\n          <span className=\"text-body-bold font-body-bold text-neutral-700 group-disabled/f1948f75:text-neutral-400\">\n            {variant === \"apple\"\n              ? \"Sign in with Apple\"\n              : variant === \"google\"\n              ? \"Sign in with Google\"\n              : \"Sign in with Facebook\"}\n          </span>\n        </button>\n      )\n    },\n  )\n\n  export const SocialSignInButton = SocialSignInButtonRoot\n  ```\n</CodeGroup>\n\nAll that's left is to export it to your codebase and add business logic. You can do that manually or with AI assistants like Claude Code, Cursor, or Codex connected to our MCP server:\n\n```tsx SignInPage.tsx expandable theme={null}\nimport React from \"react\"\nimport { Button } from \"@/ui/components/Button\"\nimport { SocialSignInButton } from \"@/ui/components/SocialSignInButton\"\n// [!code ++:2]\nimport { useNavigate } from \"react-router-dom\"\nimport { signInWithGoogle, signInWithApple } from \"@/lib/auth\"\n\nfunction SignInPage() {\n  // [!code ++:1]\n  const navigate = useNavigate()\n\n  return (\n    <div className=\"flex h-full w-full flex-col items-center justify-center bg-white\">\n      <div className=\"flex w-64 flex-col items-center justify-center gap-8\">\n        <div className=\"flex flex-col items-center justify-center gap-1\">\n          <img\n            className=\"h-16 flex-none object-cover\"\n            src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/subframe/image/upload/v1767591134/uploads/302/zzfsz5tcwky0pkjkru9d.png\"\n          />\n          <span className=\"text-heading-2 font-heading-2 text-default-font\">Welcome</span>\n          <span className=\"text-body font-body text-subtext-color\">Login or sign up below</span>\n        </div>\n        <div className=\"flex w-full flex-col items-center gap-2\">\n          <SocialSignInButton\n            variant=\"google\"\n            // [!code ++:4]\n            onClick={async () => {\n              await signInWithGoogle()\n              navigate(\"/dashboard\")\n            }}\n          />\n          <SocialSignInButton\n            variant=\"apple\"\n            // [!code ++:4]\n            onClick={async () => {\n              await signInWithApple()\n              navigate(\"/dashboard\")\n            }}\n          />\n        </div>\n        <div className=\"flex h-px w-full flex-none flex-col items-center gap-2 bg-neutral-border\" />\n        <Button\n          className=\"h-10 w-full flex-none\"\n          variant=\"brand-secondary\"\n          size=\"large\"\n          icon=\"FeatherMail\"\n          // [!code ++:3]\n          onClick={() => {\n            navigate(\"/sign-in/email\")\n          }}\n        >\n          Continue with email\n        </Button>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  )\n}\n\nexport default SignInPage\n```\n\nThat's it.\n\nYou just went from design to production-ready code in minutes, without translating mockups or pixel-pushing. With Subframe, you focus on the real engineering work.\n","metadata":{"truncated":false},"title":"https://docs.subframe.com/ (text/markdown; charset=utf-8)","time":{"start":1781420884379,"end":1781420885303}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_066767556685bc14016a2e535414408191ba0542cdcef06570"}},"id":"prt_ec4f58184001HfvMea7agCMIo8","sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","messageID":"msg_ec4f53d92001t89jloGpGP7SCD"}}
