{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781420918509,"sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"webfetch","callID":"call_NioH7HsPU9fXXwKKWseMsZMA","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"url":"https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/31304412302231-Explore-Figma-Make","format":"markdown","timeout":20},"output":"  Explore Figma Make – Figma Learn - Help Center                         \n\n[\n\n**Figma** Learn\n\n](/hc/en-us \"Home\")\n\n[Get started](https://help.figma.com/hc/categories/360002051613-Get-started) Product documentation Administration Courses, tutorials, projects Help\n\nenterto select ↑↓to navigate escto close\n\n![](/hc/theming_assets/01JYKS7CZ94QTYRX1XR0HPP9MS)\n\n[\n\nFigma Design\n\nDesign and prototype in one place\n\n\n\n](https://help.figma.com/hc/categories/360002042553)\n\n[\n\nDev Mode\n\nTranslate designs into code\n\n\n\n](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/15023066873239)\n\n[\n\nFigJam\n\nCollaborate with a digital whiteboard\n\n\n\n](https://help.figma.com/hc/categories/360002051633)\n\n[\n\nFigma Slides\n\nCo-create presentations\n\n\n\n](https://help.figma.com/hc/categories/24146015318551)\n\n[\n\nFigma Draw\n\nNew\n\nIllustrate with advanced vector tools\n\n\n\n](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/31830768959511)\n\n[\n\nFigma Buzz\n\nBeta\n\nProduce on-brand assets at scale\n\n\n\n](https://help.figma.com/hc/categories/31194838351767)\n\n[\n\nFigma Sites\n\nBeta\n\nPublish fully responsive websites\n\n\n\n](https://help.figma.com/hc/categories/31823555275671)\n\n[\n\nFigma Make\n\nPrompt to code anything you can imagine\n\n\n\n](https://help.figma.com/hc/categories/31304285531543)\n\n[\n\nAI\n\nExplore all Figma AI features\n\n\n\n](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/sections/24369548041111)\n\n[\n\nAccessibility\n\nMake Figma accessible for you and others\n\n\n\n](https://help.figma.com/hc/articles/35063862380311)\n\n[\n\nDeveloper docs\n\nWork with APIs, embeds, and more\n\n\n\n](https://www.figma.com/developers)\n\n[\n\nFigma Community\n\nDiscover resources from other Figma creators\n\n\n\n](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/categories/360002772634)\n\nFor everyone\n\n[Account](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/360006479433)\n\n-   [Manage settings](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/4403936365591)\n-   [Change preferences](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/4403936364311)\n\n[Files and projects](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/360006050633)\n\n-   [Use the file browser](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/13166486919191)\n-   [Manage files and projects](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/13166489863319)\n\nFor administration\n\n[Billing](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/4421076253719)\n\n-   [Overview](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/4403936381463)\n-   [Manage seats](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/20830735292567)\n-   [Manage your plan](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/4403929058327)\n-   [Pay for Figma](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/1500001018842)\n\n[Teams](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/360006457394)\n\n-   [Manage a team](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/360006457394)\n\n[Organizations](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/360006606913)\n\n-   [Overview](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/20832795476375)\n-   [Login and authentication](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/4403936348311)\n-   [Deploy Figma](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/4403928836759)\n-   [Members and guests](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/4403928781847)\n-   [Teams](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/20832780119959)\n-   [Libraries and resources](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/4403928823063)\n\n[Enterprise](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/20832705104407)\n\n-   [Billing groups](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/19100866155543)\n-   [Workspaces](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/4419363208855)\n-   [Security features](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/20833164749719)\n\nFind out more\n\n[\n\nCourses and collections\n\nNew\n\nLevel up your Figma skills with these comprehensive skill-based courses.\n\n](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/23691657321239)[\n\nProjects\n\nGet hands-on experience in Figma with these practical bite-sized projects.\n\n](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/13148624530967)[\n\nTutorials\n\nExplore tools and features by watching and following along with these expert-led video tutorials.\n\n](https://www.youtube.com/@Figma)\n\nGet solutions\n\n[\n\nTroubleshoot\n\nGet help with common issues and troubleshoot unexpected behavior.\n\n](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/1500000378401)[\n\nWork with support\n\nSubmit a bug report, get help collecting log files, and find your system information.\n\n](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/19818052690455)[\n\nCommon questions\n\nGet answers to frequently asked questions.\n\n](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/13148115222551)\n\n[\n\nFigma Community Forum\n\nAsk the community, share ideas, and connect with other Figma users.\n\n\n\n](https://forum.figma.com/)\n\n[Get started](https://help.figma.com/hc/categories/360002051613-Get-started)\n\nProduct documentation\n\nProducts [Figma Design](https://help.figma.com/hc/categories/360002042553) [Dev Mode](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/15023066873239) [FigJam](https://help.figma.com/hc/categories/360002051633) [Figma Slides](https://help.figma.com/hc/categories/24146015318551)[\n\nFigma Draw\n\nNew](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/31830768959511)[\n\nFigma Sites\n\nBeta](https://help.figma.com/hc/categories/31823555275671)[\n\nFigma Make\n\n](https://help.figma.com/hc/categories/31304285531543)[\n\nFigma Buzz\n\nBeta](https://help.figma.com/hc/categories/31194838351767)\n\nFeatures [AI](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/sections/24369548041111) [Accessibility](https://help.figma.com/hc/articles/35063862380311) [Developer docs](https://www.figma.com/developers) [Figma Community](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/categories/360002772634)\n\nAdministration\n\nFor everyone [Account](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/360006479433) [Files and projects](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/360006050633)\n\nFor administration [Billing](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/4421076253719) [Teams](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/360006457394) [Organizations](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/360006606913) [Enterprise](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/20832705104407)\n\nCourses, tutorials, projects\n\nFind out more [Courses and collections](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/23691657321239) [Projects](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/13148624530967) [Tutorials](https://www.youtube.com/@Figma)\n\nHelp\n\nGet solutions [Troubleshoot](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/1500000378401) [Work with support](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/19818052690455) [Common questions](https://help.figma.com/hc/sections/13148115222551) [Figma Community Forum](https://forum.figma.com/)\n\n1.  [Figma Learn - Help Center](/hc/en-us)\n2.  [Figma Make](/hc/en-us/categories/31304285531543-Figma-Make)\n3.  [Get started](/hc/en-us/sections/31304417633559-Get-started)\n\n# Explore Figma Make\n\nBefore you start\n\nWho can use this feature\n\nFigma Make is available for [Full seats](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/360039960434) on paid plans.\n\nYou can try Figma Make on [other seats and plans](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/31722591905559-Figma-Make-FAQs#h_01JZQX7SQ7RX4SJ65DHDTYS2EK).\n\n## What is Figma Make?\n\nFigma Make is an AI-driven, prompt-to-app tool that lets you bring ideas and existing Figma designs to life as functional prototypes, web apps, and interactive UI. [Through conversation](#h_01JTEHMXV40EAX57KXX54CH431), you can ideate, iterate, and improve your functional prototypes and web apps.\n\n![Figma Make-designed photo gallery app with responsive grid layout, displaying mountain, forest, and ocean demo images from Unsplash.](/hc/article_attachments/33686410199447)\n\nUse Figma Make to:\n\n-   Preview the look and feel of your designs in a functional form\n-   Turn proposals and ideas into prototypes to help hone your product approach\n-   Explore a variety of solutions for a problem you're trying to solve\n\nFigma Make provides several features that make it easy to transform your Figma designs into functional prototypes:\n\n-   Attach your existing Figma designs, components, and Community content to your prompts\n-   As you continue a conversation, [point to specific parts of the preview](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/31304485164695#h_01JTEVBJ0527WJSQ40FDX87CRH) that you want to improve\n-   [Search the web](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/39715554287255) for current information or fetch content from a specific URL to ground your prototype in real-world data\n-   Collaborate with your team in the same conversations, and simultaneously modify the generated code\n-   [Share previews of your functional prototype or web app](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/31304548273047) with other people\n-   [Publish your functional prototype or web app](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/31304586129559) as a website with a dedicated URL\n\nTo get started, check out [Create and edit a functional prototype or web app](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/31304485164695). You can create Figma Make files the same way you [create other new files in Figma](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/360038511153-Create-a-new-file). In the file browser, navigate to your drafts. Then, in the upper-right corner, click **Make**.\n\n**Note:** Figma Make may incorporate third-party content from the internet—such as fonts, code packages, or images—into your functional prototype or web app. You are responsible for ensuring you have appropriate rights to all content before publishing.\n\n## Find your way around\n\nFigma Make offers a straightforward interface to help you start generating prototypes from your designs as quickly as possible. Figma Make has two primary areas: the AI chat, where you can prompt the model, and the preview, where you can see a working version of your app and [edit the code](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/33649966245783).\n\n![Figma Make interface displaying a blank canvas with AI prompt options and sharing controls.](/hc/article_attachments/33686394896279)\n\n### Chat with AI\n\nThe AI chat in Figma Make is where you'll share Figma designs and images, converse with the model to generate your functional prototype or web app, and iterate by prompting.\n\n#### **Bring your design to Figma Make**\n\nTo use your existing designs to generate an app, click **+**, then **Import from Figma**, and then select the design you want to use. You can attach more than one design to help give the model more guidance.\n\nYou can also paste frames and components from your designs directly into the AI chat.\n\n#### **Use images to create with Figma Make**\n\nHave an idea that's not in a design file yet? Provide images in the AI chat to get your app started. To use an image, click **+**, then **Upload image** and select the image you want to add, or paste the image directly into chat.\n\n#### **Guide the AI with conversation**\n\nHave inspired ideas or instructions you want the model to follow? Just write them in the AI chat and work iteratively with Figma Make to bring those ideas to life.\n\n### Iterate with conversation and the edit tool\n\nImproving your functional prototype or web app is as simple as continuing the conversation in the AI chat. You can keep attaching designs, images, and typing into the prompt box to iterate on the result of your conversation.\n\nYou can also use Figma Make's edit tool to point to specific parts of your functional prototype or web app and make direct changes. Depending on the element, you can do things like change padding, margins, colors, text properties. You can also use the Edit tool to prompt the specific changes you want to see.\n\n## Create functional prototypes, web apps, and interactive UI\n\nReady to get started? Check out [Create and edit a functional prototype or web app](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/31304485164695), where you'll find all the details to help get you started generating with the AI chat.\n\nOnce you have your functional prototype or web app, you can also view it in [a dedicated, fullscreen preview](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/31304548273047), similar to Figma Design prototypes.\n\nYou can also [add a backend](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/32640822050199) to your functional prototype or web app to securely store and manage data. For example, you’ll need a backend when you want to maintain the state of an app across different browsers, provide login screens, save and load content like text and images, and store secrets and API keys.\n\n## Collaborate on and share functional prototypes and web apps\n\nAfter you've created a functional prototype or web app, you can share it in different ways with your teammates or anyone on the web.\n\n### Copy a Figma Make preview as design layers\n\nIn Figma Make, you can can copy a snapshot of a preview as layers and then paste those layers into Figma Design. [Bringing in Figma Make previews as layers](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/35060759685015) is a great way to iterate on designs with other teammates. For example, you could copy the different interfaces in your web app one at a time, and then use a Figma Design file as a place to collaborate with others, try out different design ideas, and further edit the designs.\n\n### Create and use templates\n\nTemplates in Figma Make are a great way to create a high quality foundation for users in a team or organization to get started faster with Figma Make.\n\nTemplates enable you to:\n\n-   Build a polished Figma Make file that's consistent with brand and product guidelines\n-   Share that file with others to use while setting guidelines for how the styles and functionality can be changed\n-   Let members of your team and organization get making in a way that respects the guidelines you’ve set\n\nWhen you [create a template in Figma Make](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/34716344138519), your teammates can start [using the template](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/34716178062871) right away to riff on and experiment with the work you've been doing.\n\n## Create and publish a Make kit\n\nIn a Make kit, you can add npm packages to provide context on which assets—like components, styles, and tokens—to use, import variables and styles from your design library, and write guidelines to provide context on how the assets should use [style context](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/33024539096471-Bring-style-context-from-a-Figma-Design-library-into-Figma-Make) and behave.\n\n### Share and publish\n\nYou can [share the preview of your functional prototype or web app](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/31304548273047#h_01JTEZH2Q3T7YR8ZTPXT567DMX) with anyone you want, using the granular permissions to control access and keep your concepts safe.\n\nThen, when you're ready, [publish your functional prototype or web app](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/31304586129559) to the public web with its own dedicated URL courtesy of Figma, or assign a custom domain that you own.\n\n## Permissions in Figma Make\n\nYour permissions determine what actions you can take in Figma Make files and whether you can make changes to a functional prototype or web app.\n\n### Sharing Figma Make files\n\nFile owners and anyone with the `can edit` permission for a Figma Make file can publish the file to the public web. Once Figma Make files are published as functional prototypes or web apps, they will be available on the public web. However, visitors to the site cannot access the Figma Make file that was used to publish the site.\n\n### Creating files\n\nTo create Figma Make files, a Full seat on a paid plan. You can also try out Figma Make with other seats and plans.\n\n### Editing, viewing, and sharing\n\nDepending on your permissions, you can take different actions in a Figma Make file.\n\n-   People with `can edit` attach designs, images, see the chat history, and write prompts in the AI chat. They can view the full-screen preview. They can invite other editors and viewers to the file. They can publish the Figma Make file to the public web.\n-   People with `can view` can view the prompts in the AI chat, see the chat history, but not write their own prompts. They can view the full-screen preview. They can invite other viewers to the file.\n\n## What's next?\n\nTo get started using Figma Make, check out the following articles:\n\n-   [Create and edit a functional prototype or web app](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/31304485164695)\n-   [Attach designs and images to a prompt](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/31304529835671)\n-   [Edit the code of a functional prototype or web app](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/33649966245783)\n-   [Preview a functional prototype or web app](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/31304548273047)\n-   [Create and update a template in Figma Make](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/34716344138519)\n-   [Custom skills for Figma Make](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/40283639496599)\n-   [Publish a functional prototype or web app to the Figma Community](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/33652209702423)\n-   [Remix a functional prototype or web app](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/33681473825303)\n-   [Publish, update, or unpublish a functional prototype or web app](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/31304586129559)\n-   [Best practices for optimizing AI credits in Figma Make](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/40097793879191)\n\n## Questions about Figma Make?\n\nIf you have questions about Figma Make or how to use the product, check out the [Figma Make FAQs](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/31722591905559).\n\nWas this article helpful?\n\nYes No\n\nHelp Center feedback Got a second? Tell us what we’re doing well.    Submit article feedback\n\nYour feedback helps us improve Figma’s Help Center. To get help from support, [submit a request through our contact form](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/requests/new).\n\nHelp Center feedback Thanks for letting us know! What was the issue?    \\-- Please choose an option -- Incorrect or missing information Hard to understand There are typos or broken links Issues with images, GIFs, or videos I wish the feature worked a different way Something else Submit article feedback\n\nYour feedback helps us improve Figma’s Help Center. To get help from support, [submit a request through our contact form](https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/requests/new).\n\nThank you for helping us improve Figma’s Help Center!\n\n![](/hc/theming_assets/01HZFG1CK3ZD17MJD7X1K6QF2N)\n\n[](https://www.figma.com/)\n\n-   English (United States) Deutsch Español (Latinoamérica) Español (España) Français 日本語 한국어 Nederlands (Nederland) Polski (Polska) Português do Brasil\n\n-   [](https://x.com/figma \"X\")\n-   [](https://www.youtube.com/figmadesign \"YouTube\")\n-   [](https://www.instagram.com/figma \"Instagram\")\n-   [](https://www.facebook.com/figmadesign \"Facebook\")\n\n###### Use cases\n\n-   [UI design](https://www.figma.com/ui-design-tool/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [UX design](https://www.figma.com/ux-design-tool/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Prototyping](https://www.figma.com/prototyping/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Graphic design](https://www.figma.com/graphic-design-tool/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Wireframing](https://www.figma.com/wireframe-tool/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Brainstorming](https://www.figma.com/brainstorming-tool/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Templates](https://www.figma.com/templates/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Remote design](https://www.figma.com/remote-design/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n\n###### Explore\n\n-   [Design features](https://www.figma.com/design/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Prototyping features](https://www.figma.com/prototyping/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Design systems features](https://www.figma.com/design-systems/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Collaboration features](https://www.figma.com/collaboration/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [FigJam](https://www.figma.com/figjam/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Pricing](https://www.figma.com/pricing/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Enterprise](https://www.figma.com/organization/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Students and educators](https://www.figma.com/education/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Customers](https://www.figma.com/customers/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Security](https://www.figma.com/security/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Integrations](https://www.figma.com/product-integrations/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Contact](https://www.figma.com/contact/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n\n###### Resources\n\n-   [Blog](https://www.figma.com/blog/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Best practices](https://www.figma.com/best-practices/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Support](https://help.figma.com/hc/ \"Support\")\n-   [Developers](https://www.figma.com/developers/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Learn design](https://www.figma.com/resources/learn-design/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Downloads](https://www.figma.com/downloads/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [What's new](https://www.figma.com/whats-new/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Releases](https://releases.figma.com/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Careers](https://www.figma.com/careers/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [About us](https://www.figma.com/about/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Agency partners](https://www.figma.com/agency-partner-program/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Privacy](https://www.figma.com/summary-of-policy/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)\n-   [Status](https://status.figma.com/?utm_source=help-center&utm_medium=marketing_referral&utm_campaign=help_center)","metadata":{"truncated":false},"title":"https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/articles/31304412302231-Explore-Figma-Make (text/html; charset=utf-8)","time":{"start":1781420918258,"end":1781420918508}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0dc690b044d24971016a2e5376327881918b1251cf1dfc5981"}},"id":"prt_ec4f605f0001HRrEA3Lw5lSsGy","sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","messag