{"type":"text","timestamp":1781421482366,"sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","part":{"id":"prt_ec4fea0de00132hTSyuytnG0Cz","messageID":"msg_ec4fe880a001089wduXzCfSMy2","sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","type":"text","text":"The consistency check failed only because `deep-research-strategy.md` is missing required charter sections: `Non-Goals`, `Stop Conditions`, and `Next Focus`. I’m reading that file and will patch only that artifact if the missing sections are straightforward.","time":{"start":1781421482206,"end":1781421482361},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0f4cdeb1d617d307016a2e55aa32fc81918395cf294c563241","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781421483409,"sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_ZTfaEz73EppGPjIPLT7Wcd7u","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/006-competitor-design-tools-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-strategy.md","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/006-competitor-design-tools-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Deep Research Strategy - gpt55fast lineage (006 competitor design tools)\"\n3: description: Persistent research plan and final reducer state for the gpt55fast fan-out lineage investigating competitor AI design-tool ideas for sk-interface-design and mcp-magicpath.\n4: importance_tier: normal\n5: contextType: planning\n6: ---\n7: \n8: # Deep Research Strategy - gpt55fast lineage\n9: \n10: Runtime strategy for the `gpt55fast` fan-out lineage of packet 006. The lineage ran to the configured hard cap of five iterations and wrote only inside the bound lineage artifact directory.\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## 2. TOPIC\n15: \n16: What do leading AI UI/design-generation tools (v0 by Vercel, Lovable, Figma Make, Subframe, and similar) do that `sk-interface-design` (design judgment) and `mcp-magicpath` (canvas/CLI) could adopt beyond the 005 Claude Design parity findings, classified ADOPT / ADAPT / SKIP per skill while preserving anti-default and lean-CLI constraints.\n17: \n18: ---\n19: \n20: ## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n21: \n22: - [x] Q1: What distinctive, design-relevant capabilities do v0, Lovable, Figma Make, Subframe, and similar tools ship?\n23: - [x] Q2: Which are net-new versus packet 005, and which are sharper restatements?\n24: - [x] Q3: Per idea, what is the ADOPT / ADAPT / SKIP verdict for each local skill?\n25: - [x] Q4: What competitor features are out of scope for two CLI skills?\n26: - [x] Q5: What prioritized recommendation set should the merge step consider?\n27: \n28: ---\n29: \n30: ## 4. NON-GOALS\n31: \n32: - Implementing any changes to `sk-interface-design` or `mcp-magicpath`.\n33: - Replacing packet 005; this lineage dedupes against it.\n34: - Adopting hosted-product capabilities such as publishing, billing, live multiplayer, app hosting, enterprise admin, or backend setup.\n35: - Turning `sk-interface-design` into a preset chooser or template generator.\n36: \n37: ---\n38: \n39: ## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n40: \n41: - Reached the configured lineage cap of 5 iterations.\n42: - All five key questions have evidence-backed answers in this lineage.\n43: - Synthesis exists with per-skill adoption verdicts and negative knowledge.\n44: \n45: ---\n46: \n47: ## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n48: \n49: - Q1 answered: primary evidence was gathered for v0, Lovable, Figma Make, Subframe, plus adjacent Builder/Anima/Framer signals.\n50: - Q2 answered: net-new patterns are pre-build direction gates, element-target grammar, adherence scanners, editable plan/guideline artifacts, presentational-wrapper boundaries, and explicit visual-test limitations.\n51: - Q3 answered: see `research.md` sections 7-9 for ADOPT / ADAPT / SKIP verdicts.\n52: - Q4 answered: negative knowledge is consolidated in `research.md` section 10 and `deep-research-findings-registry.json`.\n53: - Q5 answered: top recommendations are the direction gate, element-target feedback grammar, design-system adherence scan, presentational/generated boundary, and guidelines artifact.\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n58: ## 7. WHAT WORKED\n59: \n60: - Primary docs first: official docs for v0, Lovable, Figma Make, and Subframe provided enough feature detail to avoid marketing-only claims.\n61: - Deduping against packet 005 early kept the recommendation focused on net-new patterns rather than repeating the Claude Design fidelity loop.\n62: - Separating design judgment (`sk-interface-design`) from canvas/CLI mechanics (`mcp-magicpath`) made ADOPT / ADAPT / SKIP decisions crisp.\n63: - Treating SKIP as a first-class outcome preserved the anti-default and lean-CLI boundaries.\n64: \n65: ---\n66: \n67: ## 8. WHAT FAILED\n68: \n69: - A Lovable `visual-edits` URL returned 404; the current docs place that capability under `preview-toolbar.md`.\n70: - An initial Figma Make article URL resolved to a broader Figma UI3 page; the category and specific article pages supplied the correct Make evidence.\n71: - Some adjacent-product docs were too broad or marketing-heavy; they were used only as weak corroboration, not as core recommendations.\n72: - No completed sibling `opus48-claude2` iteration outputs were present when this lineage synthesized, so cross-lineage reconciliation is left to the merge host.\n73: \n74: ---\n75: \n76: ## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n77: \n78: ### Hosted product cloning - BLOCKED (iterations 1-5)\n79: - What was tried: considered v0 deployment, Lovable Cloud, Figma Make publishing, Framer site publishing, and Anima app hosting.\n80: - Why blocked: platform hosting and account/workspace governance are outside the two local CLI skills.\n81: - Do NOT retry: do not recommend hosted deployment, billing, admin, or public publishing features for this packet.\n82: \n83: ### Preset chooser adoption - BLOCKED (iterations 2 and 5)\n84: - What was tried: evaluated Lovable design questions and curated palettes/layouts as potential local skill features.\n85: - Why blocked: copying them as presets conflicts with `sk-interface-design` anti-default rules.\n86: - Do NOT retry: do not turn design inventory data into a chooser.\n87: \n88: ### Automated subtle visual diff - BLOCKED (iterations 2 and 5)\n89: - What was tried: evaluated browser testing as a visual quality gate.\n90: - Why blocked: Lovable documents browser testing as unreliable for subtle design details.\n91: - Do NOT retry: use screenshot-supported design judgment, not blind pixel-diff automation, as the fidelity gate.\n92: \n93: ---\n94: \n95: ## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n96: \n97: - v0-style full-stack deployment/backend agent for these skills: platform scope, not local CLI-skill scope.\n98: - Lovable-style preset palette/font/layout chooser in `sk-interface-design`: conflicts with anti-default mandate.\n99: - Figma Make-style local Git branch/PR management in `mcp-magicpath`: belongs to sk-git/workflow tooling.\n100: - Subframe-style two-way source-of-truth for generated component code: use generated-file plus wrapper boundaries instead.\n101: - Hosted live multiplayer canvas, public publishing, billing, enterprise admin, or backend setup: out of scope.\n102: \n103: ---\n104: \n105: ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n106: \n107: Lineage complete. Merge host should reconcile this `gpt55fast` synthesis with the sibling `opus48-claude2` lineage when available, then produce the packet-level `research/research.md`.\n108: \n109: ---\n110: \n111: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n112: ## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n113: \n114: - Packet 005 baseline: shared Claude Design parity protocol (design-context snapshot, iteration ledger, handoff manifest), mcp-magicpath fidelity verification after submit, context intake, and handoff emit are already known.\n115: - `sk-interface-design` is a judgment skill: it grounds subject/audience/job, builds a compact token system, critiques against AI defaults, and must not become templated.\n116: - `mcp-magicpath` is a CLI/canvas skill: it discovers, inspects, installs, authors, edits, and imports MagicPath components, and it already delegates aesthetic direction to `sk-interface-design`.\n117: - `resource-map.md` was absent at the parent spec folder at init; lineage emitted a local evidence resource map from gathered sources.\n118: \n119: ---\n120: \n121: ## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n122: \n123: - Max iterations: 5.\n124: - Convergence threshold: 0.05.\n125: - Stop reason: maxIterationsReached.\n126: - Output boundary: artifact directory only, per operator instruction.\n127: - Spec write-back and memory save: skipped/deferred for this isolated fan-out lineage.\n128: - Lineage: gpt55fast (`cli-opencode` / `openai/gpt-5.5-fast`).\n129: - Current generation: 1.\n130: - Started: 2026-06-14T09:20:00Z.\n\n(End of file - total 130 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Deep Research Strategy - gpt55fast lineage (006 competitor design tools)\"\ndescription: Persistent research plan and final reducer state for the gpt55fast fan-out lineage investigating competitor AI design-tool ideas for sk-interface-design and mcp-magicpath.\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: planning\n---\n\n# Deep Research Strategy - gpt55fast lineage\n\nRuntime strategy for the `gpt55fast` fan-out lineage of packet 006. The lineage ran to the configured hard cap of five iterations and wrote only inside the bound lineage artifact directory.\n\n---\n\n## 2. TOPIC\n\nWhat do leading AI UI/design-generation tools (v0 by Vercel, Lovable, Figma Make, Subframe, and similar) do that `sk-interface-design` (design judgment) and `mcp-magicpath` (canvas/CLI) could adopt beyond the 005 Claude Design parity findings, classified ADOPT / ADAPT / SKIP per skill while preserving anti-default and lean-CLI constraints.\n\n---\n\n## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/006-competitor-design-tools-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-strategy.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Deep Research Strategy - gpt55fast lineage (006 competitor design tools)\"\ndescription: Persistent research plan and final reducer state for the gpt55fast fan-out lineage investigating competitor AI design-tool ideas for sk-interface-design and mcp-magicpath.\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: planning\n---\n\n# Deep Research Strategy - gpt55fast lineage\n\nRuntime strategy for the `gpt55fast` fan-out lineage of packet 006. The lineage ran to the configured hard cap of five iterations and wrote only inside the bound lineage artifact directory.\n\n---\n\n## 2. TOPIC\n\nWhat do leading AI UI/design-generation tools (v0 by Vercel, Lovable, Figma Make, Subframe, and similar) do that `sk-interface-design` (design judgment) and `mcp-magicpath` (canvas/CLI) could adopt beyond the 005 Claude Design parity findings, classified ADOPT / ADAPT / SKIP per skill while preserving anti-default and lean-CLI constraints.\n\n---\n\n## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n\n- [x] Q1: What distinctive, design-relevant capabilities do v0, Lovable, Figma Make, Subframe, and similar tools ship?\n- [x] Q2: Which are net-new versus packet 005, and which are sharper restatements?\n- [x] Q3: Per idea, what is the ADOPT / ADAPT / SKIP verdict for each local skill?\n- [x] Q4: What competitor features are out of scope for two CLI skills?\n- [x] Q5: What prioritized recommendation set should the merge step consider?\n\n---\n\n## 4. NON-GOALS\n\n- Implementing any changes to `sk-interface-design` or `mcp-magicpath`.\n- Replacing packet 005; this lineage dedupes against it.\n- Adopting hosted-product capabilities such as publishing, billing, live multiplayer, app hosting, enterprise admin, or backend setup.\n- Turning `sk-interface-design` into a preset chooser or template generator.\n\n---\n\n## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n\n- Reached the configured lineage cap of 5 iterations.\n- All five key questions have evidence-backed answers in this lineage.\n- Synthesis exists with per-skill adoption verdicts and negative knowledge.\n\n---\n\n## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n\n- Q1 answered: primary evidence was gathered for v0, Lovable, Figma Make, Subframe, plus adjacent Builder/Anima/Framer signals.\n- Q2 answered: net-new patterns are pre-build direction gates, element-target grammar, adherence scanners, editable plan/guideline artifacts, presentational-wrapper boundaries, and explicit visual-test limitations.\n- Q3 answered: see `research.md` sections 7-9 for ADOPT / ADAPT / SKIP verdicts.\n- Q4 answered: negative knowledge is consolidated in `research.md` section 10 and `deep-research-findings-registry.json`.\n- Q5 answered: top recommendations are the direction gate, element-target feedback grammar, design-system adherence scan, presentational/generated boundary, and guidelines artifact.\n\n---\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n## 7. WHAT WORKED\n\n- Primary docs first: official docs for v0, Lovable, Figma Make, and Subframe provided enough feature detail to avoid marketing-only claims.\n- Deduping against packet 005 early kept the recommendation focused on net-new patterns rather than repeating the Claude Design fidelity loop.\n- Separating design judgment (`sk-interface-design`) from canvas/CLI mechanics (`mcp-magicpath`) made ADOPT / ADAPT / SKIP decisions crisp.\n- Treating SKIP as a first-class outcome preserved the anti-default and lean-CLI boundaries.\n\n---\n\n## 8. WHAT FAILED\n\n- A Lovable `visual-edits` URL returned 404; the current docs place that capability under `preview-toolbar.md`.\n- An initial Figma Make article URL resolved to a broader Figma UI3 page; the category and specific article pages supplied the correct Make evidence.\n- Some adjacent-product docs were too broad or marketing-heavy; they were used only as weak corroboration, not as core recommendations.\n- No completed sibling `opus48-claude2` iteration outputs were present when this lineage synthesized, so cross-lineage reconciliation is left to the merge host.\n\n---\n\n## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n\n### Hosted product cloning - BLOCKED (iterations 1-5)\n- What was tried: considered v0 deployment, Lovable Cloud, Figma Make publishing, Framer site publishing, and Anima app hosting.\n- Why blocked: platform hosting and account/workspace governance are outside the two local CLI skills.\n- Do NOT retry: do not recommend hosted deployment, billing, admin, or public publishing features for this packet.\n\n### Preset chooser adoption - BLOCKED (iterations 2 and 5)\n- What was tried: evaluated Lovable design questions and curated palettes/layouts as potential local skill features.\n- Why blocked: copying them as presets conflicts with `sk-interface-design` anti-default rules.\n- Do NOT retry: do not turn design inventory data into a chooser.\n\n### Automated subtle visual diff - BLOCKED (iterations 2 and 5)\n- What was tried: evaluated browser testing as a visual quality gate.\n- Why blocked: Lovable documents browser testing as unreliable for subtle design details.\n- Do NOT retry: use screenshot-supported design judgment, not blind pixel-diff automation, as the fidelity gate.\n\n---\n\n## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n\n- v0-style full-stack deployment/backend agent for these skills: platform scope, not local CLI-skill scope.\n- Lovable-style preset palette/font/layout chooser in `sk-interface-design`: conflicts with anti-default mandate.\n- Figma Make-style local Git branch/PR management in `mcp-magicpath`: belongs to sk-git/workflow tooling.\n- Subframe-style two-way source-of-truth for generated component code: use generated-file plus wrapper boundaries instead.\n- Hosted live multiplayer canvas, public publishing, billing, enterprise admin, or backend setup: out of scope.\n\n---\n\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n\nLineage complete. Merge host should reconcile this `gpt55fast` synthesis with the sibling `opus48-claude2` lineage when available, then produce the packet-level `research/research.md`.\n\n---\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n\n- Packet 005 baseline: shared Claude Design parity protocol (design-context snapshot, iteration ledger, handoff manifest), mcp-magicpath fidelity verification after submit, context intake, and handoff emit are already known.\n- `sk-interface-design` is a judgment skill: it grounds subject/audience/job, builds a compact token system, critiques against AI defaults, and must not become templated.\n- `mcp-magicpath` is a CLI/canvas skill: it discovers, inspects, installs, authors, edits, and imports MagicPath components, and it already delegates aesthetic direction to `sk-interface-design`.\n- `resource-map.md` was absent at the parent spec folder at init; lineage emitted a local evidence resource map from gathered sources.\n\n---\n\n## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n\n- Max iterations: 5.\n- Convergence threshold: 0.05.\n- Stop reason: maxIterationsReached.\n- Output boundary: artifact directory only, per operator instruction.\n- Spec write-back and memory save: skipped/deferred for this isolated fan-out lineage.\n- Lineage: gpt55fast (`cli-opencode` / `openai/gpt-5.5-fast`).\n- Current generation: 1.\n- Started: 2026-06-14T09:20:00Z.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":130,"totalLines":130,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/148-sk-interface-design/006-competitor-design-tools-research/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1781421483405,"end":1781421483408}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f4cdeb1d617d307016a2e55aa4b888191a5974e5d48595a7b"}},"id":"prt_ec4fea17a0014ndKKrr984pZAu","sessionID":"ses_13b0d8207ffeDxrpg470blid9T","messageID":"msg_ec4fe880a001089wduXzCfSMy2"}}
